\id EXO Kapingamarangi
\h Exodus
\toc1 Di Beebaa Exodus
\toc2 Exodus
\toc3 Exo
\mt1 EXODUS
\mt2 Di Beebaa Exodus
\imt1 Di haga modongoohia:
\im Telekai dela bolo \bk Exodus\bk* dono hadinga bolo “E hagatanga gi daha”. Gei di mee deenei le e haga modongoohia nia mee hagalabagau ala i lodo di kai o digau Israel ala nogo hai hege hagahuaidu i lala digau Egypt, ga hagatanga gaa hula gi daha.
\ip Di beebaa deenei e wwae haa:
\ili1 1) Tagalohaa digau Hebrew gi daha mo di nadau noho hege,
\ili1 2) di nadau hula gi di Gonduu Sinai,
\ili1 3) di hagababa ne hai go God i hongo di Gonduu Sinai ang gi ana daangada, mo nia haganoho belee hai hegau ai digaula, mo
\ili1 4) di hau mo di humu haga madamada o di gowaa hai daumaha digau Israel, mo di hai o nnegau o digau hai mee dabu mo nnangaahai e daumaha ang gi God.
\im Di mee koia e hagalabagau la go nia mee a God ne hai, gaa mee ai di hagamehede ana dama nogo mouli huaidu, gaa hai digaula gii hai digau e hai mee gi di hagadagadagagee gi di madagoaa dela digi dae mai.
\ip Tangada hagalabagau i lodo di beebaa deenei la go Moses, tangada dela ne hilihili go God belee lahi digau Israel gi daha mo Egypt. Gei di mee koia e hagalabagau la go nia Haganoho e Madangaholu a God, dela i di mada e 20.
\iot Di hagahonu di beebaa deenei:
\io1 Digau Israel gu maahede gi daha mo Egypt \ior (1.1—15.21)\ior*
\io2 a. Di mouli hai hege i lodo o Egypt \ior (1.1-22)\ior*
\io2 b. Di haanau o Moses mo dono tomo aga \ior (2.1—4.31)\ior*
\io2 c. Moses mo Aaron e heetugi gi di king o Egypt \ior (5.1—11.10)\ior*
\io2 d. Pasoobaa mo di hula gi daha mo Egypt \ior (12.1—15.21)\ior*
\io1 Mai Tai Mmee adu gi di Gonduu Sinai \ior (15.22—18.27) \ior*
\io1 Nnaganoho mono hagababa \ior (19.1—24.18)\ior*
\io1 Di Hale laa o di Hagababa mo di aago di hai e daumaha \ior (25.1—40.38)\ior*
\c 1
\s1 Di haingadaa o digau Israel i Egypt
\p 
\v 1 Aanei la go nia ingoo o nia dama daane o Jacob ala ne hula gi Egypt dalia a mee, nia daane huogodoo mo digau nadau hale:
\v 2 Reuben, Simeon, Levi mo Judah,
\v 3 Issachar, Zebulun mo Benjamin,
\v 4 Dan, Naphtali, Gad mo Asher.
\v 5 Di hagadili o Jacob huogodoo e mada hidu.\f + \fr 1.5 \ft \bk mada hidu\bk*: Di Beebaa Namua dela ne hihi gi lodo nnelekai Greece le e hai bolo \bk mada hidu maa lima\bk* (Acts 7.14)\f* Gei Joseph nogo i Egypt mai hua i mua.
\v 6 Malaa, Joseph mo ono duaahina huogodoo guu mmade mo digau huogodoo o di adu dangada deelaa.
\v 7 Di hagadili o Israel gu dogologowaahee, gei gu maaloo dangihi i hongo tenua go Egypt.\x * \xo 1.7 \xt Acts 7.17\x*
\p 
\v 8 Di king hoou guu dagi Egypt, geia digi iloo ia Joseph,\x * \xo 1.8 \xt Acts 7.18\x*
\v 9 gei mee ga helekai gi ana daangada, “Digau Israel la gu dogologowaahee, digaula ga maaloo dangihi i gidaadou.
\v 10 Gidaadou e hai tadau mee e hai digaula gi de dogologowaahee, ga huli mai digaula ga hagamaamaa tadau hagadaumee ma ga heebagi mai gi gidaadou, gaa lawa ga diiagi tenua deenei.”\x * \xo 1.10 \xt Acts 7.19\x*
\v 11 Malaa, digau Egypt gaa hai gi nia dagi o digau ngalua bolo gi wanga ina nia ngalua kono gi digaula, gei digau Israel gaa hau nia waahale Pithom mo Rameses, e hai ai nia waahale dugu meegai di king.
\v 12 Ma e aha maa nia moomee kono la ne wanga gi digau Israel, gei digaula koia ne hagadili i digaula i mua, gu modoho i nia madagoaa huogodoo i hongo tenua. Gei digau Egypt koia gu mmaadagu i digaula,
\v 13 ga haga ngalua digaula gi nia moomee haingadaa huoloo.
\v 14 Digau Egypt gu hai hua digaula hagauwwou gi nadau moomee haingadaa beenei ala e hai nadau hadu hau hale mono mee ala e haga pigi ai, mo nia hagadilinga ngalua hadagee. Gei digau Egypt hagalee e aloho i digaula.
\p 
\v 15 Di king o Egypt ga helekai gi nia ahina go Shiphrah mo Puah ala e haga hahaanau nia ahina o Hebrew boloo,
\v 16 “Di gulu madagoaa ma ga haga haanau di gulu ahina o Hebrew, gei di maa tama daane, gei goolua daaligidia gii made, gei di maa tama ahina, la dugu ina hua haga mouli.”
\v 17 Gei nia ahina aalaa le e mmaadagu i God, meemaa digi heia di mee di king ne helekai ai gi ginaua, gu haga mouli hua nia dama daane.
\v 18 Di king ga gahi mai nia ahina aalaa, ga heeu gi meemaa, “Goolua ne aha ala ne dugu haga mouli nia dama daane?”
\p 
\v 19 Gei nia ahina aalaa ga helekai gi mee, “Idimaa nia ahina o Hebrew hagalee hai be nia ahina o Egypt. Digaula e haanau ngoohia, e haanau hua gei tei gimaua digi dau adu.”
\v 20-21 Idimaa nia ahina aalaa e mmaadagu i God, gei God e hila anga gi meemaa, gaa wanga gi meemaa nau dama donu. Digau Israel gu haga dili, gu dogologo, ge maaloo huoloo.
\p 
\v 22 Di king gaa hai dana haganoho gi ana daangada huogodoo boloo, “Nia ligiana daane huogodoo o Hebrew la gi kilia gi lodo di monowai Nile, gei nia ligiana ahina dugua haga mouli.”\x * \xo 1.22 \xt Acts 7.19\x*
\c 2
\s1 Di haanau o Moses
\p 
\v 1 Dahi daane i di madawaawa Levi ne lodo gi di ahina dono madawaawa donu.
\v 2 Di ahina ga haanau dana dama daane. Geia gaa mmada bolo dana dama le e humalia huoloo, geia gaa dugu hagammuni a mee i nia malama e dolu.\x * \xo 2.2 \xt Acts 7.20; Hebrews 11.23\x*
\v 3 Dono madagoaa ne deemee di benebene di tama deelaa gi waalooloo, geia ga gaamai dana gada ne llanga gi nia aalek, e hunu gi nia ‘tar’ gi dee ulu nia wai gi lodo. Geia gaa wanga di tama gi no lodo, gaa kae gaa dugu gi lodo di monowai i lodo di waa aalek i taalinga di monowai.
\v 4 Tuaahina ahina o di tama e duu mai mada tanga, e mmada be di maa di aha dela gaa hai gi di tama.
\p 
\v 5 Tama ahina di king ne haneia e gaugau i di monowai, gei ana dama ahina hai hegau e heehee madamada i taalinga di monowai. Mee ga gidee ia di gada i lodo di waa aalek, ga hagau dana dama ahina hai hegau gi gaamai.
\v 6 Tama ahina di king gaa huge di maa, gaa mmada gi di tama e dangidangi. Gei mee ga aloho, ga helekai, “Tama deenei la tama ni digau Hebrew.”
\p 
\v 7 Tuaahina ahina di tama daane ga heeu gi tama ahina di king, “Ma hagalee humalia bolo au ga laha mai dagu ahina Hebrew e benebene dau dama?”
\p 
\v 8 Gei mee ga helekai, “Uaa, e humalia, hana.” Gei mee ga hana hua ga laha mai tinana donu o di tama.
\v 9 Tama ahina di king ga helekai gi tinana, “Lahia di tama deenei, madamada humalia i mee. Au gaa hui laa goe.” Malaa, gei di ahina guu lahi di tama gu benebene.
\p 
\v 10 Gaa dae loo gi di tama gu mada madua, gei mee gaa lahi a mee gi tama ahina di king gii hai dana dama, gei tama ahina gaa gahi di ingoo o maa bolo Moses,\f + \fr 2.10 \fk Moses: \ft Di lee o di ingoo deenei i nnelekai Hebrew le e hai gadoo be di helekai \bk “daa gi daha” \bk*\f*\x * \xo 2.10 \xt Acts 7.21\x* ga helekai boloo, “I mee dela ne daa ko au gi daha mo nia wai.”
\s1 Moses guu lele hagammuni gi Midian
\p 
\v 11 Di madagoaa Moses ne madua aga, gei mee ga haneia gi baahi ono gau donu, ga gidee ia hogi nadau moomee haingadaa ala e hai. Mee gu gidee ia labelaa tangada o Egypt e haga mamaawa dana daane o Hebrew gii made, taane i nia gau donu o Moses.\x * \xo 2.11 \xt Hebrews 11.24\x*
\v 12 Gei mee ga hilahila gi daha be di maa tangada i golo, ge di maa hagalee, geia ga daaligi taane o Egypt gii made, gaa danu a mee gi nia gelegele gii ngala.
\p 
\v 13 Dono daiaa, gei mee gaa hana labelaa ga gidee ia nia daangada dogolua o Hebrew e heebagi. Geia ga heeu gi tangada dela e hala i meemaa, “Goe e aha dela e daaligi do duaahina dangada o Hebrew?”
\p 
\v 14 Gei taane ga helekai, “Ma koai dela ne haga mogobuna goe belee dagi ge e hagi aga gimaua? Goe ga daaligi au be dau hai dela ne hai gi taane o Egypt?” Gei Moses gu madagu, gu hagabaubau boloo, “Dagu mee dela ne hai la guu dele dono longo.”\x * \xo 2.14 \xt Acts 7.23-28\x*
\v 15 Di madagoaa di king ne longono ia di mee deelaa, geia ga halahala dana hai belee daaligi a Moses gii made, gei Moses guu lele hagammuni gi daha mo di king gi tenua go Midian, gaa noho gi lala i baahi di monowai geli.\x * \xo 2.15 \xt Acts 7.29; Hebrews 11.27\x*
\p 
\v 16 Di madagoaa deelaa, gei nia dama ahina dogohidu a Jethro, tangada hai mee dabu o Midian, ga lloomoi gi di monowai geli deelaa belee haga hau nadau mee dugu wai ge e haga inu nia manu di nadau damana.
\v 17 Digau hagaloohi siibi ne loomoi labelaa gi golo, ga hagabagi gi daha nia ahina aalaa, gei Moses ga du gi nua, ga hagamaamaa nia ahina aalaa ga haga inu nia manu digaula.
\v 18 Di madagoaa o nia dama ahina aalaa ne hula gi muli gi baahi di nadau damana go Reuel, gei mee ga heeu gi digaula boloo, “Goodou e aha ala gu lloomoi limalima dangi nei?”
\p 
\v 19 Gei digaula ga helekai anga, “Taane Egypt ne hagamaamaa gimaadou gi daha mo digau hagaloohi siibi i golo. Mee gu haga hau madau wai, gei gu haga inu madau manu labelaa.”
\p 
\v 20 Gei mee ga heeu, “Mee i hee? Goodou ne diiagi a mee eiaha? Gahia mai a mee e miami gidaadou.”
\p 
\v 21 Moses gu hiihai hua gi dono noho i baahi o taane deelaa, gei Jethro gaa wanga Zipporah gi Moses gi lodo ginai.
\v 22 Zipporah gu haanau dana ligiana daane, gei Moses gaa wanga dono ingoo go Gershom,\f + \fr 2.22 \fk Gershom: \ft Di lee o di ingoo deenei i nnelekai Hebrew le e hai gadoo be di bida helekai “tangada mai i daha”.\f* ga helekai, “Au tangada mai i daha i lodo tenua deenei.”
\p 
\v 23 I muli nia ngadau e logo, gei di king o Egypt guu made, gei digau Israel e kono hua igolo i lodo nadau ngalua huaidu, ge e tangitangi bolo God la gi hagamaamaa ina ginaadou. Nia lee o digaula gu dau loo i God,
\v 24 gei Mee gu longono nia madamadau digaula, gu haawe Ia dana hagababa dela ne hai gi Abraham, Isaac mo Jacob.\x * \xo 2.24 \xt Genesis 15.13-14\x*
\v 25 God guu mmada gi digau Israel, gei gu aloho i digaula ala e ngalua kono.
\c 3
\s1 Dimaadua e gahi mai a Moses
\p 
\v 1 Dahi laangi hua, gei Moses nogo madamada humalia i nia manu a Jethro, go tamana dono lodo, go tangada hai mee dabu o Midian, gei mee ne dagi nia manu la gi di baahi dela i golo di anggowaa, gaa dau loo gi Horeb,\f + \fr 3.1 \fk Horeb \ft be \fk Sinai \f* go di gonduu haga madagu a God.
\v 2 Gei tangada di langi o Dimaadua ga gila mai gi mee i lodo di ulaula ahi i lodo di laagau tomo. Gei Moses ga mmada adu gi di laagau le e ulaula, ge di laagau la hagalee wele.\x * \xo 3.2 \xt Acts 7.30-34\x*
\v 3 Moses ga hagabau ang gi deia, “Au ga hagaabo adu gii mmada au gii donu be ma e aha go di laagau dela hagalee wele.”
\p 
\v 4 Dimaadua gaa mmada bolo Moses gu menege mai bolo gi gidee ia donu, gei Mee gaa gahi a mee mai i lodo di laagau boloo, “Moses, Moses.”
\p Gei Moses ga helekai, “Deenei au.”
\p 
\v 5 Gei God ga helekai, “Hudee menege mai gi di gowaa deenei. Daawa o hiiwae la gi daha, idimaa, di gowaa dela e duu iei goe le e haga madagu.
\v 6 Ko Au go di God o damana mmaadua, di God o Abraham, di God o Isaac mo di God o Jacob.”
\p Gei Moses gaa uhi ono golomada, i mee e lliga dana mmada gi God.
\v 7 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai, “Au gu gidee di hagaduadua o agu daangada ala e noho i Egypt, gei Au gu longono nadau dangidangi, ne hidi mai i di gili nadau dagi moomee, gei Au gu iloo nadau hagaduadua.
\v 8 Deelaa ne haneia ei Au, belee lahi digaula gi daha mo nia mogobuna o digau Egypt, e lahi gi tenua humalia ge damana, go tenua tomo ge logo ono meegai, go tenua hogi e noho ai digau Canaan mo Hittite mo Amor, mo digau Perizzite mo Hivite, mo digau Jebus.
\v 9 Au gu longono e Au nia lee o agu dama ala e tangi huoloo i nia hai huaidu o digau Egypt ala e hai gi digaula.
\v 10 Deenei laa Au e hagau goe gi di king o Egypt bolo goe gi dagia mai agu dama Israel gi daha mo Egypt.”
\p 
\v 11 Moses ga heeu gi God, “Au di aha dela belee hana gi di king o Egypt, e dagi mai digau Israel gi daha mo Egypt?”
\p 
\v 12 Gei God ga helekai, “Au ga madalia laa goe. Do madagoaa ma ga laha mai digau Israel gi daha mo Egypt, gei goe ga daumaha mai gi di Au i hongo di gonduu deenei. Deenei di haga modongoohia bolo ma ko Au dela ne hagau goe.”
\p 
\v 13 Moses ga helekai, “Maa au gaa hana gi digau Israel, ga helekai boloo, ‘Di God o godou damana mmaadua ne hagau mai au gi goodou,’ dolomaa digaula ga heeu mai boloo, ‘Di ingoo o Maa koai?’ Gei au ga helekai bolo aha?”\x * \xo 3.13 \xt Exodus 6.2-3\x*
\p 
\v 14 Gei God ga helekai gi Moses, “Ko Au dela ko Au.\f + \fr 3.14 \ft I nnelekai Hebrew di ingoo o Dimaadua go Yihowah le e hai dono lee be di bida helekai “Ko Au dela ko Au” \f* Goe ga helekai gi digaula boloo, Tangada dela e haga ingoo bolo “Ko Au deenei”, go Mee dela ne hagau mai au.\x * \xo 3.14 \xt Revelation 1.4,8\x*
\v 15 Helekai gi digau Israel bolo ma ko Au, go Yihowah, go di God o godou damana mmaadua, di God o Abraham, di God o Isaac mo di God o Jacob, dela ne hagau goe gi ginaadou. Deenei di ingoo o nia adu daangada gi muli e haga ingoo Au ga hana hua dee odi.
\v 16 Hana, haga dagabuli ina nia dagi o digau Israel, hagi anga ina boloo, “Ma go Yihowah, go di God o godou damana mmaadua, di God o Abraham, Isaac mo Jacob gu heetugi mai gi di au.” Hagi anga ina gi digaula boloo, “Au gu gidee nia hai hai huaidu digau Egypt ala e hai adu gi goodou.”
\v 17 Au guu hai bolo Au gaa lahi ginaadou gi daha mo nia hagahuaidu o digau Egypt, e lahi gi tenua o digau Canaan, Hittite, Amor, Perizzite, Hivite, Jebus, gi tenua tomo ge logo ono meegai.
\p 
\v 18 “Gei digaula ga hagalongo adu gi di goe, gei goe gaa hula goodou mo nia dagi digaula gi baahi di king o Egypt, gei goe ga helekai gi mee boloo, ‘Yihowah go di God o digau Hebrew gu heetugi mai gi di au, gei goe dugua mai gimaadou gii hula gi lodo di anggowaa i nia laangi e dolu, e hai madau tigidaumaha ang gi Yihowah di madau God.’
\v 19 Au e iloo bolo di king o Egypt hagalee dumaalia goodou gii hula gi daha mo Egypt, maa Au digi dugu ang gi mee gi haga uaa.
\v 20 Malaa, gei Au ga ngalua gi ogu mogobuna haga goboina e hagaduadua digau Egypt. Nomuli, gei mee ga hagau goodou gii hula.
\p 
\v 21 “Gei Au gaa hai agu daangada gi hagalabagau ina go digau Egypt, gi dee hula hua goodou godou mee ai.\x * \xo 3.21 \xt Exodus 12.35-36\x*
\v 22 Nia ahina Israel huogodoo e hai gi madau nadau goloo gi nadau ihoo ahina Egypt mo digau ala e hoohoo mai nadau hale, ala go nia mee ne hai gi nia silber mono goolo, mo nia goloo gahu, gei goodou ga haga gahu godou dama daane mo dama ahina gi nia goloo o Egypt, gei e kae gi daha nia maluagina digau Egypt.”
\c 4
\s1 Dimaadua e hagi anga ono mogobuna gi Moses
\p 
\v 1 Moses ga helekai gi Dimaadua, “Dolomaa digau Israel la ga hagalee hagadonu au, ga hagalee hagalongo mai, ga helekai mai boloo: Dimaadua la digi haga gidee Ia gi di goe.”
\p 
\v 2 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai, “Ma di aha dela i doo lima?”
\p Gei Moses ga helekai, “Togodogo.”
\p 
\v 3 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai, “Hudua gi hongo di gelegele.”
\p Gei Moses gaa hudu, gei di maa guu huli guu hai di gihaa, gei Moses gu gabadaa gi daha mo di maa.
\v 4 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi mee, “Hagadaudae ina adu doo lima. Kumidia di hugu o maa.”
\p Gei mee gaa kumi, gei di maa guu hai labelaa togodogo i lodo dono lima.
\v 5 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Heia di mee deenei, gei digaula ga haga donu laa bolo ma ko Au dela go Yihowah, go di God o nadau damana mmaadua, go di God o Abraham, di God o Isaac mo di God o Jacob dela ne haga gida adu gi di goe.”
\p 
\v 6 Dimaadua ga helekai labelaa, “Daalo doo lima gi lodo doo gahu.” Gei Moses gu daalo. Dono madagoaa ne haga mmuu mai dono lima gi daha, gei dono lima guu magi genegene, gu kene hua be ‘snow’.
\v 7 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi mee, “Wanga ina labelaa doo lima la gi lodo doo gahu.” Gei Moses guu wanga labelaa, gei di maa guu hili, gu hai hua be di hoo dono lima.
\v 8 Dimaadua ga helekai, “Maa digaula hagalee hagadonu goe i di mogobuna matagidagi, gei digaula ga hagadonu laa i di mogobuna i nomuli.
\v 9 Maa digaula hagalee hagadonu nia mogobuna haga goboina e lua aanei, ge hagalee hagalongo gi au helekai, gei goe ga huai aga au wai i di monowai Nile, gaa dui gi hongo di gelegele maangoo. Nia wai aalaa la gaa huli gaa hai nia dodo.”
\p 
\v 10 Gei Moses ga helekai gi Dimaadua, “Meenei Tagi, Goe hudee hagau ina au. Au tangada de wouwou di leelee. Au mee aanaa e helekai mai gi di au dolomeenei, e deemee labelaa di hai ko au. Au e huaidu dogu helehelekai, e buna gei e nonoogia.”
\p 
\v 11 Dimaadua ga helekai gi mee, “Ma koai dela ne hai di ngudu o tangada? Ma koai dela e hai tangada gi longoduli, ge e hai gi de leelee, be e hai gi gidee ia be gi dee gida? Ma ko Au go Dimaadua!
\v 12 Hana dolomeenei. Au e hana dalia goe e hagamaamaa i dau helehelekai, ga aago adu laa au mee ala e helekai iei goe.”
\p 
\v 13 Gei Moses ga helekai, “Meenei Tagi, dumaalia mai. Hagau ina dau huai dangada e hai dau hegau.”
\p 
\v 14 Gei Dimaadua gu hagawelewele gi Moses, ga helekai, “Do duaahina daane go Aaron tangada o Levi? Au e iloo bolo mee e mee di helekai. Mee gu hanimoi belee heetugi adu gi di goe, gei mee ga tenetene i di gulu madagoaa ma ga heetugi.
\v 15 Goe hagi anga ina nia mee ala belee helekai iei mee. Au ga hagamaamaa laa goolua i lodo gulu helekai, gei Au ga hagi adu nia mee huogodoo ala belee hai go goolua.
\v 16 Mee ga pono laa goe ga helekai i mua digau dogologo, guu ala be go doo ngudu, gei goe guu ala be di God ni mee.
\v 17 Kae ina dau dogodogo dalia goe, deelaa dau mee e hai ai au mogobuna.”
\s1 Moses e hana labelaa gi Egypt
\p 
\v 18 Nomuli gei Moses gaa hana gi muli gi baahi o Jethro go tamana dono lodo, ga helekai gi mee, “Dumaalia mai gi di au e hana gi baahi ogu daangada donu ala e noho i Egypt, gi gidee au be digaula e mouli hua igolo.” Jethro ga helekai, “Hana i di aumaalia.”
\p 
\v 19 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses i Midian, “Hana labelaa gi Egypt, idimaa, digau huogodoo ala bolo e daaligi goe gii made, la guu mmade.”
\v 20 Malaa, Moses ga haga uda dono lodo mo ana dama daane gi hongo di ‘donkey’, gaa hula gi Egypt. Geia e kae togodogo a God ne hai gi mee bolo gi kae ina.
\p 
\v 21 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Goe ma gaa dau i Egypt, gei goe heia nia mogobuna ala ne gowadu ko Au bolo gi heia kooe i mua di king. Au ga haga hamaaloo laa dono manawa gi de hiihai di dugu adu digau Israel gii hula gi daha mo ia.
\v 22 Goe ga helekai gi di king bolo ma ko Au go Dimaadua dela ne helekai boloo, ‘Israel la di tama madua ni aagu.
\v 23 Au ne helekai bolo goe gi dugua digau Israel gii hula e daumaha mai gi di Au, gei goe gu dagalili bolo digaula hagalee hula. Malaa, gei Au ga daaligi dau ulu madua daane gii made.’”\x * \xo 4.23 \xt Exodus 12.29\x*
\p 
\v 24 Dimaadua gu heetugi gi Moses i di gowaa o mee ne hagamolooloo i dono ala nogo hana ai gi Egypt, ga daaligi a mee bolo gii made.
\v 25-26 Gei Zipporah ga dahi aga dana dama hadugalaa gaa, ga sirkumsais dana dama daane, ga hagatale di gilibege ne tuu gi daha gi nia babaawae o Moses. Mai i di hai o di sirkumsais, gei Zipporah ga helekai gi Moses, “Goe go dogu lodo mai i nia dodo.”
\p Gei Dimaadua gu dugu hua a mee gi mouli beelaa.
\p 
\v 27 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Aaron, “Hana e heetugi gi Moses i lodo di anggowaa.” Geia gaa hana ga heetugi gi Moses i baahi di gonduu haga madagu a God, gaa hongi ginaua.
\v 28 Moses ga hagamodongoohia gi Aaron nia mee huogodoo a Dimaadua ala e hagau gineia belee hai, mo nia mogobuna huogodoo bolo gi heia.
\v 29 Malaa, Moses mo Aaron gaa hula gi Egypt, ga haga dagabuli nia dagi o digau Israel huogodoo gi di gowaa e dahi.
\v 30 Gei Aaron gaa kai gi digaula nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hagi anga gi Moses, gei Moses gaa hai labelaa nia mogobuna huogodoo i mua digaula.
\v 31 Digaula gu hagadonu, gei digaula gaa pala gi lala ga daumaha gi Dimaadua, mai i di nadau iloo bolo Dimaadua la gu hanimoi gei gu gidee Ia nadau duadua.
\c 5
\s1 Moses mo Aaron i mua di king o Egypt
\p 
\v 1 Gei nomuli, Moses mo Aaron gaa hula gi di king, ga helekai gi mee, “Yihowah, go di God o digau Israel e helekai boloo, ‘Goe hagamehede ina mai agu daangada gii hula e daumaha mai gi di Au i lodo di anggowaa.’”
\p 
\v 2 Gei di king o Egypt ga heeu, “Yihowah la koai dela bolo au gi hagalongo ang gi de Ia gi hagau ina digau Israel? Au e de iloo eau Yihowah, gei au hogi hagalee hai digau Israel gii hula.”
\p 
\v 3 Gei meemaa ga helekai, “Go di God o digau Hebrew dela ne haga modongoohia Ia mai gi gimaua. Malaa, dugua gimaadou gii hula i nia laangi e dolu i lodo henua, e daumaha gi Yihowah go di madau God, idimaa, ma ga hagalee hai go gimaadou beenei, gei Mee ga hagaduadua gimaadou gi tau magi huaidu, be gi tauwa.”
\p 
\v 4 Di king ga helekai gi meemaa, “Ma di aha dela e hai go goolua e hai nia daangada gi hagatoo gi di nadau moomee? Heia digaula gi moomee labelaa!
\v 5 Goodou gu dogologowaahee i digau donu o tenua deenei, gei goolua bolo goodou gi hagalee ngalua!”
\p 
\v 6 Di laangi hua deelaa, gei di king gaa wanga dana haganoho deenei gi nia daane Egypt ala e dagi nia hege mo nia dagi moomee o Israel boloo:
\v 7 “Guu lawa, hudee wanga ina nia aalek hai hadu gi digaula, digaula gii bida halahala ina nadau aalek hai hadu e ngalua ai ginaadou.
\v 8 Hai gi digaula bolo gi heia nadau hadu hau hale la gi logo be di hulu o nadau mee nogo hai mai mua, hudee heia gi hogoohi, i digaula e hagatoo, dela e hai iei digaula bolo au gi hagau ina ginaadou e daumaha gi di nadau God.
\v 9 Wanga ina nadau moomee gii logo, gi de nohonoho hua digaula, ga longono ginaadou nia agoago dilikai aanei e hai.”
\p 
\v 10 Nia dagi moomee o Egypt mo nia dagi moomee Israel gaa hula ga helekai gi digau Israel, “Di king bolo ia gu hagalee gowadu nia aalek hai hadu gi goodou.
\v 11 Mee e helekai bolo goodou gii bida halahala ina hua godou mee, gei goodou gi heia godou hadu hau hale gii logo be di hulu o godou mee ala nogo hai mai mua.”
\v 12 Malaa, digau Israel guu hula gu modoho gi daha i lodo Egypt belee halahala mai nadau aalek hai hadu.
\v 13 Nia dagi moomee Egypt gaa hono digaula bolo gi heia nia hadu hau hale gii logo be di madagoaa nia aalek hai hadu nogo wanga gi digaula.
\v 14 Nia dagi moomee Egypt e haga mamaawa nia dagi moomee o Israel ala ne dugu go ginaadou, mo di wwou gi digaula boloo, “Nia hadu dangi nei le e aha ala hagalee logo be di maa nogo hai mai mua?”
\p 
\v 15 Gei nia dagi moomee o Israel gaa hula gaa hai nadau donu gi di king boloo, “Meenei di king, ma di aha dela e hai mai kooe gi gimaadou?
\v 16 Gimaadou gu hagalee gaamai ginai nia aalek hai hadu, ge e hai bolo gimaadou gi heia madau hadu! Gei gimaadou e dadaaligi labelaa. Ma go au daangada donu o do henua ala e hala.”
\p 
\v 17 Gei di king ga helekai, “Goodou digau hagatoo ge e de hiihai di ngalua dela e tangitangi mai ai goodou bolo au gi heia goodou gii hula e daumaha gi Dimaadua.
\v 18 Hula gi di godou moomee gi ngalua goodou! Gei di aalek hai hadu e dahi e gowadu ai, gei goodou heia godou hadu hau hale gii logo be di hulu dela ne dugu.”
\v 19 Nia dagi moomee o Israel gu iloo bolo ginaadou guu noho i lodo di hagaduadua, idimaa di king dela gu helekai bolo ginaadou gi heia i nia laangi huogodoo nia hadu hau hale gii logo be di hulu dela guu dugu mai mua bolo gi heia.
\p 
\v 20 I di nadau lawa i baahi o mee, gei digaula ga heetugi gi Moses mo Aaron ala e talitali ginaadou.
\v 21 Digaula ga helekai gi meemaa, “Dimaadua gu gidee Ia di gulu mee ne hai mai gi gimaadou, ge Ia hogi ga hagaduadua goolua, idimaa nia mee a di king mo ana gau aamua la ne hai mai gi gimaadou la ne hidi mai goolua. E ala be goolua ne wanga nia hulumanu dauwa gi nia lima o digaula belee daaligi gimaadou gii mmade.”
\s1 Moses e hai ono donu gi Dimaadua
\p 
\v 22 Moses gaa huli gi Dimaadua, ga helekai, “Meenei Tagi, Goe e hagaduadua au dama beleiaha? Goe ne hagau mai au gi kinei eiaha?
\v 23 Mai loo i taamada ogu hana gi baahi di king ga helehelekai i do ingoo, gei mee hagalee lawa dana haga hagaduadua au daangada, gei Goe hagalee hagamaamaa digaula!”
\c 6
\p 
\v 1 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Dolomeenei gei goe ga gidee be dagu maa di aha dela gaa hai gi di king. Au gaa hono a mee gi dugua anga agu daangada gii hula. Au gaa hono a mee gi hagabagia digaula gi daha mo dono henua.”
\s1 God e gahi a Moses
\p 
\v 2 God ga helekai gi Moses, “Au go Yihowah.\x * \xo 6.2 \xt Genesis 17.1; 28.3; 35.11; Exodus 3.13-15\x*
\v 3 Au gu haga gida gi Abraham, Isaac mo Jacob gadoo be di God Mogobuna, gei Au digi heia digaula gi iloo ginaadou dogu ingoo haga madagu go Yihowah.
\v 4 Au guu hai labelaa dagu hagababa gi digaula, bolo e wanga tenua Canaan gi digaula, tenua dela nogo noho ai digaula be digau mai i daha.
\v 5 Dolomeenei, gei Au gu longono e Au nia lee duadua o digau Israel ala e haga hai hege go digau Egypt, gei Au gu maanadu aga dagu hagababa dela ne hai.
\v 6 Helekai gi digau Israel bolo Au e helekai gi digaula boloo, ‘Au go Yihowah, Au gaa daa goodou gi daha mo godou hai hege go digau Egypt. Au ga dahi aga dogu lima maaloo dangihi ga hagaduadua digaula, gei Au ga benebene goodou.
\v 7 Au gaa hai goodou gii hai nia daangada ni aagu, gei Au gaa hai di godou God. Goodou ga iloo bolo ma ko Au go Yihowah go di godou God i dogu madagoaa ma ga hagamehede goodou gi daha mo di hai hege i Egypt.
\v 8 Au ga laha mai goodou gi tenua dela ne hagababa hagahumalia belee wanga gi Abraham, Isaac mo Jacob, gei Au ga gowadu di maa gi goodou e hai mee ginai. Au go Yihowah.’”
\p 
\v 9 Moses ga hagi anga nia helekai aanei gi digau Israel, gei digaula digi hagalongo gi mee, idimaa, nadau hagataalunga la gu haga mooho go nia haingadaa llauehe o nadau hai hege huaidu.
\p 
\v 10 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses,
\v 11 “Hana helekai gi di king o Egypt bolo ia e hai loo digau Israel gi hagatanga gi daha mo dono henua.”
\p 
\v 12 Moses ga helekai, “Digau Israel hogi hagalee e hagalongo gi agu helekai, gei di king la belee hagalongo mai behee? Au tangada dela e de iloo di helehelekai.”
\p 
\v 13 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses mo Aaron, “Helekai gi digau Israel mo di king o Egypt bolo Au gu hagawaalanga adu gi goolua bolo gi dagia digau Israel gi daha mo Egypt.”
\s1 Di beebaa madahaanau Moses mo Aaron
\p 
\v 14 Reuben, tama daane madua Jacob, guu hai ana dama daane dogo haa: Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, mo Carmi. Digaula la nia maadua mmaadua o nia madahaanau llauehe ala e hai hegau gi nadau ingoo.
\p 
\v 15 Simeon ana dama daane dogo ono: Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar mo Shaul; tinana Shaul la di ahina Canaan. Digaula la nia maadua mmaadua o nia madahaanau llauehe ala e hai hegau gi nadau ingoo.
\p 
\v 16 Levi ana dama daane dogo dolu: Gershon, Kohath mo Merari. Digaula la nia maadua mmaadua o nia madahaanau llauehe ala e hai hegau gi nadau ingoo. Levi nogo mouli nia ngadau e 137.\x * \xo 6.16 \xt Numbers 3.17-20; 26.57-58; 1-Chronicles 6.16-19\x*
\p 
\v 17 Gershon ana dama daane dogo lua: Libni mo Shimei, meemaa e logo nau hagadili.
\p 
\v 18 Kohath ana dama daane dogo haa: Amram, Izhar, Hebron mo Uzziel. Kohath nogo mouli nia ngadau e 133.
\p 
\v 19 Merari ana dama daane dogolua: Mahli mo Mushi. Aanei go nia madahaanau llauehe a Levi mo nadau hagadili.
\p 
\v 20 Amram ne lodo gi tuaahina ahina o dono damana go Jochebed ga haanau gi mee ana dama daane dogolua go Aaron mo Moses. Amram nogo mouli nia ngadau e 137.
\v 21 Izhar ana dama daane dogo dolu: Korah, Nepheg mo Zichri.
\v 22 Uzziel ana dama daane dogo dolu: Mishael, Elzaphan mo Sithri.
\p 
\v 23 Aaron ne lodo gi Elisheba, tama ahina Amminadab gei tuaahina ahina o Nahshon, ga haanau gi mee ana dama daane dogohaa go Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar mo Ithamar.
\p 
\v 24 Korah ana dama daane dogo dolu: Assir, Elkanah mo Abiasaph. Digaula la nia maadua mmaadua o nia manga di madahaanau damana o Korah.
\p 
\v 25 Eleazar tama daane Aaron guu lodo gi tama ahina e dahi a Putiel dela ga haanau gi mee dana dama daane go Phinehas. Aanei nia libogo o nia madahaanau lligi mo llauehe o di madawaawa Levi.
\p 
\v 26 Aaron mo Moses la nia daangada ne helekai ginai Dimaadua, “Dagia mai nia madawaawa Israel gi daha mo Egypt.”
\v 27 Meemaa go nia daane ala ne helekai gi di king o Egypt bolo gi hagamehede ina digau Israel.
\s1 Taganoho a Dimaadua ang gi Moses mo Aaron
\p 
\v 28 Di madagoaa Dimaadua ne helekai gi Moses i hongo tenua go Egypt,
\v 29 Mee ga helekai boloo, “Ko Au go Dimaadua. Goe hagi anga ina gi di king o Egypt agu mee huogodoo ala e hagi adu gi di goe.”
\p 
\v 30 Gei Moses ga helekai, “Goe e iloo hua bolo au tangada hua de wouwou di helekai, gei di king o Egypt e hagalongo mai gi di au behee?”
\c 7
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Mmada, Au gaa hai goe gii hai be God i mua di king o Egypt, gei do duaahina daane go Aaron gaa hai be di soukohp ni aau.
\v 2 Goe ga helekai gi Aaron i agu mee huogodoo ala e hagi adu, gei mee ga helekai gi di king o Egypt bolo gi heia digau Israel gii hula gi daha mo dono henua.
\v 3-4 Gei Au ga haga hamaaloo di manawa o di king gi de hagalongo adu gi goolua, dehei eia agu mogobuna haga goboina e logo ala e hai i lodo tenua go Egypt. Au ga hagaduadua digau Egypt hagahuaidu, nomuli gei Au gaa dagi agu dama Israel gi daha mo Egypt.\x * \xo 7.3-4 \xt Acts 7.36\x*
\v 5 Gei digau Egypt ga iloo ginaadou bolo ma ko Au go Dimaadua, i di daahi dogu lima gi nua e hai baahi gi Egypt, mo di laha mai nia dama o Israel gi daha mo ginaadou.”
\p 
\v 6 Nia mee a Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses mo Aaron bolo gi heia, guu hai huogodoo go meemaa.
\v 7 Di madagoaa dela e leelee ai meemaa gi di king, gei Moses gu huowalu ono ngadau gei Aaron gu huowalu maa dolu.
\s1 Togodogo mogobuna a Aaron
\p 
\v 8 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses mo Aaron,
\v 9 “Dolomaa di king gaa hai adu bolo goolua gi heia gulu mogobuna, e haga modongoohia ai goolua, gei goe ga helekai gi Aaron bolo gi hudua dana dogodogo la gii doo i mua di king, ge togodogo la gaa hai di gihaa.”
\p 
\v 10 Moses mo Aaron gaa hula gi baahi di king, gaa hai nia mee a Dimaadua ne hai ang gi ginaua. Aaron ga hudu adu dana dogodogo la gi mua di king mo ana gau aamua, gei togodogo la guu hai di gihaa.
\v 11 Gei di king ga gahi mai ana gau kabemee mono gau hai buubuu o Egypt, gaa hai nadau mogobuna be di maa.
\v 12 Digaula gaa kili nadau dogodogo la gi hongo tenua gei nia maa guu hai nia gihaa. Gei togodogo Aaron gaa holo nia dogodogo digaula.
\v 13 Gei di king koia gu hamaaloo dangihi dono manawa, koia gu hagalee hagalongo gi meemaa gadoo be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai.
\s1 Nia haingadaa guu dau i Egypt
\s2 Nia dodo
\p 
\v 14 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Di king o Egypt guu lodo hamaaloo hua, mee e de hiihai e diiagi digaula gii hula.
\v 15 Hana haga luada gi di monowai Nile, heetugi gi mee i dono madagoaa dela e hana ai gi di monowai deelaa. Kae ina dau dogodogo dela ne hai di gihaa dalia goe, taalia a mee i di gili di monowai.
\v 16 Goe helekai gi mee boloo, ‘Yihowah go di God o digau Hebrew ne hagau mai au gi hai adu bolo goe gi diagia ana daangada gii hula, e daumaha ang gi de Ia i lodo di anggowaa, gei goe digi hagalongo gaa dae mai loo gi dolomeenei.
\v 17 Deelaa laa gei Dimaadua ga helekai boloo, “Deenei dau mee ga iloo bolo Au go Yihowah.” Mmada, au ga hagamaawa nia wai o di monowai deenei gi togodogo dela i dogu lima, gei nia wai gaa huli gaa hai nia dodo.\x * \xo 7.17 \xt Revelation 16.4\x*
\v 18 Gei nia iga o di monowai deenei gaa mmade ga haga bilau di maa, gei digau Egypt ga ginagina di inu i di maa.’”
\p 
\v 19 Dimaadua ga helekai labelaa gi Moses, “Hagi anga ina gi Aaron bolo gi daahi aga ina dana dogodogo gi nua ang gi nia monowai huogodoo o Egypt, nia monowai llauehe mo lligi, mo nia madapua. Gei nia maa gaa huli gaa hai nia dodo i hongo tenua hagatau. Nia wai hogi ala i lodo nia baisin laagau mo nia loaabi hadu gaa hai nia dodo.”
\v 20 Moses mo Aaron guu hai gii hai be nia helekai a Dimaadua. Gei Aaron ga daahi aga togodogo ga hagamaawa nia wai o di monowai i mua di king mo ana gau aamua, gei nia wai la guu huli guu hai nia dodo.
\v 21 Nia iga o lodo di monowai deelaa guu mmade, di monowai gu bilau huoloo, gei digau Egypt gu deemee di inu i di monowai. Nia monowai i Egypt huogodoo guu honu dodo.
\v 22 Gei digau hai mogobuna o Egypt guu hai hogi nadau mogobuna beelaa, gei di hamaaloo o di manawa o di king koia gu hamaaloo mai. Mee hagalee loo e hagalongo gi Moses mo Aaron, guu hai gadoo be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai.
\v 23 Gei di king gaa huli gaa hana gi dono hale, gei di mee ne haga ngalua dono manawa i nia mee aanei ai.
\v 24 Malaa, digau Egypt gu geligeli nadau madapua i daha mo di monowai belee inu ai ginaadou. Idimaa digaula gu deemee di inu nia wai o di monowai damana.
\p 
\v 25 Nia laangi e hidu i muli o Dimaadua ne hagamaawa di monowai, gei di lua hagaduadua gaa hai.
\c 8
\s2 Nia kailuu
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hana gi di king, helekai gi mee boloo, ‘Aanei nnelekai Dimaadua: Diagia agu daangada gii hula, e daumaha mai gi di Au.
\v 2 Maa goe ga hagalee hai digaula gii hula, gei Au ga hagahuaidu goodou gi nia kailuu gii honu i hongo do henua hagatau.
\v 3 Nia kailuu ga logowaahee i lodo di monowai Nile, ga lloo aga gi lodo doo hale, mo lodo do ruum kii, mo hongo doo hada, mo lodo nia hale oo gau aamua mo au daangada, mo lodo au mee daa palaawaa, mo au gowaa hai meegai.
\v 4 Nia maa gaa hobo gi oo nua mo hongo au daangada mo au gau aamua huogodoo.’”
\p 
\v 5 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hagi anga ina gi Aaron bolo gi daahia gi nua dono lima mo dana dogodogo gi nia monowai lligi mo llauehe, mono madapua gi lloo aga nia kailuu gi hongo tenua go Egypt.”
\v 6 Gei Aaron ga daahi dono lima gi hongo nia monowai o Egypt, gei nia kailuu gu lloo aga, gu buni hua i hongo tenua go Egypt.
\v 7 Gei digau hai mogobuna o Egypt guu hai nadau mogobuna, guu hai nia kailuu gi lloo aga labelaa gi hongo tenua go Egypt.
\v 8 Di king ga gahi aga a Moses mo Aaron ga helekai gi meemaa, “Dalodalo ina mua gi Dimaadua bolo gi heia nia kailuu aanei la gi daha, gei au laa ga dumaalia adu gulu daangada gii hula, e hai nadau tigidaumaha gi Dimaadua.”
\p 
\v 9 Moses ga helekai, “Au ga tenetene di dalodalo i di goe. Goe laa gi hilihilia dau madagoaa dela e hiihai ginai goe bolo au gi dalodalo i di goe mo au gau aamua mo au daangada, gi heia nia kailuu gi daha mo goodou mo godou hale, nia kailuu e dubu i golo ai aalaa hua i lodo di monowai Nile.”
\v 10 Di king ga helekai, “Goe dalodalo i di au daiaa.”
\p Gei Moses ga helekai, “Au gaa hai gii hai be au helekai, bolo gi modongoohia e goe bolo ma deai di God i golo e hai be Dimaadua go di madau God ai.
\v 11 Nia kailuu la gaa hula gi daha mo goe mo oo hale mo au gau aamua mo au daangada, deai nia kailuu e dubu i golo ai aalaa hua i lodo di monowai Nile.”
\p 
\v 12 Di hagatanga hua Moses mo Aaron i baahi di king, gei Moses ga dalodalo gi Dimaadua bolo gi heia gi daha nia kailuu ala ne hagau mai go Mee gi di king.
\v 13 Gei Dimaadua gu haga gila talodalo a Moses, malaa, nia kailuu ala nogo i lodo nia hale mo i lodo nia hadagee mo lodo henua huogodoo la guu mmade.
\v 14 Gei digau Egypt ga hagabae mai nia kailuu guu hai nia hagabae llauehaa gu haga bilau tenua.
\v 15 Di king ga iloo ia bolo nia kailuu la guu mmade, geia gu hamaaloo labelaa dono manawa, gu hagalee hagalongo labelaa gi Moses mo Aaron gadoo be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai.
\s2 Nia lamu gai dangada
\p 
\v 16 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hai gi Aaron bolo gi hagamaawa dia di gelegele gi dana dogodogo, gei nia gelegele gaa huli gaa hai nia lamu gai dangada i hongo Egypt hagatau.”
\v 17 Gei Aaron ga hagamaawa di gelegele gi dana dogodogo. Nia gelegele o Egypt huogodoo guu hai nia lamu, gu buni hua i nia gili o nia daangada mono manu.
\v 18 Digau hai mogobuna guu hai nadau mogobuna labelaa bolo gii hai nia lamu, ge deemee. Nia lamu gu honu hua i nia gowaa huogodoo,
\v 19 gei digau hai mogobuna ga helekai gi di king, “Di mee deelaa di mee mai God!” Gei di king e lodo hamaaloo hua igolo, hagalee loo e hagalongo gi Moses mo Aaron be nnelekai Dimaadua ala ne hai.\x * \xo 8.19 \xt Luke 11.20\x*
\s2 Nia lamu
\p 
\v 20 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hana haga luada heetugi gi di king o Egypt i di madagoaa o mee dela e hana ai gi di monowai, helekai gi mee boloo, ‘Dimaadua gu helekai bolo goe gi hagau ina agu daangada gii hula digaula gi daumaha mai gi di Au.
\v 21 Maa goe ga hagalee hagau digaula, gei Au ga hagaduadua goe, Au ga hagau adu nia lamu gi doo gili, mo au gau aamua mo au daangada. Nia hale o digau Egypt gaa honu lamu mo nia gelegele o tenua gaa gahu gi nia maa.
\v 22 Gei Au e loohi di guongo go Goshen dela e noho ai agu daangada, gi dee hai nia lamu. Au e hai beenei gi iloo e goe bolo ma ko Au go Dimaadua dela e ngalua i tenua deenei.
\v 23 Au gaa wwae gi daha agu daangada mo au daangada. Di mogobuna deenei le e gila aga daiaa.’”
\p 
\v 24 Dimaadua guu hai di mee deenei, nia lamu gu ulu gi lodo di hale o di king mo nia hale o ono gau aamua. Egypt hagatau gu hagahuaidu hua go nia lamu aalaa.
\p 
\v 25 Di king ga gahi mai a Moses mo Aaron, ga helekai gi meemaa boloo, “Goolua hula, tigidaumaha gi di gulu God i lodo tenua deenei.”
\p 
\v 26 Moses ga helekai, “Deemee di hai beenaa, idimaa tigidaumaha manu dela e hai go gimaadou ang gi Dimaadua go di madau God, le e haga lodo huaidu digau Egypt. Maa gimaadou ga hai hegau gi nia manu ala e hagahuaidu nadau manawa, ga tigidaumaha iei gimaadou, gaa mmada ginai digaula, gei ogo digaula ga dilidili gimaadou gii mmade.
\v 27 Gimaadou belee hula gi lodo di anggowaa i lodo nia laangi e dolu e tigidaumaha gi Dimaadua go di madau God, be nia helekai a Mee ala ne hai mai gi gimaadou.”
\p 
\v 28 Di king ga helekai, “Au ga hagau goodou e daumaha gi Dimaadua go di godou God i di anggowaa dela e hoohoo mai, hagalee mogowaa. Dalodalo laa i di au.”
\p 
\v 29 Gei Moses ga helekai, “Di madagoaa hua dela ga hagatanga iei au i ginei, gei au ga dalodalo gi Dimaadua, gei daiaa nia lamu gaa hula gi daha mo goe mo au gau aamua mo au daangada huogodoo. Goe hudee halahalau ina labelaa gimaadou be dugu gimaadou ala belee hula e daumaha gi Dimaadua.”
\p 
\v 30 Moses ga hagatanga gi daha mo di king gaa hana, ga dalodalo ang gi Dimaadua.
\v 31 Gei Dimaadua gu dumaalia gi talodalo a Moses ne hai. Nia lamu gu de igolo i baahi di king mo digau aamua mo di gau huogodoo. Di lamu e dahi ne dubu i golo ai.
\v 32 Gei di king gu haga hamaaloo ono lodo hua igolo, hagalee hagau digau Israel.
\c 9
\s2 Di mmade o nia manu
\p 
\v 1 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hana, hai gi di king o Egypt bolo Yihowah go di God o digau Hebrew le e helekai boloo, ‘Heia agu daangada gii hula gi daumaha mai gi di Au.
\v 2 Maa goe ga daahi hua digaula gi dee hula,
\v 3 gei Au ga daaligi au manu gii mmade: nia hoodo, ‘donkey’, ‘camel’, kau, siibi mono kuudi.
\v 4 Au e wwae gi daha nia manu digau Israel mo nia manu digau Egypt, deai di manu e dahi e made i nia manu o digau Israel ai.
\v 5 Ma ko Au go Dimaadua dela gu helekai bolo daiaa gei Au gaa hai di mee deenei.’”
\p 
\v 6 Dono daiaa, gei Dimaadua gaa hai ana mee ala nogo helekai ai. Nia manu o Egypt guu mmade huogodoo, deai di manu e dahi ne made i nia manu o digau Israel ai.
\v 7 Di king ga hagau digau hagadina be ma guu hai behee, gei digaula ga helekai bolo ma deai di manu e dahi ne made i nia manu o digau Israel ai. Gei dono manawa e hamaaloo hua igolo, hagalee hagau digau Israel gii hula.
\s2 Tau magi bala
\p 
\v 8 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses mo Aaron, “Kae ina gulu luaahi gii honu gulu babaalima, hula gi mua di king o Egypt, gei Moses gaa mmaga nia maa gi di ahiaalangi i mua di king.
\v 9 Gei nia luaahi la ga modoho i lodo o Egypt gadoo be nia gohu gelegele, ga haga dogo mahana nia gili o nia daangada mo nia manu gi hidi ai nia magibala.”
\v 10 Gei meemaa gaa kae nau luaahi gaa tuu i mua di king, gei Moses gaa mmaga nia luaahi gi lodo di ahiaalangi, gei nia daangada mo nia manu gu magibala.\x * \xo 9.10 \xt Revelation 16.2\x*
\v 11 Digau hai mogobuna gu deemee di lloomoi e tuu i baahi o Moses, idimaa digaula guu buni magibala be digau Egypt huogodoo ala i golo.
\v 12 Gei ogo Dimaadua gu haga hamaaloo di manawa o di king gi de hagalongo a mee gi Moses mo Aaron, be nnelekai Dimaadua ala ne hai.
\s2 Di uwa hadu magalillili
\p 
\v 13 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hana hagaluada, hai gi di king o Egypt boloo: Yihowah go di God o digau Hebrew le e helekai boloo, ‘Dugua agu daangada gii hula e daumaha mai gi di Au.
\v 14 Tolongo deenei, gei agu hagaduadua la ga hagalee hai hua ang gi au gau aamua mo au daangada, gaa hai labelaa adu gi di goe, gi modongoohia e goe bolo ma deai di God i henuailala e hai be Au ai.
\v 15 Maa nei bolo Au ne hagaabo hua ogu lima bolo e hagahuaidu goe mo au daangada, gei goodou guu mmade huogodoo gi daha mo henuailala.
\v 16 Gei Au e dugu goe haga mouli, belee haga modongoohia ogu mogobuna, gii dele dogu ingoo i henuailala hagatau.\x * \xo 9.16 \xt Romans 9.17\x*
\v 17 Gei goe e hagamuamua ge hagalee dugu agu daangada gii hula.
\v 18 Di madagoaa beenei daiaa, gei Au ga haga doo dagu uwa hadu magalillili, tagadilinga mee digi gila mai loo i taamada o Egypt, gaa dae mai loo gi dolomeenei.
\v 19 Malaa, hagau ina au gau e haga malu au manu mo au mee huogodoo ala i malaelae gi lodo nia hale, idimaa di uwa hadu magalillili gaa doo gi hongo nia daangada mono manu huogodoo ala i daha mo nia hale, gei digaula gaa mmade huogodoo.’”
\p 
\v 20 Malaa, hunu gau aamua o di king gu mmaadagu i nia helekai a Dimaadua, gei digaula gu haga malu nadau gau hai hegau mo nadau manu gi lodo nia hale.
\v 21 Gei hunu gau hagalee haga dahidamee nnelekai Dimaadua, ginaadou hagalee haga malu nadau gau hai hegau mo nadau manu.
\p 
\v 22 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Holohia gi nua doo lima gi di langi gii doo di uwa hadu magalillili gi hongo Egypt hagatau, gi hongo nia daangada mono manu mo nia laagau tomo huogodoo o lodo henua.”
\v 23-24 Malaa, Moses ga daahi dana dogodogo gi di langi, gei Dimaadua ga dugu ia nia atili mo dono uwa hadu magalillili, gei ogo di ila gu dabadaba gi di gelegele. Dimaadua ga hagau mai dana madangi maaloo mono ila ala e mamaahina gi mua mo muli. Deenei hua di uwa hadu huaidu ne hai i hongo Egypt, digi hai loo beelaa mai loo i taamada.\x * \xo 9.23-24 \xt Revelation 8.7; 16.21\x*
\v 25 Di uwa hadu magalillili la gu daaligi nia mee ala i daha mo nia hale, go nia daangada mo nia manu huogodoo. Ma guu hai nia geinga tomo o lodo henua mono laagau huogodoo la gi momooho.
\v 26 Gei tenua go Goshen dela e noho ai digau Israel digi tale ginai di uwa hadu magalillili deelaa.
\p 
\v 27 Di king ga gahi mai a Moses mo Aaron, ga helekai, “Au gu hai hala dolomeenei, gei Dimaadua la guu donu, au mo agu daangada le e huaidu.
\v 28 Goolua dalodalo gi Dimaadua i gimaadou bolo nia atili mo di uwa hadu magalillili aanei la gi hagalee. Au gaa hai goodou gii hula, hagalee noho i ginei.”
\p 
\v 29 Gei Moses ga helekai gi mee, “Di madagoaa hua ga hagatanga iei au gi daha mo di waahale, gei au ga daahi ogu lima mo di dalodalo gi Dimaadua, gei nia atili gaa noho, gei nia uwa hadu magalillili la ga hagalee, gei goe ga iloo laa bolo henuailala la di mee ni Dimaadua.
\v 30 Gei au gu iloo bolo goe mo au gau aamua digi mmaadagu i Yihowah-God\f + \fr 9.30 \ft Di ingoo o God deenei le e hai dono hadinga bolo “Yihowah di God dela e noho i baahi ana daangada”\f*.”
\p 
\v 31 Nia laagau ‘flax’ mo nia ‘barley’ la guu mmade, idimaa nia ‘barley’ la gu mmaadua, gei nia ‘flax’ la gu matili aga.
\v 32 Gei nia huwa o nia ‘wheat’ la digi huaidu, idimaa, nia maa digi mmaadua.
\v 33 Gei Moses ga hagatanga i baahi di king gaa hana gi daha mo di waahale. Mee ga daahi aga ono lima ga dalodalo gi Dimaadua, gei nia atili mo di uwa hadu magalillili mo di uwa guu noho.
\v 34 Di madagoaa o di king o Egypt ne iloo ia bolo di uwa mo di uwa hadu magalillili mono atili guu noho, geia mo ana gau aamua gu haga hamaaloo labelaa nadau manawa.
\v 35 Gei mee digi hai digau Israel la gii hula, guu hai be nnelekai Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses.
\c 10
\s2 Nia manu ‘locust’
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hana gi baahi di king o Egypt, i di Au gu haga hamaaloo ono lodo mo lodo ana gau hai hegau bolo gii mee Au di haga modongoohia aga ogu mogobuna haga goboina aanei i mua digaula,
\v 2 gei goe gi hagi anga ina labelaa gi au dama mo nadau dama i dogu hagahinihini digau Egypt gi ogu mogobuna, bolo gi iloo e goodou bolo ma ko Au go Yihowah.”
\p 
\v 3 Moses mo Aaron gaa hula, ga helekai gi di king, “Yihowah go di God o digau Hebrew e helekai boloo, ‘Gu waalooloo behee go do hagalee hagalongo mai gi di Au? Heia agu daangada la gii hula e daumaha mai gi di Au.
\v 4 Maa goe ga hagalee hai digaula gii hula, daiaa gei Au ga hagau mai nia manu ‘locust’ gi di godou henua,
\v 5 ga logowaahee i lodo henua, gei tenua la gaa gahu hua go nia maa, gaa gai nia mee huogodoo ala digi mmade i di uwa hadu magalillili, mono laagau hogi ala e tomo hua igolo i lodo henua.
\v 6 Gei nia manu ‘locust’ gaa honu i lodo oo hale mo lodo nia hale o au gau aamua mo au daangada huogodoo. Nia maa koia ga huaidu i nia hagahuaidu ala gu gidee ai godou damana mmaadua i mua.’” Nomuli, gei Moses guu huli guu hana.
\p 
\v 7 Digau aamua o di king ga helekai gi mee, “Nia daane aanei le e waalooloo behee i di nau haga de aadee gidaadou? Heia nia daane Israel gii hula gi daumaha ang gi Dimaadua go di nadau God. Goe e de iloo bolo Egypt la gu mooho?”
\p 
\v 8 Moses mo Aaron ga gahi mai labelaa gi mua di king, gei di king ga helekai gi meemaa, “Goodou guu mee hua di hula e daumaha gi Dimaadua di godou God, malaa koai ala gaa hula?”
\p 
\v 9 Moses ga helekai, “Gimaadou huogodoo e hula, digau lligi mono gau mmaadua, mono damagiigi daane mo ahina, mo madau siibi, madau kuudi, mo madau kau, idimaa, gimaadou huogodoo e hai loo gii hai di madau daumaha hagamiami ang gi Dimaadua.”
\p 
\v 10 Gei di king ga helekai, “Au e hai dagu hagamodu gi Dimaadua bolo au hagalee dugu adu nia ahina mono dama gii hula goodou! Ma gu modongoohia bolo goolua e haga noho di gulu hai huaidu i gulu lodo.
\v 11 Malaa, deeai! Aalaa hua go nia daane ala e mee di hula e daumaha gi Dimaadua, be di maa deelaa di gulu mee e hiihai ginai.” Gei Moses mo Aaron ga hagabagi gi daha mo di king.
\p 
\v 12 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Daahia aga ina doo lima laa hongo Egypt, gei nia ‘locust’ ga lloomoi gi hongo Egypt, gaa gai nia mee huogodoo ala digi mmade i di uwa hadu magalillili.”
\v 13 Gei Moses ga daahi dana dogodogo gi nua, gei Dimaadua gaa hai di madangi gi angiangi mai i dua i di laangi deelaa mo di boo deelaa, gei dono luada gei di madangi deelaa gu haga maangi mai nia ‘locust’.
\v 14 Gu logowaahee hua be di aha i hongo Egypt hagatau. Di logowaahee beenei ne gila mai mua ai, ge hagalee gila labelaa beelaa maalia.\x * \xo 10.14 \xt Revelation 9.2-3\x*
\v 15 Tenua la guu gahu hua go nia maa, guu buni gei guu gai nia huwa laagau mono lau mo nia mee huogodoo ala digi huaidu i muli di uwa hadu magalillili. Deai di lau laagau e dahi ne dubu i hongo Egypt ai.
\p 
\v 16 Di king ga hagalimalima hua ga gahi mai a Moses mo Aaron ga helekai gi meemaa, “Au gu hai hala gi Dimaadua go di gulu God mo adu gi goolua.
\v 17 Goolua dumaalia mai gi di au, gei dalodalo gi Dimaadua go di gulu God, bolo gi daawa di hagahuaidu deenei gi daha mo au.”
\v 18 Moses ga hagatanga i baahi di king gaa hana ga dalodalo ang gi Dimaadua.
\v 19 Gei Dimaadua gaa hai di madangi gi gono aga i dai, gaa hai nia ‘locust’ gi mmaangi gi lodo Tai Mmee.\f + \fr 10.19 \fk Tai Mmee: \ft Di ingoo Hebrew di tai deenei go Yam Suph, dono hadinga bolo di Tai o nia Aalek\f* Deai di ‘locust’ e dahi ne dubu i lodo tei madagoaa i lodo o Egypt ai.
\v 20 Gei Dimaadua e haga hamaaloo hua igolo lodo o di king o Egypt, deelaa di mee a mee hagalee hai digau Israel gii hula.
\s2 Di langi bouli dongoeho
\p 
\v 21 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Daahia doo lima gi di langi, gei di bouli dongoeho gaa gahu i hongo tenua go Egypt.”
\v 22 Moses ga daahi dono lima gi di langi, gei di bouli dongoeho guu gahu Egypt i lodo nia laangi e dolu.\x * \xo 10.22 \xt Pisalem 105.28; Revelation 16.10\x*
\v 23 Digau Egypt gu de gidee ginaadou gi daha, ge gu deemee di ulu gi daha mo nadau hale i lodo nia laangi e dolu aalaa. Gei di gowaa dela e noho ai digau Israel le e maalama hua.
\v 24 Di king ga gahi mai a Moses ga helekai gi mee, “Goodou guu mee hua di hula e daumaha gi Dimaadua, nia ahina mo godou dama guu mee di hula goodou, aalaa hua go godou siibi mono kuudi mono kau le e dugu hua.”
\p 
\v 25 Moses ga helekai, “Goe hai beenaa laa, heia gimaadou gii kae madau manu hai tigidaumaha, e hai madau tigidaumaha dudu go gimaadou gi Dimaadua go di madau God.
\v 26 Deeai, madau manu huogodoo le e kae labelaa go gimaadou, deai di manu e dahi e dugu ai. Madau manu ala e tigidaumaha ei gimaadou gi Dimaadua go di madau God le e hilihili go gimaadou ma gaa dau i di gowaa dela e hai ai tigidaumaha, gei gimaadou e de iloo be aahee nia mee ala ga hai hegau ai.”
\p 
\v 27 Dimaadua ga haga hamaaloo lodo di king o Egypt. Deelaa ai ga hagalee hai digaula gii hula.
\v 28 Di king ga helekai gi Moses, “Hana gi daha mo au, goe hudee hanimoi labelaa. Maa au ga mmada adu labelaa gi di goe, gei goe ga daaligi gii made i di laangi hua deelaa.”
\p 
\v 29 Gei Moses ga helekai, “E hai gadoo be dau kai dela bolo goe ga hagalee mmada mai labelaa gi di au.”
\c 11
\s1 Moses e haga iloo di mmade o nia ulu mmaadua
\p 
\v 1 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Di hagaduadua hua e dahi i golo dela gaa hai ko Au gi di king mo digau Egypt. Nomuli gei mee ga hagau goodou gii hula. Gei muli dana hagau goodou gii hula, mee ga hagabagi goodou huogodoo gi daha mo Egypt.
\v 2 Goe helekai gi nia daane mono ahina o Israel bolo ginaadou huogodoo la gi madau ina nadau mee ne hai gi nia silber mo goolo, gi nadau ihoo hagaaloho o Egypt.”
\v 3 Dimaadua guu hai digau Egypt gi dumaalia gi digau Israel, gei digau aamua o di king mo digau Egypt hagatau la guu hai bolo Moses tangada hagalabagau.
\p 
\v 4 Moses ga helekai gi di king, “Deenei telekai a Dimaadua boloo, ‘I di madahidi waelua di boo, gei Au gaa hana laa lodo Egypt.
\v 5 Nia ulu mmaadua daane o Egypt huogodoo la gaa mmade, e daamada i tama daane madua di king o Egypt dela belee pono di lohongo king, gaa dae loo gi di ulu madua daane di hege ahina dela e olo ana ‘wheat’ gi di mee olo mee. Gei nia ulu mmaadua o nia kau huogodoo la gaa mmade labelaa.
\v 6 Nnangihangi manawa gee ga longoaa i nia madagoaa huogodoo i hongo Egypt. Deai di lee manawa gee ne hai beenei i mua ai, ge hagalee gila beenei maalia labelaa.
\v 7 Gei digau Israel digi hagalongo gi di paana e wwouwwou gi tangada Israel be e wwouwwou ang gi nia manu. Gei goodou ga iloo laa bolo ma ko Au go Dimaadua dela e dugu gee digau Egypt mo digau Israel.’”
\v 8 Moses ga haga lawa ana helekai, “Au gau aamua huogodoo ga lloomoi ga dogoduli i ogu mua, ga tangi mai gi di au bolo au gi lahia agu daangada gii hula. Nomuli gei au gaa hana.” Moses ga hagatanga i baahi di king mo dono hagawelewele.
\p 
\v 9 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Di king la hagalee loo e hagalongo adu gi di goe, bolo gii mee Au di hai agu mogobuna la gii logo i hongo Egypt.”
\v 10 Moses mo Aaron la ne hai nia mogobuna aalaa i mua o di king o Egypt, gei Dimaadua la gu haga hamaaloo di manawa di king, deelaa e hidi ai iei mee hagalee hagau digau Israel gii hula gi daha mo dono henua.
\c 12
\s1 Di Pasoobaa
\r (Leviticus 23.5; Numbers 9.1-5; 28.16; Deuteronomy 16.1-2)
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses mo Aaron i lodo o Egypt,
\v 2 “Di malama deenei la go taamada o di godou ngadau.
\v 3 Deenei di gulu mee belee hagi anga go goolua gi digau Israel, bolo di madangaholu laangi o di malama deenei, gei nia daane dagidahi i goodou gi hilihilia dana dama siibi be tamaa kuudi ang gi digau dono hale, di manu e dahi ang gi digau o di hale e dahi.
\v 4 Maa di hale e hogoohi ang gi tama siibi dogomaalia, digaula la gii buni anga hua gi digau o di hale dela e hoohoo mai. Digaula di nadau dama siibi hua e dahi, e hagabau be dogohia e mee di gai di manu dulii deelaa.
\v 5 Goodou hilihilia di kuudi daane be di siibi daane, dono ngadau e dahi, dela e humalia ge madammaa.
\v 6 Hiahi di madangaholu maa haa o di malama deelaa, gei digau Israel huogodoo e hai gi daaligi nia manu aalaa.
\v 7 Digaula gii kae nia dodo o nia manu aalaa gi hunu ina nia waduu o nadau bontai mo nia laagau di ulu gi nua o nia bontai o nia hale ala e miami ai ginaadou, e gai nia manu aalaa.
\v 8 Di boo hua deelaa, digaula gi geina nia goneiga o nia manu ala ne dunu i hongo di ahi, gidagia gi nia lau laagau mmala mo nia palaawaa digi wanga ginai nia ‘yeast’.
\v 9 Hudee geina mada be dunu nia goneiga gi nia wai i lodo di baalanga, gei gi geina di mee dela guu dunu haga dogomaalia, mo dono libogo, mono wae, mono mee ala i lodo huogodoo.
\v 10 Goodou hudee dugu mee gi di luada. Nia mee ala ma gaa dubu, la gi duungia.
\v 11 Deenei di godou hai e gai nia manu aalaa: goodou ulu godou gahu mo godou suudi e hagatogomaalia e hula, kumi godou dogodogo i godou lima, ga miami laa haga lellele. Idimaa deelaa di godou Hagamiami o di Pasoobaa, e hagalaamua Au, go Dimaadua.
\p 
\v 12 “Di boo hua deelaa gei Au ga daaligi nia ulu mmaadua daane mono ulu mmaadua manu huogodoo i hongo Egypt, ga hagahuaidu nia balu god o Egypt huogodoo. Ko Au go Dimaadua.
\v 13 Nia dodo ala gaa hunu gi nia waduu nia bontai le e haga modongoohia nia hale ala e noho ai goodou. Au ma ga gidee nia dodo, gei Au ga haga hili goodou i golo. Deai di hagaduadua e tale adu gi goodou ai i dagu hagaduadua digau Egypt.
\v 14 Goodou la gi budubudu ina di laangi tagamiami dabu deenei, e haga langahia go goodou mo godou hagadili gi muli, bolo ma ko Au, go Dimaadua, ne hai di mee deenei.”\x * \xo 12.14 \xt Exodus 23.15; 34.18; Leviticus 23.6-8; Numbers 28.17-25; Deuteronomy 16.3-8\x*
\s1 Tagamiami o di Palaawaa Digi Hagatanga
\r (Exodus 34.18; Leviticus 23.6-8)
\p 
\v 15 Dimaadua ga helekai, “I lodo nia laangi e hidu, goodou la gi geina go nia palaawaa digi hagatanga gi nia ‘yeast’. Di laangi matagidagi di tabu deelaa, goodou la gi haga mmaa ina gi daha nia ‘yeast’ ala i lodo godou hale, idimaa, tangada ma gaa gai dana palaawaa gu hagatanga gi nia ‘yeast’ mai tahi laangi gaa hana gi di hidu laangi, geia hagalee dau ang gi digau Israel.
\v 16 Goodou gi dagadagabuli daumaha i di laangi matagidagi mo di hidu laangi di tabu deelaa. Nia laangi aalaa di moomee e hai ai. Di moomee e mee di hai la go di hai nia meegai e gai.
\v 17 Goodou la gi heheia tagamiami dabu deenei, idimaa dela dagu laangi ne dagi mai godou madawaawa gi daha mo Egypt. Goodou la gi heheia tagamiami dabu deenei gi digau huogodoo ala e hagadili mai gaa hana hua beelaa.
\v 18 Goodou e gai nia palaawaa digi hagatanga gi nia ‘yeast’, daamada i di hiahi o di madangaholu maa haa laangi o di malama matagidagi, gaa huli gi di hiahi o di madalua maa dahi laangi.
\v 19 I lodo nia laangi e hidu la deai di ‘yeast’ i lodo godou hale ai. Di ingoo hua tangada dela ma gaa gai dana palaawaa tanga, go tangada hua deelaa le e hagamodu gi daha mo digau Israel, ma e aha maa mee tangada mai i daha be tangada donu o tenua.
\v 20 Goodou hudee geina nia palaawaa tanga, aalaa hua e gai go nia palaawaa digi hagatanga ina i di ingoo hua di gowaa dela ma gaa noho ai goodou.”
\s1 Di Pasoobaa matagidagi
\p 
\v 21 Gei Moses ga haga dagabuli nia dagi o digau Israel ga helekai gi digaula, “Tangada nei mo tangada nei i goodou tei gi hilihilia dana dama siibi be tamaa kuudi ang gi digau dono hale, daaligidia, gii mee di hai di godou hagamiami haga madagu o di Pasoobaa.
\v 22 Goodou ga haga tiu di lau o di laagau hisop gi lodo nia dodo i lodo di baisin, ga haga tiutiu nia duludulu o nia bontai mo hongo nia bontai gi nia maa. Deai tangada i goodou e ulu gi daha mo dono hale ai, gaa dae loo gi di luada.
\v 23 Dimaadua ma gaa hana i hongo Egypt e daaligi digau Egypt, ga gidee ia nia dodo i di gili nia duludulu o nia bontai mo hongo nia bontai, ge Ia hagalee hai tangada di langi haga made dangada gi ulu gi lodo godou hale e daaligi goodou.\x * \xo 12.23 \xt Hebrews 11.28\x*
\v 24 Goodou la gi haga gila ina aga nia haganoho aanei gii hai di mee e hana hua beelaa, gi daahi go godou dama laalaa gi muli loo.
\v 25 Di godou madagoaa ma ga ulu i tenua a Dimaadua dela gu hagababa adu gi goodou, gei goodou la gi heheia taumaha deenei.
\v 26 Di madagoaa godou dama ma ga heheeu adu boloo, ‘Di mee deenei le e haihai eimaha?’
\v 27 Gei goodou ga hagi anga boloo, ‘Deenei la di tigidaumaha Pasoobaa ang gi Dimaadua dela nogo daaligi digau Egypt, ge Ia gu hagahili digau Israel digi daaligidia.’”
\p Digau Israel ne hagalongo gi nia mee aanei, gaa pala gi lala ga daumaha gi God.
\v 28 Gei digaula gaa hula gaa hai gii hai be nia helekai a Dimaadua ala ne hai gi Moses mo Aaron bolo gi heia.
\s1 Di mmade o nia ulu mmaadua
\p 
\v 29 I di madahidi waelua di boo, gei Dimaadua ga daaligi nia ulu mmaadua huogodoo digau Egypt, daamada mai tama daane madua a di king dela belee kae dono lohongo king, gaa tugi loo i di ulu madua o tangada dela i lodo di hale galabudi, mo nia ulu mmaadua o nia manu huogodoo.\x * \xo 12.29 \xt Exodus 4.22-23\x*
\v 30 Di king mo ono gau aamua mono gau o Egypt ala i golo gu aala huogodoo i di boo deelaa. Nia hangihangi guu logo i hongo Egypt, idimaa, deai di hale bolo dono dama daane ne made ai ai.
\v 31 Di boo hua deelaa, gei di king o Egypt ga gahi mai a Moses mo Aaron, ga helekai ginai, “Goolua hula hagalimalima gi daha, goodou mo digau Israel huogodoo! Hula gi daha mo dogu henua gi daumaha goodou gi Dimaadua be godou kai ala ne hai.
\v 32 Kae ina godou siibi mo godou kuudi mo godou kau. Goodou hula, gei goodou dalodalo ina labelaa gi hagahumalia au go Dimaadua.”
\p 
\v 33 Digau Egypt e uhuuhuli digau Israel bolo gi hagalimalima gi daha mo di nadau henua, mo di helekai, “Maa goodou ga duai, gei gimaadou gaa mmade huogodoo!”
\v 34 Malaa, digau Israel gaa kae nadau palaawaa digi unugi gi nia ‘yeast’, gaa hii gi nia hii goloo, ga dahi aga ga aamo, ga hagatanga gaa hula.
\v 35 Gei digaula ga hai hegau gi nia helekai a Moses ala ne helekai ang gi ginaadou, bolo ginaadou gi madau ina nadau goloo ne hai gi nia silber mono goolo mono goloo gahu mai digau Egypt.\x * \xo 12.35 \xt Exodus 3.21-22\x*
\v 36 Dimaadua guu hai digau Israel gi hagalabagau go digau Egypt, malaa, digau Egypt gu dumaalia gi digau Israel, guu wanga nia mee huogodoo ala ne madau go digaula. Deenei di hai ne daa ai nia goloo digau Egypt go digaula.
\s1 Digau Israel guu hula gi daha mo Egypt
\p 
\v 37 Digau Israel la ga hagatanga i Rameses gaa hula gi Sukkoth. Nia daane le e ono lau mana (600,000), nia ahina mono damagiigi digi daulia.
\v 38 Nia daangada dogologowaahee mai i daha mo nadau hagabae siibi, kuudi mono kau guu hula i nadau muli labelaa.
\v 39 Digaula gaa daa nadau palaawaa i nadau mee ne gaamai i Egypt digi wanga ginai nia ‘yeast’, idimaa, digaula ne hagabagi gi daha mo Egypt hagalimalima, digi hagatogomaalia hagahumalia nadau meegai, ge digi hagatogomaalia nia palaawaa unugi gi nia ‘yeast’.
\v 40 Digau Israel ne noho i Egypt nia ngadau e 430.\x * \xo 12.40 \xt Genesis 15.13; Galatians 3.17\x*
\v 41 Di laangi hagamuliagina di ngadau e 430, deelaa di laangi o nia madawaawa o nia dama o Dimaadua huogodoo ne hagatanga ai gi daha mo Egypt.
\v 42 Deenei di boo a Dimaadua nogo dagi mai digau Israel gi daha mo Egypt mo di madamada humalia ai digaula huoloo. Deelaa di mee digau Israel e haga dabu ai di boo deelaa, e hagalaamua Dimaadua mai i nadau haga aala i di boo deelaa, gaa hana hua beelaa gi daahi go nadau dama laalaa gi muli.
\s1 Nnaganoho di Pasoobaa
\p 
\v 43 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses mo Aaron, “Aanei nnaganoho di Pasoobaa: Tangada henua gee e miami i tagamiami di Pasoobaa ai,
\v 44 gei di ingoo hua di hege ne hui kooe e mee di miami maa goe gu sirkumsais a mee i mua.
\v 45 Tangada e noho i Israel i di madagoaa bodobodo be tangada ne hagangalua e miami di maa ai.
\v 46 Tagamiami hagatau e hai gi miami i lodo di hale ne hagatogomaalia gi di maa; hagalee kae gi malaelae. Hudee ohaa gi mooho nia iwi o di manu.
\v 47 Nia daangada huogodoo o Israel e hai gii hai tagamiami deenei.
\v 48 Tangada digi sirkumsais e hagalee miami. Maa tangada henua gee guu noho i godou baahi, gei mee e hiihai e budu di Pasoobaa e hagalaamua Dimaadua, goodou e hai gi sirkumsais nia daane huogodoo o di hale o maa. Nomuli, gei mee le e dugu be tangada Israel donu, e dau gi di budu deenei.
\v 49 Nnaganoho hua aanei e hai hegau gi digau Israel mo digau henua gee ma gaa noho i godou baahi.”
\p 
\v 50 Digau Israel huogodoo gu hagalongo mo di hagagila aga nia helekai Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses mo Aaron.
\v 51 Di laangi deelaa, gei Dimaadua gu laha mai nia madawaawa Israel gi daha mo Egypt.
\c 13
\s1 Di hagadabu o nia dama mmaadua
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses,
\v 2 “Hagadabu ina nia dama daane mmaadua mai gi di Au, idimaa digaula mo nia manu daane mmaadua huogodoo la nia mee ni aagu.”\x * \xo 13.2 \xt Numbers 3.13; Luke 2.23\x*
\s1 Tagamiami o di Palaawaa Digi Hagatanga
\p 
\v 3 Moses ga helekai gi nia daangada, “Hagamaanadu ina di laangi deenei, di laangi dela ne hagatanga ai goodou gi daha mo Egypt, di gowaa nogo noho ai goodou. Deenei di laangi Dimaadua ne laha mai goodou gi ono mahi maaloo dangihi. Nia palaawaa gu hagatanga le hagalee gai.
\v 4 Goodou e hagatanga i Egypt i di laangi deenei i lodo di malama go Abib.
\v 5 Dimaadua gu hagababa maaloo gi godou maadua mmaadua bolo Ia ga gowadu gi goodou tenua digau Canaan, Hittite, Amorite, Hivite mo digau Jebus. Mee ga laha mai goodou gi lodo tenua maluagina ge tomo huoloo. Di madagoaa deelaa, gei goodou heia gii budu di laangi deenei i lodo di malama matagidagi o nia ngadau huogodoo.
\v 6 I lodo nia laangi e hidu goodou e hai gii gai nia palaawaa digi hagatanga, di hidu laangi e hai taumaha e hagalaamua Dimaadua.
\v 7 I lodo nia laangi e hidu goodou hagalee gai nia palaawaa gu hagatanga. Nia palaawaa gu hagatanga e hagalee hai gi i golo i di ingoo hua di gowaa i lodo godou henua.
\v 8 I di laangi deelaa, gei goe hagi anga ina gi godou dama daane bolo goodou e hai nia mee aanei, idimaa aanei nia mee Dimaadua ne hai adu gi goodou i di godou hagatanga i Egypt.
\v 9 Nia mee aanei e hai di hagalangahia be di mee dela e nnoo doo lima be i hongo doo lae, e hagalangahia ge hagamaumau nnaganoho Dimaadua, idimaa ma go Dimaadua ne laha mai goodou gi daha mo Egypt gi ono mahi maaloo dangihi.
\v 10 Budu ina di laangi i nia madagoaa ala gu haganoho i lodo di ngadau e dahi.
\s1 Nia ulu mmaadua
\p 
\v 11 “Dimaadua gaa lahi goodou gi tenua o digau Canaan dela ne hagababa hagamodu go Mee adu gi goodou mo godou maadua mmaadua. Mee ga gowadu di maa gi goodou,
\v 12 gei goodou e hai gi wanga nia ulu mmaadua huogodoo gi Dimaadua. Nia ulu mmaadua daane o godou manu la nia mee ni Dimaadua.\x * \xo 13.12 \xt Exodus 34.19-20; Luke 2.23\x*
\v 13 Goodou e hai loo gii hui gi muli mai nia ‘donkey’ daane ulu mmaadua huogodoo i di godou tigidaumaha tama siibi i dono lohongo. Maa goodou e hagalee hiihai e hui gi muli nia manu ‘donkey’, hagadagamila ina nia uwa digaula. Goodou e hai gii hui gi muli nia ulu mmaadua daane o godou dama huogodoo.
\v 14 Dagidilaangi dau dama daane ma gaa heeu tadinga di hagalangahia di laangi deenei, gei goe ga helekai gi mee boloo, ‘Ma go di maaloo dangihi Dimaadua dela ne laha mai gidaadou gi daha mo Egypt, di gowaa nogo hege ai gidaadou.
\v 15 Di madagoaa di king Egypt nogo hamaaloo ono lodo e de hiihai di hagau gidaadou gii hula, Dimaadua gu daaligi nia ulu mmaadua daane huogodoo o Egypt, nia daangada mo nia manu. Gaa hidi ai gidaadou e tigidaumaha nia ulu mmaadua o nia manu huogodoo ang gi Dimaadua, e hui gi muli tadau ulu mmaadua daane.
\v 16 Di laangi deenei e hai di hagalangahia, e hai be di mee dela e nnoo gi hongo tadau lima be i hongo tadau lae, e hagalangahia bolo Dimaadua ne laha mai gidaadou gi daha mo Egypt gi ono mahi maaloo dangihi.’”
\s1 Di waduu gololangi mo di waduu ahi
\p 
\v 17 Di madagoaa di king o Egypt ne hai digau Israel gii hula gi daha mo Egypt, gei God digi dagia digaula i di ala dela e hana laa daha tenua e hana e moe adu gi Philistia, ma e aha maa di ala deelaa le e bodobodo, i Mee e hagabaubau boloo, “Digaula gi dee huli hua nadau lodo, gaa hai bolo ginaadou gaa hula gi muli gi Egypt i di nadau mmada gi nia dauwa ala e hai go ginaadou.”
\v 18 Gei Mee gaa dagi digaula laa lodo di anggowaa adu gi Tai Mmee.\f + \fr 13.18 \fk Tai Mmee \ft Di ingoo Hebrew di tai deenei go Yam Suph, dono hadinga bolo di Tai o nia Aalek\f* Digau Israel ne hula mo nadau goloo dauwa.
\p 
\v 19 Moses gaa kae nia iwi o Joseph dalia ia, idimaa Joseph guu hai dana hagababa hagamodu gi digau Israel boloo, “Di madagoaa a God ma ga haga dagaloaha goodou, gei goodou kae ina dogu huaidina dalia goodou gi daha mo kinei.”\x * \xo 13.19 \xt Genesis 50.25; Joshua 24.32\x*
\p 
\v 20 Gei digau Israel ga hagatanga i Sukkoth adu gi Etham, ga haga duu nadau hale laa i taalinga di anggowaa.
\v 21 Ma gaa aa, gei Dimaadua le e hana i mua digaula e dina gi di waduu gololangi e daudali go digaula, ge ma gaa boo, di waduu ahi e duu gi nua, e hana i nadau mua, e inaina digaula, gii mee di hula digaula boo mo aa.
\v 22 Nia aa huogodoo gei di waduu gololangi le e hana i nadau mua, gei nia boo huogodoo gei di waduu ahi le e hana i nadau mua, e inaina di nadau ala.
\c 14
\s1 Digau Israel e hula laa lodo Tai Mmee
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses,
\v 2 “Hai gi digau Israel gi maalui mai, hauhia nadau hale laa i mua o Pi-Hahiroth i mehanga o Migdol mo Tai Mmee, hoohoo gi Baal-Zephon.
\v 3 Di king o Egypt ga hagabaubau bolo digau Israel la gu ihala hua e heehee hua i lodo di anggowaa i lodo henua.
\v 4 Gei Au ga haga hamaaloo di manawa o di king, gei mee ga waluwalu goodou. Gei Au ga haga magedaa a mee mo ana gau dauwa, gei digaula ga hagalaamua Au. Gei digau Egypt ga iloo ginaadou bolo ma ko Au go Dimaadua.” Gei digau Israel gu daudali nnelekai a Maa.
\p 
\v 5 Di haga iloo gaa dau i di king o Egypt bolo digau Israel la guu llele, geia mo ana gau aamua gaa huli labelaa nadau lodo, ga helekai, “Gidaadou la ne hai tadau aha dela ne hagau digau Israel ala nogo hai tadau hege la gii hula gi daha mo gidaadou?”
\v 6 Gei di king ga hagatogomaalia dana waga hongo henua ga haga dagabuli mai ana gau dauwa.
\v 7 Mee gaa hana mo ana waga hongo henua e ono lau ala koia e humalia, mono waga hongo henua ala i golo, huogodoo e dagi go ana dagi dauwa.
\v 8 Dimaadua ga haga hamaaloo lodo o di king gaa hidi ai ei mee ga waluwalu digau Israel ala e hula i lala di hagaloohi o Dimaadua.
\v 9 Digau dauwa Egypt mo nadau hoodo, waga hongo henua mo digau e dele nia maa huogodoo ga waluwalu digau Israel ga hoohoo adu i di gowaa digaula dela ne haga duu aga ai nadau hale laa i taalinga Tai Mmee, hoohoo adu gi Pi-Hahiroth mo Baal-Zephon.
\p 
\v 10 Di madagoaa digau Israel ne mmada gi di king o Egypt mo ana gau dauwa ala e lloomoi, digaula gu mmaadagu huoloo, ga gahigahi Dimaadua bolo gi hagamaamaa ina ginaadou.
\v 11 Gei digaula ga helekai gi Moses, “Ma deai di gowaa danu dangada i Egypt ai, dela goe ne laha mai gimaadou belee mmade i lodo di anggowaa deenei? Mmada malaa gi dau hai dela ne hai mai gi gimaadou dela ne laha mai gimaadou gi daha mo Egypt!
\v 12 E hai behee? Gimaadou digi helekai adu gi di goe i mua tadau hagatanga bolo nia mee aanei le e kila aga? Gimaadou gu helekai adu boloo: Dugua hua gimaadou gii hege gi digau Egypt. Ma koia e humalia e hege i lala digaula i di madau mmade i lodo di anggowaa deenei!”
\p 
\v 13 Gei Moses ga helekai, “Goodou hudee mmaadagu! Goodou hagamahi, goodou gaa mmada gi di mee a Dimaadua dela gaa hai, ga haga dagaloaha goodou dangi nei. Digau Egypt aanei ga hagalee mmada ginai goodou labelaa.
\v 14 Dimaadua ga heebagi e pono goodou, goodou deai di godou mee e hai ai.”
\p 
\v 15 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Goe e gahigahi Au eiaha? Hai gi digau Israel bolo gi hagatanga, lloo adu.
\v 16 Gei goe daahia dau dogodogo gi hongo tai deenaa gi wwae lua, gii bagu di gowaa e hula ai digau Israel.
\v 17 Au gaa hai digau Egypt gi lodo hamaaloo gi waluwalu goodou go digaula. Gei dogu aamua la ga modongoohia i di Au ma ga haga magedaa di king o Egypt mo ana gau dauwa, mo ana waga hongo henua, mo digau ala e dele nia maa.
\v 18 Au ma ga haga magedaa digaula, gei digau Egypt ga iloo ginaadou bolo ma ko Au go Dimaadua.”
\p 
\v 19 Tangada di langi o God dela nogo hana i mua di llongo gau dauwa o Israel ga hagadiga mai la muli digaula, gei di waduu gololangi dela nogo i mua digaula, gaa hana labelaa la muli digaula,
\v 20 gaa hana gaa duu i mehanga digau Egypt mo digau Israel. Di boo deelaa gei di waduu gololangi deelaa gaa hai digau Egypt gii noho i lodo di bouli, gei digau Israel e noho i lodo di maalama, gei nia baahi e lua gau dauwa aalaa digi hoohoo nau mehanga i di boo deelaa.
\p 
\v 21 Gei Moses ga daahi dono lima laa hongo tai deelaa, gei Dimaadua gaa hai dana madangi gi gono ia i dua ga hagabagibagia tai deelaa i di boo deelaa hagatau, gaa hai di tai la gii bagu gi maangoo. Nia wai la gu wwae lua,
\v 22 gei digau Israel gaa hula i tungaalodo o di tai i di gowaa dela ne maangoo, gei nia wai la guu hai nia abaaba ni digaula i di baahi gau donu mo di baahi gau ihala.\x * \xo 14.22 \xt 1-Corinthians 10.1-2; Hebrews 11.29\x*
\v 23 Digau Egypt ga waluwalu mai muli digau Israel gi tungaalodo di tai mo nadau hoodo mo nadau waga hongo henua mono gau ala e dele nia maa.
\v 24 Hagaluada loo, Dimaadua ga mmada iha mai i lodo di waduu ahi mo di waduu gololangi, gi digau dauwa o Egypt, ga hagahinihini digaula.
\v 25 Mee ga haga de ngalungalua nia duaadiga o nadau waga hongo henua, gei nia maa gu deemee di llele. Gei digau Egypt ga helekai boloo, “Gidaadou gaa hula gaa llele gi daha mo digau Israel, idimaa Dimaadua le e huli mai e heebagi mai i di baahi o Israel!”
\p 
\v 26 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Daahia doo lima gi hongo di tai deenaa, gi honu mai di tai laa hongo digau Egypt mo nadau waga hongo henua mono gau ala e dele nia maa.”
\v 27 Gei Moses ga daahi dono lima laa hongo di tai deelaa, malaa, hooaga hagaluada gei nia wai o di tai deelaa gu buni mai gi ono lohongo, gei digau Egypt gu hagamahi bolo ginaadou belee llele gi daha mo tai deelaa, ge gu deemee, gu hai hua go Dimaadua gi aabulu gi lodo di tai deelaa.
\v 28 Tai deelaa la gu buni mai guu gahu nia waga hongo henua mo digau ala e dele nia maa mo digau dauwa Egypt huogodoo ala nogo waluwalu digau Israel laa lodo di tai deelaa. Deai tangada e dahi ne mouli ai, huogodoo guu mmade.
\v 29 Gei digau Israel guu hula i hongo di gowaa bagu i tungaalodo di tai, gei nia wai la guu hai nia abaaba e lua ni digaula, e dahi i di baahi gau ihala ge dahi i di baahi gau donu.
\p 
\v 30 Deelaa di hai a Dimaadua ne haga dagaloaha digau Israel gi daha mo digau Egypt. Digau Israel guu mmada gi digau Egypt ala e dadaahee guu mmade i tongotai.
\v 31 Digaula gu mmada hua haga mmaa gi di mogobuna damanaiee a Dimaadua dela ne hai gi digau Egypt, gei digaula gu hagamadagudia a Dimaadua gu hagadonu a Mee mo tangada hai hegau a Maa go Moses.
\c 15
\s1 Taahili a Moses
\p 
\v 1 Malaa digau Israel mo Moses ga daahili gi Dimaadua i taahili deenei:\x * \xo 15.1 \xt Revelation 15.3\x*
\q1 Au e daahili hagaamu a Dimaadua
\q1 i ono mahi aamua i dono aali.
\q1 Mee ne haga abulu nia hoodo
\q1 mo digau ala e deledele nia maa
\q1 la gi lodo di tai.
\q1 
\v 2 Dimaadua la go dogu abaaba maaloo,\x * \xo 15.2 \xt Pisalem 118.14; Isaiah 12.2\x*
\q1 go Mee dela ne haga mouli au.
\q1 Go Mee dela go dogu God,
\q1 gei au e haga hagaamu a Mee,
\q1 go Mee dela go di God o dogu damana,
\q1 gei au e daahili i ono mahi.
\q1 
\v 3 Dimaadua la tangada dauwa de madagu,
\q1 di ingoo o Maa go Yihowah.
\b
\q1 
\v 4 Mee ne kili di llongo gau dauwa o
\q1 Egypt mo nadau waga gi lodo di tai.
\q1 Digau dauwa ala e maaloo dangihi
\q1 la gu maalemu i lodo Tai Mmee.
\q1 
\v 5 Di tai guu gahu digaula
\q1 gu aabulu gadoo be di hadu
\q1 gi tua di moana.
\q1 
\v 6 Meenei Dimaadua, doo lima
\q1 gau donu le e mahi huoloo,
\q1 gu hunahuna hagauwwou
\q1 madau hagadaumee.
\q1 
\v 7 Goe gu hunahuna o hagadaumee
\q1 gi oo mahi.
\q1 Do hagawelewele la gu ulaula
\q1 guu dudu digaula gii wwele
\q1 gadoo be nia geinga maangoo.
\q1 
\v 8 Goe ne ili di tai,
\q1 gei nia wai gu tuu gi nua,
\q1 gu wwae lua guu hai nia abaaba,
\q1 gei gu bagu ia gi tua loo i lala.
\q1 
\v 9 Di madau hagadaumee ne helekai boloo,
\q1 ‘Au ga waluwalu digaula gaa kumi
\q1 ko au, gaa duwwe nia goloo digaula,
\q1 gei au gaa daa agu mee
\q1 ala e hiihai ginai au.
\q1 Au ga haga mmuu dagu
\q1 hulumanu dauwa
\q1 gaa dada nia mee huogodoo digaula.’
\q1 
\v 10 Gei deeai! Meenei Dimaadua,
\q1 Goe gu ili hua dau madangi gei di tai
\q1 gu lamuhi digaula gi aabulu gadoo be
\q1 nia baalanga daamaha gi lodo di moana.
\b
\q1 
\v 11 Meenei Dimaadua, ma di god
\q1 koai e hai be Goe?
\q1 Ge koai e hai be Goe
\q1 dela e mogobuna huoloo ge dabuaahia?
\q1 Ge koai e hai be Goe
\q1 dela e hagamadagudia huoloo?
\q1 
\v 12 Goe ne dahi aga hua doo lima
\q1 gau donu gei henuailala
\q1 guu holo madau hagadaumee.
\q1 
\v 13 Goe gu haga huudonu au hagababa
\q1 i dau dagi au daangada
\q1 ala ne haga mouli Kooe.
\q1 Goe gu laha mai digaula gi do henua
\q1 dabu i nia mahi o mogobuna.
\q1 
\v 14 Digau o nnenua llauehe gu longono
\q1 gei gu mmaadagu.
\q1 Di manawa gee huoloo
\q1 gu i lodo digau Philistia.
\q1 
\v 15 Nia dagi o Edom
\q1 gu mmaadagu huoloo.
\q1 Digau maaloo o Moab
\q1 gu daamada gu polepole.
\q1 Gei digau Canaan
\q1 gu paagege nadau lodo.
\q1 
\v 16 Digaula gu mmaadagu,
\q1 gei gu uli nadau gai huoloo.
\q1 Meenei Dimaadua, digaula guu mmada
\q1 gi o maaloo, gei gu noho deemuu
\q1 i di nadau mmaadagu,
\q1 gaa dae loo gi di tanga adu gi daha
\q1 o au daangada, go au daangada
\q1 ala ne haga dagaloaha mai gi daha
\q1 mo nadau noho hege.
\q1 
\v 17 Meenei Dimaadua, Goe ne dagi mai
\q1 digaula gaa dugu i hongo dau gonduu,
\q1 go di gowaa dela ne dongo Kooe
\q1 belee hai do lohongo, go di Hale
\q1 Daumaha dela ne bida hau Kooe.
\q1 
\v 18 Meenei Dimaadua, go Kooe hua di
\q1 king ga hana hua dee odi.
\s1 Taahili a Miriam
\p 
\v 19 Nia hoodo a di king o Egypt mono waga hongo henua mo digau ala e dele nia maa guu hula gi lodo di tai, gei Dimaadua gu haga mmidi mai nia wai gi hongo digaula, gei digau Israel gu hula hua gi di baahi dela i golo i di gowaa hua bagu ia.
\p 
\v 20 Soukohp ahina go Miriam, tuaahina o Aaron ne gaamai dana mee hagatangitangi ‘tambourine’, gei nia ahina huogodoo ga daudali a mee mo di haga tangitangi nadau ‘tambourine’ mo di gagaalege.
\v 21 Miriam gaa huwa taahili deenei gi digaula:
\q1 “Goodou daahili hagaamuina Dimaadua,
\q1 i Mee dela ne aali i dono mahi aamua.
\q1 Mee ne haga abulu nia hoodo
\q1 mo digau dele nia maa gi lodo di tai.”
\s1 Nia wai mmala
\p 
\v 22 Moses ga dagi mai digau Israel mai Tai Mmee gi lodo di Anggowaa o Shur. Digaula nogo taele i nia laangi e dolu i lodo di anggowaa, digi gidee nia wai.
\v 23 Digaula gaa dau i di gowaa dono ingoo go Marah, gei nia wai i golo le e mmala, e deemee di inu, deelaa di mee digaula ne haga ingoo di gowaa deelaa bolo ‘Marah’.\f + \fr 15.23 \fk Marah: \ft i nnelekai Hebrew le e hai dono hadinga bolo e mmala\f*
\v 24 Nia daangada guu hai nadau donu gi Moses boloo, “Gidaadou ga inu tadau aha?”
\v 25 Gei mee gaa dangi gi Dimaadua, gei Dimaadua ga hagi anga dana bida laagau, gei Moses gaa hudu di maa gi lodo di monowai, gei nia wai gu humalia dono inu.
\p Di madagoaa deelaa, gei Dimaadua guu wanga ana haganoho gi digaula, gu hagamada digaula.
\v 26 Mee ga helekai, “Maa goodou ga hagalongo mai gi di Au huoloo, gaa hai go nia mee ala e humalia, ga hagagila aga agu haganoho, gei Au hagalee hagaduadua goodou gi nia magi huaidu ala ne hai ko Au gi digau Egypt. Idimaa deenei Au go Yihowah di godou God dela e hagahili goodou.”
\p 
\v 27 Nomuli, gei digaula gaa dau adu gi Elim, go di gowaa dela iai nia monowai uwa aga e madangaholu maa lua, ge mada hidu laagau niu, gei digaula ga haga duu aga nadau hale laa i baahi o nia monowai aalaa.
\c 16
\s1 Nia palaawaa ‘manna’ mo nia manu ‘quail’
\p 
\v 1 Digau Israel huogodoo ga hagatanga i Elim i di madangaholu maa lima laangi o di lua malama i muli di nadau tanga mai gi daha mo Egypt, gei digaula gaa dau i lodo di Anggowaa o Sin, dela i mehanga o Elim mo Sinai.
\v 2 Digaula huogodoo guu hai nadau donu gi Moses mo Aaron i lodo di anggowaa deelaa,
\v 3 ga helekai gi meemaa, “Maa nei bolo Dimaadua ne daaligi gimaadou i lodo Egypt la koia e humalia. Gimaadou nogo noho i golo i baahi nia baalanga goneiga, giidagi madau meegai gii tau gi di madau hiihai, gei goe ne laha mai gimaadou huogodoo gii mmade i di hiigai i kinei.”
\p 
\v 4 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Au ga llingi iha gi goodou agu palaawaa mai i di langi. Nia laangi huogodoo, nia daangada gii hula gi ogohia nadau meegai ala e dohu ang gi ginaadou i lodo di laangi e dahi, idimaa Au e hagamada digaula be digaula e hagalongo gi agu haganoho be deeai.\x * \xo 16.4 \xt John 6.31\x*
\v 5 Di ono laangi, gei digaula gi hagabudu ina nadau mee gii logo nia holongo lua i nia mee ala nogo ogo i nia laangi huogodoo ala ne hula, gaa lawa ga hagatogomaalia.”
\p 
\v 6 Moses mo Aaron ga helekai gi digau Israel, “Hiahi nei gei goodou ga iloo bolo ma go Dimaadua dela ne dagi mai goodou gi daha mo Egypt.
\v 7 Hagaluada goodou gaa mmada gi di mogobuna madamada o Dimaadua, i Mee dela gu longono godou tamu e hai baahi ang gi de Ia. Goodou hagalee ne tamu gimaua, idimaa gimaua e hai hua nia moomee a Maa!”
\v 8 Gei Moses ga duudagi adu ana helekai boloo, “Ma go Dimaadua dela ga gowadu godou goneiga manu e gai go goodou i nia hiahi huogodoo, gei nia palaawaa e logo be di godou hiihai i nia luada huogodoo, i Mee gu longono Ia di godou tamu Ia. Idimaa hagalee go gimaua ala ne tamu go goodou, ma go Dimaadua.”
\p 
\v 9 Moses ga helekai gi Aaron bolo digau Israel huogodoo gi lloomoi gii tuu i mua o Dimaadua, i Mee gu longono Ia nadau tamu nogo hai.
\v 10 Di madagoaa hua a Aaron ne helekai gi tagabuli deelaa, gei digaula gaa huli ga mmada adu gi di anggowaa, gei di madamada o Dimaadua gu gidee i lodo di gololangi.
\v 11 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses,
\v 12 “Au gu longono digau Israel nogo tamu Au. Hagi anga ina gi digaula bolo ma ga hiahi, gei digaula gaa gai nadau goneiga manu, ge ma ga luada gei digaula gaa gai nadau palaawaa logowaahee, gi iloo ginaadou bolo ma ko Au go Dimaadua, go di nadau God.”
\p 
\v 13 Gaa dae gi di hiahi, gei nia manu ‘quail’ gu mmaangi mai, gu buni hua i lodo di waahale laa, ge luada la go di gohu o di magalillili gu i di gili di waahale laa deelaa.
\v 14 Di gohu o di magalillili o di luada la ne maa, gei nia mee be nia una iga e mmoemmoe i hongo nia gelegele i lodo di anggowaa.
\v 15 Digau Israel ne mmada e de iloo be nia maa ni aha, ga heheeu i nadau mehanga boloo, “Nia maa ni aha aanei?”
\p Gei Moses ga helekai, “Nia mee aanei la go nia palaawaa a Dimaadua ala ne gowadu gi goodou e gai.\x * \xo 16.15 \xt 1-Corinthians 10.3\x*
\v 16 Dimaadua guu hai bolo tangada nei i goodou gi hagabudu ina ana mee ala e dohu ang gi deia, holongo di baahi galon ang gi tangada e dahi i digau huogodoo i dono hale.”
\p 
\v 17 Digau Israel guu hai di maa beenei, hunu gau gu haga budu gu iehe, ge hunu gau gu haga budu nadau mee hogoohi.
\v 18 Digau ala ne hagabudu nadau mee gii logo, la digi logowaahee, gu dohu hua, gei digau ala ne haga budu nadau mee hogoohi laa, hagalee hogoohi, digaula huogodoo guu dohu hua.\x * \xo 16.18 \xt 2-Corinthians 8.15\x*
\v 19 Moses ga helekai gi digaula, “Deai tangada e dugu ana mee dubu gi daiaa ai.”
\v 20 Hunu gau hagalee hagalongo gi Moses, e benebene nadau mee dubu gi luada dono daiaa. Hooaga luada, gei nia maa guu ila gu bilau, gei Moses gu hagawelewele gi digaula.
\v 21 Malaa, nia luada huogodoo, tangada nei mo tangada nei e haga budu hua ana mee ala e dohu ang gi deia. Di madagoaa di laa ma gaa dii, gei nia mee ala ne dubu ga waiwai gi daha.
\p 
\v 22 Di ono laangi gei digaula gu haga budu nadau meegai holongo lua, nia pauna e madangaholu maa lua ang gi tangada e dahi, gei nia dagi o Israel ga lloomoi ga hagi anga gi Moses bolo deelaa di hai ne hai.
\v 23 Gei mee ga helekai gi digaula, “Dimaadua guu hai bolo daiaa la di Laangi Sabad e hagamolooloo, di laangi dela e hagadabu ang gi Dimaadua. Goodou daa ina godou mee ala belee daa gi di imu, ge godou mee belee dunu gi di baalanga la dunaa ina, gei nia mee ala gaa dubu la benabena gi dono daiaa.”\x * \xo 16.23 \xt Exodus 20.8-11\x*
\v 24 Digaula gaa hai be nia helekai a Moses, ga benebene nia mee ala e dubu gi dono daiaa, ge nia maa digi bilau, ge deai nia ila i lodo nia maa ai.
\v 25 Moses ga helekai, “Goodou geina godou mee aalaa dangi nei, idimaa deenei di laangi hagamolooloo e hagadabu ang gi Dimaadua. Goodou e deemee di kida nia meegai i lodo henua dangi nei.
\v 26 Nia laangi e ono, gei goodou gi hagabudu ina godou mee, idimaa di hidu laangi la di Laangi Sabad, deai nia mee e hai ai.”
\p 
\v 27 Hunu gau i digaula guu hula haga budu nadau mee i di Laangi Sabad, ge digi kida nadau mee.
\v 28 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “E waalooloo behee go di godou dee daudali agu haganoho?
\v 29 Goodou la gi langahia bolo Au go Dimaadua ne gowadu di laangi hagamolooloo, gei di ono laangi e gowadu agu meegai ala e dohu gi nia laangi e lua, bolo huogodoo gi noho hua i godou hale i di hidu laangi, hagalee e ulu gi daha.
\v 30 Malaa, digaula gu hagamolooloo i di hidu laangi.”
\p 
\v 31 Digau Israel ga haga ingoo nia meegai aalaa bolo ‘manna’.\f + \fr 16.31 \ft Di bida helekai \bk manna\bk* i lodo telekai Hebrew le e hai dono lee boloo “Ma ni aha?”\f* Nia maa e hai gadoo be nia dama golee kene, ge di kala o di maa le e hai gadoo be nia palaawaa ne unugi mono mee maangala lodo henua.\x * \xo 16.31 \xt Numbers 11.7-8\x*
\v 32 Moses ga helekai, “Dimaadua la guu hai bolo gidaadou la gi benebene ina di baahi galon i tadau ‘manna’ ang gi tadau hagadili, gi gidee digaula bolo aalaa go nia meegai a Mee nogo haangai gidaadou i lodo di anggowaa i dono dagi mai gidaadou i Egypt.”
\v 33 Moses ga helekai gi Aaron, “Haawa dau loaabi hadu gi nia ‘manna’ gii hai di baahi galon, gaa dugu kooe gi mua o Dimaadua, bolo e benebene ang gi tadau hagadili.”\x * \xo 16.33 \xt Hebrews 9.4\x*
\v 34 Aaron gaa dugu di loaabi gi mua Tebedebe o di Hagababa gi benebene nia maa i golo, be nia helekai a Dimaadua ala ne hai gi Moses.
\v 35 Digau Israel nogo miami i nia ‘manna’ aanei i lodo nia ngadau e mada haa, gaa dae loo gi di nadau dau gi tenua go Canaan, gaa noho i golo.\x * \xo 16.35 \xt Joshua 5.12\x*
\v 36 (Di baahi galon le e tongaadahi gi dahi baahi madangaholu o di mee dela e papauna nia huwa laagau a digaula.)
\c 17
\s1 Nia wai mai i lodo tadugalaa
\r (Numbers 20.1-13)
\p 
\v 1 Digau Israel huogodoo ga hagatanga i di Anggowaa o Sin, ga taele gi di gowaa nei mo di gowaa nei, mai nnelekai o Dimaadua gi digaula, gaa dau i Rephidim ga haga duu nadau hale laa i golo, di gowaa deelaa la ono wai inu ai.
\v 2 Gei digaula gaa hai nadau donu gi Moses boloo, “Goe haga inumia gimaadou.”
\p Gei Moses ga helekai, “Goodou e hai baahi mai gi di au eiaha? Goodou e hagamada a Dimaadua eiaha?”
\p 
\v 3 Digaula gu hieinu gaa tamu a Moses boloo, “Goe ne laha mai gimaadou nogo i Egypt laa i aha? Goe ne laha mai gimaadou belee daaligi gimaadou mo madau dama mo madau manu gii mmade?”
\p 
\v 4 Gei Moses ga dalodalo hagamahi gi Dimaadua, “Au gaa hai dagu aha gi digau aanei? Digaula e hoohoo hua ga dilidili au.”
\p 
\v 5 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Gahia mai nia dagi o digau Israel, hula goodou i mua digau Israel. Kae ina dau dogodogo dela nogo hagamaawa di monowai Nile.
\v 6 Au ga duu laa i oo mua i hongo di Gonduu Sinai, gei goe ga hagamaawa tadugalaa, gei nia wai gaa hali mai, e inu ai nia daangada.” Gei Moses gaa hai hua nia mee aanei hagammaa i mua nia dagi o digau Israel.
\p 
\v 7 Di gowaa deelaa gu haga ingoo bolo ‘Massah’ mo ‘Meribah’\f + \fr 17.7 \fk Massah mo Meribah: \ft Nia ingoo e lua aanei le hai nau lee i nnelekai Hebrew boloo “hagamada” mo “tamu” \f* i digau Israel ne hai tamu gei gu hagamada a Dimaadua gi di nadau heeu boloo, “Dimaadua la i tadau baahi be hagalee?”
\s1 Tauwa ang gi digau Amalek
\p 
\v 8 Digau Amalek ne lloomoi ga heebagi gi digau Israel i Rephidim.
\v 9 Gei Moses ga helekai gi Joshua, “Hilia au daane, e hula e heebagi gi digau Amalek daiaa. Au gaa duu laa i hongo di gonduu deelaa, e daahi togodogo hagamadagu a God.”
\v 10 Gei Joshua gaa hana ga heebagi gi digau Amalek be nia helekai a Moses ne hai, gei Moses mo Aaron mo Hur guu hula gi hongo di gonduu deelaa.
\v 11 Malaa, di waalooloo o Moses e daahi ono lima gi nua, gei digau Israel ga heebagi maaloo, gei mee ma gaa dugu ono lima gi lala, gei digau Amalek ga heebagi maaloo.
\v 12 Nia lima o Moses ma ga maanu, gei ogo Aaron mo Hur ga gaamai di nau hadugalaa, ga haga noho a Moses gi nonua, gei meemaa gaa tuu i baahi o mee, e daahi nia lima o maa gi nua, gaa dae loo gi di laa ga ulu.
\v 13 Gei Joshua gu daaligi digau Amalek huogodoo i di hai deenei ne hai.
\p 
\v 14 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hihia di mee deenei gi lodo di beebaa e hai di mee haga langahia. Gei goe gi haga iloo ina gi Joshua bolo Au ga hagammaa digau Amalek gi hagalee.”\x * \xo 17.14 \xt Deuteronomy 25.17-19; 1-Samuel 15.2-9\x*
\v 15 Moses ga haga duu dana gowaa hai tigidaumaha i di gowaa deelaa, ga haga ingoo boloo ‘Yihowah Nissi’\f + \fr 17.15 \fk Yihowah Nissi \ft di ingoo deenei dono hadinga boloo, “Dimaadua la go dagu Hagallebe”.\f*
\v 16 mo di helekai, “Dahi aga ina gi nua tagallebe o Dimaadua, gei Dimaadua la ga heebagi gi digau Amalek ga hana hua dee odi!”
\c 18
\s1 Jethro e hana hagahidihidi gi baahi Moses
\p 
\v 1 Jethro, tamana di lodo Moses, tangada hai mee dabu o Midian, gu longono nia mee huogodoo Dimaadua ne hai gi digau Israel mo Moses i dana dagi digaula gi daha mo Egypt.
\v 2 Mee ga hanimoi gi Moses, ga laha mai a Zipporah di lodo Moses dela ne dugu,
\v 3 mo Gershom mo Eliezer, nia dama daane dogolua a Zipporah. (Moses gu helekai, “Au nogo hai tangada henua gee i hongo tenua digau tuadimee”, gei mee ga hagaingoo dana dama daane e dahi bolo Gershom.\f + \fr 18.3 \fk Gershom: \ft Di lee o di ingoo deenei i nnelekai Hebrew le e hai gadoo be di bida helekai “tangada mai i daha”.\f*\x * \xo 18.3 \xt Acts 7.29\x*
\v 4 Mee gu helekai labelaa, “Di God o dogu damana gu hagamaamaa au gu hagalee daaligi go di king Egypt”, gei mee gaa gahi dana dama daane dela i golo bolo Eliezer.\f + \fr 18.4 \fk Eliezer: \ft Di lee o di ingoo deenei i nnelekai Hebrew le e hai gadoo be di bida helekai “God e hagamaamaa au”.\f*)
\v 5 Jethro ga hanimoi dalia di lodo Moses mo ana dama dogolua gi hongo di anggowaa, di gowaa nogo noho ai Moses hoohoo gi di gonduu hagamadagu Dimaadua.
\v 6 Mee gu hagailoo gi Moses bolo ginaadou e lloomoi,
\v 7 gei Moses gaa hana belee heetugi gi mee, ga bala gi lala i mua o mee gaa hongi a mee. Digaula ga heheeu be ginaadou guu hai behee, ga ulu gi lodo di hale laa Moses.
\v 8 Moses ga hagi anga gi Jethro nia mee huogodoo Dimaadua ne hai gi di king mo nia daangada Egypt belee haga dagaloaha digau Israel. Mee gu hagi anga labelaa gi mee nia haingadaa ne heetugi ginai ginaadou i di nadau lloomoi, mo di hai Dimaadua ne benebene ginaadou.
\v 9 Jethro ne longono ia nia mee aanei huogodoo, ge gu tenetene,
\v 10 ga helekai,
\q1 “Hagaamuina Dimaadua dela
\q1 ne benebene goodou gi daha mo di
\q1 king mo nia daangada o Egypt.
\q1 Hagaamuina Dimaadua dela
\q1 ne benebene ana daangada gi daha
\q1 mo di hai hege”.
\m 
\v 11 Dolomeenei au e iloo bolo Dimaadua e aamua i nia god huogodoo, idimaa Dimaadua guu hai di mee deenei gi digau Egypt ala nogo hagahuaidu digau Israel.
\v 12 Jethro ga gaamai dana tigidaumaha belee dudu hagadogomaalia mono tigidaumaha ala i golo belee wanga gi God, ge Aaron mo nia dagi Israel huogodoo gaa hula belee miami e hagagila nnangaahai daumaha.
\s1 Moses e dongo digau hai gabunga
\r (Deuteronomy 1.9-18)
\p 
\v 13 Di laangi nomuli, gei Moses nogo daadaamee e haga donudonu nia mee i mehanga nia daangada mai di luada gaa tugi i di boo.
\v 14 Jethro ne mmada gi nia mee huogodoo a Moses e hai, ga heeu, “Ma ni aha ala e hai kooe gi nia daangada? Goe e aha dela e hai nia maa modogoe gei nia daangada e tuu i kinei mai luada gaa tugi di boo belee heeu adu nadau mee?”
\v 15 Moses ga helekai, “Au e hai gii hai beenei idimaa nia daangada e lloomoi gi di au e kabe di manawa o God.
\v 16 Nia daangada dogolua ma ga lagalagamaaloo, meemaa e lloomoi gi di au, gei au ga hilihili be di ma koai dela e donu i meemaa, gei au e hagi anga gi meemaa nnelekai mo nnaganoho a God.”
\p 
\v 17 Jethro ga helekai, “Goe hagalee hai donu nia mee aanei.
\v 18 Goe ga hagaduadua goe mo nia daangada aanei. Aanei la guu logo balua di hai kooe modogoe.
\v 19 Dugua mai e gowadu nia hagamaamaa humalia, gei God ga madalia laa goe. Ma e donu go dau pono nia daangada i mua o God, e gaamai nadau lagamaaloo gi Mee.
\v 20 Goe ne belee aago nnelekai a God gi nia daangada, ga hagamodongoohia di hai e noho mo e mouli, gei ni aha belee hai go ginaadou.
\v 21 E humalia goe hilihilia hunu daangada ala e mee, gaa dongo digaula e hai nia dagi o nia daangada: Nia dagi nia madahaanau dagi mana, dagi llau, dagi madalima mo dagi madangaholu. Digaula e hai gii hai digau e mmaadagu i God, e hagadagadagagee ginai, e deemee di hui halahalau go tangada gi nia bahihadu.
\v 22 Heia digaula gi ngalua be digau hai gabunga i nia madagoaa huogodoo ang gi digau Israel. Digaula e mee di gaamai nia gabunga haingadaa huogodoo gi di goe, gaa hai nia lagamaaloo lligi huogodoo go ginaadou. Deelaa di hai ga haga haingoohia, i digaula ala gaa dau e hagamaamaa goe.
\v 23 Maa goe gaa hai di mee deenei be nnelekai a God, goe ga hagalee hagaduadua goe, gei nia daangada huogodoo gaa hula gi nadau guongo, gei nadau lagamaaloo ga hagahumalia.”
\p 
\v 24 Moses gu daudali nnelekai a Jethro,
\v 25 ga hilihili nia daane e mee di hai nnegau i lodo digau Israel huogodoo. Mee ne dongo digaula belee hai nia dagi o nia daangada madangaholu llau, dagi llau, dagi madalima mo dagi madangaholu.
\v 26 Digaula e hai hegau be digau hai gabunga e ngalua gi muli ang gi nia daangada, e gaamai nia gabunga haingadaa gi Moses, gaa hai nia gabunga lligi go ginaadou.
\p 
\v 27 Moses ga hagaaloho hagamaewae gi Jethro dela gaa hana gi muli gi dono guongo.
\c 19
\s1 Digau Israel i di Gonduu Sinai
\p 
\v 1-2 Digau Israel ga hagatanga i Rephidim, gaa dau i di Anggowaa o Sinai i tahi laangi o di tolu malama i muli nadau hagatanga gi daha mo Egypt, ga haga duu aga nadau hale laa i mua di Gonduu Sinai.
\v 3 Moses gaa hana gi tomo di gonduu deelaa belee heetugi gi God.
\p Dimaadua gaa gahi a mee mai i hongo di gonduu bolo gi helekai gi digau Israel, go di madawaawa Jacob, boloo,
\v 4 “Goodou gu gidee hua hagammaa gi agu mee ala ne hai ko Au go Dimaadua gi digau Egypt mo dagu laha mai goodou gadoo be di ‘eagle’ e laha mai ana dama i hongo ono bakau.
\v 5 Maa goodou ga hagalongo mai gi di Au mo di haga gila aga agu hagababa, gei goodou gaa hai digau hagalabagau ni aagu. Henuailala hagatau la di mee ni aagu, gei goodou digau ni aagu ne hilihili.\x * \xo 19.5 \xt Deuteronomy 4.20; 7.6; 14.2; 26.18; Titus 2.14\x* \x * \xo 19.5 \xt 1-Peter 2.9\x*
\v 6 Goodou gaa hai di golohenua dela gu hagadabu mai gi di Au modo go Au ge ga hai hegau mai gi di Au be digau hai mee dabu.”\x * \xo 19.6 \xt Revelation 1.6; 5.10\x*
\v 7 Gei Moses ga haneia, ga haga dagabuli mai nia dagi ga hagi anga nia helekai a Dimaadua ala ne hai.
\v 8 Digau huogodoo ga helekai be di mee e dahi boloo, “Gimaadou gaa hai nia helekai a Dimaadua la gii kila huogodoo.” Gei Moses ga hagi anga telekai digaula gi Dimaadua.
\p 
\v 9 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Au ga haneia i lodo di gololangi maadolu e helekai adu gi di goe, gei digaula ga longono ga hagadonu goe gaa hana hua beelaa.”
\p Gei Moses ga hagi anga telekai digaula gi Dimaadua.
\v 10 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hana labelaa, helekai gi digaula bolo ginaadou gi hagatogomaalia ina dangi nei mo daiaa ang gi di hai daumaha. Digaula gi heia nadau gahu gi madammaa,
\v 11 ge gi togomaalia labelaa gi dono daiaa, idimaa deelaa di laangi e haneia iei Au gi hongo di Gonduu Sinai, deelaa di gowaa ga gidee ginaadou Au.
\v 12 Dugua di hagageinga e haganiga di gonduu deenei, e bule nia daangada gi dee lloo aga gi hongo di gonduu deenei, ge hudee tale gi tono di gonduu. Tangada dela ma gaa tale gi di gonduu le e daaligi gii made.\x * \xo 19.12 \xt Hebrews 12.18-20\x*
\v 13 Tangada deelaa la gi dilidilia gi nia hadu, be gi puugia gi nia maalei, ge deai tangada e bili gi mee ai. Di mee deenei le e hai gi nia daangada mono manu, digaula la gi daaligidia gii mmade. Di madagoaa o nia buu ma ga iliili haga lloo, deelaa di madagoaa digau Israel ga lloo aga ai gi di gonduu.”
\p 
\v 14 Moses gaa gaga ia i di gonduu gi baahi o nia daangada, ga helekai gi digaula bolo gi togomaalia ginaadou gi taumaha. Gei digaula gaa tugi nadau goloo gii mmaa,
\v 15 gei Moses ga helekai gi digaula, “Goodou heia goodou gi togomaalia gi dono daiaa, goodou hudee heia di hiihai o taga hai lodo.”
\p 
\v 16 Malaa, luada togodolu laangi, gei di atili gu maawa i hongo di gonduu, gei nia ila gu dabadaba, gei di gololangi maadolu guu gahu di gonduu guu buni. Gei di lee o di buu gu hai loo gi nua i lodo di ahiaalangi, gei digau o di waa hale laa gu polepole mo di uli nadau gai.\x * \xo 19.16 \xt Revelation 4.5\x* \x * \xo 19.16 \xt Deuteronomy 4.11-12\x*
\v 17 Moses ga dagi mai digaula gi daha mo lodo di waahale belee heetugi ang gi God, gei digaula gaa tuu i golo i tono di gonduu.
\v 18 Gei di huiahi guu gohu guu gahu di Gonduu Sinai, idimaa Dimaadua ne haneia i lodo di ulaula ahi. Di gonduu la guu gohu gadoo be di huiahi imu damanaiee, gei nia daangada gu polepole gu uli nadau gai.
\v 19 Di lee o di buu dela e iliili gu longono gi nonua mai. Moses ga helekai, gei God ga helekai gi mee i di lee atili.
\v 20 Dimaadua ga haneia gi hongo di Gonduu Sinai ga gahi aga a Moses gi golo, gei Moses guu hana gi Mee.
\v 21 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi mee, “Hana gi lala, helekai gi nia daangada bolo ginaadou hudee lloomoi laa hongo tagageinga bolo e mmada mai gi di Au, gi dee mmade ginaadou dogologo.
\v 22 Digau hai mee dabu hogi ala ma ga hoohoo mai gi di Au, e hai gi hagadabu ina ginaadou mai gi di Au, ma ga hagalee hagadabu, gei Au ga hagahuaidu digaula.”
\p 
\v 23 Moses ga helekai gi Dimaadua, “Nia daangada le e deemee di lloo aga, i di Goe guu hai bolo gimaadou gi hagamadagudia ina di gonduu deenei ge gi hagageinga ina di maa.”
\p 
\v 24 Dimaadua ga helekai, “Hana, laha aga a Aaron madalia goe. Gei digau hai mee dabu mo digau Israel hudee lloomoi gi lodo tagageinga belee lloo aga gi di Au, gi de hagahuaidu digaula ko Au.”
\v 25 Malaa, Moses ga haneia ga hagi anga gi digaula beenei.
\c 20
\s1 Madangaholu Haganoho
\r (Deuteronomy 5.1-21)
\p 
\v 1 God ga helekai i nia helekai aanei:
\b
\q1 1
\v 2 Ko au go Yihowah go di godou God
\q1 dela ne dagi mai goodou gi daha
\q1 mo Egypt, di godou gowaa
\q1 dela nogo ngalua hege ai.
\q1 
\v 3 Goodou hudee hai god hua gee mo Au.
\b
\q1 2
\v 4 Goodou hudee hai god gi nia ada o
\q1 tei mee i di langi i nua be i henuailala,
\q1 be i lodo di moana o lala henuailala.\x * \xo 20.4 \xt Exodus 34.17; Leviticus 19.4; 26.1; Deuteronomy 4.15-18; 27.15\x*
\q1 
\v 5 Hudee pala ginai be e daumaha ginai,
\q1 idimaa, deenei Au go Yihowah
\q1 go di godou God, di God dubua.
\q1 Digau ala ma ga ginagina i di Au,
\q1 gei Au ga hagaduadua digaula
\q1 mo nadau hagadili gi muli gaa dae loo
\q1 gi di tolu mo di haa adu dangada.\x * \xo 20.5 \xt Exodus 34.6-7; Numbers 14.18; Deuteronomy 7.9-10\x*
\q1 
\v 6 Gei Au e dumaalia hua gi nia mada
\q1 haanau e mana o digau ala e aloho
\q1 i di Au ge e haga kila aga agu haganoho.
\b
\q1 3
\v 7 Goodou hudee hai hegau ihala
\q1 gi dogu ingoo,
\q1 idimaa ko au go Yihowah go di godou
\q1 God dela e hagahuaidu tangada
\q1 dela ma ga hai hegau ihala dogu ingoo.\x * \xo 20.7 \xt Leviticus 19.12\x*
\b
\q1 4
\v 8 Gi langahia di Laangi Sabad,
\q1 heia gi dabuaahia.\x * \xo 20.8 \xt Exodus 16.23-30; 31.12-14\x*
\q1 
\v 9 Heia godou moomee gii lawa i lodo
\q1 nia laangi e ono.\x * \xo 20.9 \xt Exodus 23.12; 31.15; 34.21; 35.2; Leviticus 23.3\x*
\q1 
\v 10 Gei di hidu laangi
\q1 la di laangi hagamolooloo,
\q1 e haga dabu ai goodou mai gi di Au.
\q1 Deai tangada i goodou
\q1 e hai ana moomee ai,
\q1 goodou mo godou dama
\q1 mo godou gau hai hegau mo godou manu,
\q1 mo digau mai i daha ala e noho goodou.
\q1 
\v 11 Go Au ne hai di langi mo henuailala
\q1 mo di moana mo ono mee huogodoo
\q1 ala i ono lodo i nia laangi e ono,
\q1 ga hagamolooloo i di hidu laangi,
\q1 deelaa dagu mee ne hagahumalia ai
\q1 di Laangi Sabad gaa hai gi dabuaahia.\x * \xo 20.11 \xt Genesis 2.1-3; Exodus 31.17\x*
\b
\q1 5
\v 12 Hagalabagau ina do damana
\q1 mo do dinana, gi mouli goe waalooloo
\q1 i hongo dagu henua
\q1 dela ga gowadu ko Au gi di goe.\x * \xo 20.12 \xt Deuteronomy 27.16; Matthew 15.4; 19.19; Mark 7.10; 10.19; Luke 18.20; Ephesians 6.2,3\x*
\b
\q1 6
\v 13 Hudee daaligidia tangada gii made.\x * \xo 20.13 \xt Genesis 9.6; Leviticus 24.17; Matthew 5.21; 19.18; Mark 10.19; Luke 18.20; Romans 13.9; James 2.11\x*
\b
\q1 7
\v 14 Hudee hai be di manu.\x * \xo 20.14 \xt Leviticus 20.10; Matthew 5.27; 19.18; Mark 10.19; Luke 18.20; Romans 13.9; James 2.11\x*
\b
\q1 8
\v 15 Hudee gaiaadanga.\x * \xo 20.15 \xt Leviticus 19.11; Matthew 19.18; Mark 10.19; Luke 18.20; Romans 13.9\x*
\b
\q1 9
\v 16 Hudee hagahuaidu ina tangada
\q1 gi nia kai tilikai.\x * \xo 20.16 \xt Exodus 23.1; Matthew 19.18; Mark 10.19; Luke 18.20\x*
\b
\q1 10
\v 17 Hudee hagagailaa gi di hale o tangada,
\q1 be go dono lodo, be go ana ‘donkey’,
\q1 be go dana kau, be go di ingoo hua
\q1 di mee i ana mee.\x * \xo 20.17 \xt Romans 7.7; 13.9\x*
\s1 Nia daangada gu mmaadagu
\r (Deuteronomy 5.22-33)
\p 
\v 18 Di madagoaa digau Israel ne longono nia lee atili mono lee buu iliili ge ne mmada gi nia ila ala e dabadaba, mo di gonduu dela guu gohu, digaula gu polepole i di nadau mmaadagu, gu tuu hua mogowaa i daha mo di gonduu deelaa.\x * \xo 20.18 \xt Hebrews 12.18-19\x*
\v 19 Gei digaula ga helekai gi Moses, “Ma kooe hua belee helekai mai gi gimaadou, gei gimaadou ga hagalongo adu. Hudee heia God gi helekai mai gi gimaadou, gi dee mmade hua gimaadou.”
\p 
\v 20 Gei Moses ga helekai, “Goodou hudee mmaadagu. God ne hanimoi hua belee hagamada goodou, gii hai goodou digau e hagalongo, gi dee hai goodou digau e hai hala gi Mee.”
\v 21 Gei nia daangada gu tuu hua mada tanga i di gonduu, go Moses hua modogoia dela ne hana gi hoohoo gi di gololangi maadolu dela e noho ai a God i ono lodo.
\s1 Nnaganoho nia gowaa hai tigidaumaha
\p 
\v 22 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses bolo gi hagi anga ina gi digau Israel, “Goodou gu mmada mai gi di Au go Dimaadua i dagu hai ne helekai adu gi goodou mai di langi.
\v 23 Hudee hai nia ada god silber be goolo e daumaha ginai goodou laa daha mo Au.
\v 24 Heia dagu gowaa hai tigidaumaha gi nia gelegele henua, tigidaumaha ina nia siibi mono kau e dudu dogomaalia e hai ai tigidaumaha hagadaubuni. I nia gowaa huogodoo ala ne dugu ko Au bolo e daumaha mai goodou, Au ga hanimoi e haga maluagina goodou.
\v 25 Maa goodou gaa hai di gowaa hai tigidaumaha gi nia hadugalaa, hudee heia di maa gi nia hadu ne hahaahi, idimaa, goodou ma ga hai hegau gi di ‘chisel’ e haluhalu nia hadu, goodou e hai nia maa gi hagalee humalia di hai hegau iei Au.
\v 26 Goodou hudee hauhia mai gi di Au di gowaa hai tigidaumaha dela e gaga di gaagenge gi nua, gi dee kila mai godou huaidina i di godou madagoaa ma gaa kaga gi nua.
\c 21
\s1 Nnangahaihai nia hege
\p 
\v 1 “Wanga ina nnaganoho aanei gi digau Israel:
\v 2 Maa goe gaa hui dau hege dangada Israel, mee e ngalua adu i lodo nia ngadau e ono. I lodo di hidu ngadau, mee e hagamehede ge hagalee e hui ana mee.\x * \xo 21.2 \xt Leviticus 25.39-46\x*
\v 3 Maa mee digi hai dono lodo i dono madagoaa ne daamada gaa hege, mee hagalee lahi dono lodo dalia ia ma ga hagatanga. Maa mee guu hai dono lodo i mua dono hai dau hege, mee e mee di lahi dono lodo dalia ia.
\v 4 Maa di tagi di hale guu wanga dana ahina gii lodo ginai dana hege, gei di ahina deelaa gaa hai ana dama daane mono dama ahina, di ahina mo nia dama aalaa la nia daangada ni di tagi di hale, gei di hege le e hagatanga hua e hana modogoia.
\v 5 Maa di hege gaa hai bolo ia e aloho i dono dagi, dono lodo mo ana dama, gei e de hiihai bolo e hagamehede,
\v 6 gei dono dagi gaa lahi a mee gi di gowaa hai daumaha. Di tagi o maa ga hagaduu a mee gi taalinga di bontai, ga haga bongoo talinga o maa, gei mee gaa hai dana hege i lodo dono mouli hagatau.
\p 
\v 7 “Maa taane gaa hui gi daha dana dama ahina belee hai di hege, tama ahina hagalee hagamehede gadoo be nia hege daane.
\v 8 Maa di ahina deenei la ne hui gi tangada belee hai dono lodo gi mee, gei taane la hagalee hiihai gi mee, mee gaa hui gi muli gi dono damana. Di tagi o maa e deemee di hui a mee gi tangada henua gee, idimaa di tagi o maa guu hai a mee hagahuaidu.
\v 9 Maa taane gaa hui dana hege ahina belee wanga gi dana dama daane, mee e dugu a mee be dana dama ahina.
\v 10 Maa taane gaa hai dono lua lodo, mee e hai gi wangawanga hua igolo gi dono lodo matagidagi nia meegai, nia gahu mo nia donu ala nogo hai mee ginai mee i mua.
\v 11 Maa mee ga hagalee hagahonu ono waawa gi di ahina matagidagi, mee e hai gi hagamehede a mee ge hagalee kumi dono hui.
\s1 Nnaganoho o nnanga ngalungalua dodookono
\p 
\v 12 “Tangada ma ga daaligi dana dangada gii made le e daaligi gii made.\x * \xo 21.12 \xt Leviticus 24.17\x*
\v 13 Maa di mee hua ne tiba ga daaligi dana dangada gii made, mee e mee di lele gi daha gi di gowaa dela ga hagi anga ko Au gi goodou gei mee gaa noho i golo i di aumaalia.
\v 14 Maa tangada ga hagawelewele ga daaligi dana dangada gii made, mee e daaligi gii made, ma e aha maa mee guu lele gi di gowaa hai tigidaumaha.
\p 
\v 15 “Be koai hua ma ga daaligi dono damana be go dono dinana le e daaligi gii made.
\p 
\v 16 “Be koai hua ga gaiaa dana dangada belee hui gi daha be e hai dana hege le e daaligi gii made.\x * \xo 21.16 \xt Deuteronomy 24.7\x*
\p 
\v 17 “Tangada ma ga helekai huaidu i dono damana be dono dinana le e daaligi gii made.\x * \xo 21.17 \xt Leviticus 20.9; Matthew 15.4; Mark 7.10\x*
\p 
\v 18-19 “Maa teebagi gaa hai, gei tangada ga daaligi dana dangada gi di hadu be gi dono lima ge digi daaligidia a mee gii made, mee hagalee hagaduadua. Maa tangada ne daaligi la guu kii i hongo di moenge, nomuli ga du gi nua ga heehee i malaelae gi togodogo, tangada ne daaligi a mee le e hui dono kii magi mo nia mee ne hai di magi o maa, gaa dae loo gi dono hili.
\p 
\v 20 “Maa taane ga daaligi dana hege daane be ahina gi di laagau, gei di hege gaa made hua i golo, taane le e daaligi.
\v 21 Maa di hege la digi made i di laangi e dahi be lua, tagi o maa hagalee hagaduadua, idimaa di hege la di mee ni mee.
\p 
\v 22 “Maa hunu daane e heebagi gaa tugi di ahina hai dama, gei dana dama guu made i lodo tinae, gei di ahina digi lauwa, tangada dela ne tugi di ahina deelaa, le e hui gi di ahina deelaa di hulu dela e hiihai ginai taane di lodo o di ahina deelaa, e hagamogobuna go digau hai gabunga.
\v 23 Maa di ahina la gu mohole, di hagaduadua la ga hagatau gi di mouli ang gi di mouli,
\v 24 di golomada ang gi di golomada, di niha ang gi di niha, di lima ang gi di lima, di babaewae ang gi di babaewae,\x * \xo 21.24 \xt Leviticus 24.19-20; Deuteronomy 19.21; Matthew 5.38\x*
\v 25 di wele ang gi di wele, di lauwa ang gi di lauwa, mo di mohole ang gi di mohole.
\p 
\v 26 “Maa tangada gaa tugi di golomada o dana hege daane be ahina gaa hai di maa gii doo gi daha, di tagi deelaa le e hagamehede di hege deelaa e hai ai di hui o di golomada.
\v 27 Maa tangada ga hagadoo di niha dana hege, di tagi e hai gi hagamehede di hege e hui di niha.
\s1 Di waawa tangada i ana mee
\p 
\v 28 “Maa di kau daane ga daaligi dana dangada gii made, di kau deelaa le e dilidili, gei nia goneiga di maa e hagalee gai, ge tangada dana kau le hagalee hagaduadua.
\v 29 Maa di kau daane e nnoo mau e heheebagi gi nia daangada, tangada dana kau dela gu hagailoo ginai gei mee digi hai dana duuli, gei di kau ga daaligi dana dangada gii made, di kau le e dilidili gii made ge tangada dana kau le e daaligi gii made labelaa.
\v 30 Ge tangada dana kau e mee di dumaalia ginai gi huia dana daabani e benebene dono mouli, gei mee gi huia di hulu hagatau.
\v 31 Maa di kau ga daaligi dana dama daane be dama ahina, taganoho la hua e hai hegau ai.
\v 32 Maa di kau ga daaligi dana hege daane be ahina, tangada dana kau e hui nia silber e motolu di hege e dahi, gei di kau le e dilidili gii made.
\p 
\v 33 “Maa tangada ga daa gi daha di pono di bongoo, be e geli dana bongoo ge hagalee gahu di maa, gei di kau be di ‘donkey’ gaa doo gi lodo,
\v 34 mee e hai gii hui di manu gi tangada ana manu, gei e mee di hai mee gi di manu ne made.
\v 35 Maa di kau daane o tangada ga daaligi di kau daane o tangada i golo, nia daane dogolua aanei le e hui gi daha di kau deelaa e mouli, ga wwae lua nia bahihadu i ginaua. Meemaa belee wwae labelaa i ginaua nia goneiga di kau dela ne made.
\v 36 Gei di manu le e nnoo mau e heheebagi gi nia manu, gei tangada dana manu digi duulia dana manu, mee e hagahumalia tangada ne made dana manu, e wanga gi mee dana manu mouli, gei mee e hai mee gi di manu ne made.
\c 22
\s1 Nnaganoho nia hui nia mee gaiaa
\p 
\v 1 “Maa tangada ga gaiaa dana kau be siibi ga daaligi be e hui di maa gi daha, mee e hai loo gii hui gi muli ana kau e lima ang gi di kau e dahi, mo ana siibi e haa ang gi di siibi e dahi.\x * \xo 22.1 \xt Luke 19.8\x*
\v 2-4 Tangada gaiaa le e hai loo gii hui gi muli ana mee ne gaiaa. Maa mee ana mee ai, mee e hui ia gi daha be di hege e hui ana mee ne gaiaa. Maa di kau, ‘donkey’ be di siibi gaa gida mouli i baahi tangada deenei, mee e hui ana manu e lua ang gi di manu e dahi.
\p “Maa tangada gaiaa gaa poo e ulu i di boo gi lodo di hale tangada, ga daaligi gaa made, tangada dela ne daaligi tangada gaiaa le e hagalee hala, maa di mee deenei ne hai i di aa, gei tangada dono hale e hala di daaligi tangada gaiaa.
\p 
\v 5 “Maa tangada gaa dugu ana manu gi miami i lodo di gowaa be di gowaa dogi waini gei nia manu a maa ga heehee hua gi di gowaa o tuai dangada, gaa gai nia hagadili tangada dana gowaa, tangada ana manu le e hui nia hagadili ne mooho i lodo di gowaa be di gowaa dogi waini tangada.
\p 
\v 6 “Maa tangada ga daamada dana ahi i lodo dana gowaa dogi mee, gei di maa ga modoho gi lodo di gowaa tuai dangada, gaa dudu nia hagadili ala e tomo i golo, be nia hagadili ala gu daagi gu hagabae gi nua, tangada ne daamada di ahi le e hui nia mee ne mooho.
\p 
\v 7 “Maa tangada gaa donu ginai bolo e benebene nia bahihadu tangada, be nia mee dahidamee, gei nia maa ga gaiaa i dono hale, gei tangada dela ne gaiaa nia maa guu gida le e hui holongo lua nia maa.
\v 8 Gei tangada gaiaa la digi gida, tangada nogo benebene nia mee dahidamee e lahi gi di gowaa hai daumaha e hai dana helekai hagamodu bolo ia digi kaina nia maa.
\p 
\v 9 “Di hai e gabunga i mehanga nia daangada dogolua ala e huhuudada i nia maluagina o tangada: di kau, ‘donkey’, siibi, goloo gahu, be tei mee ne ngala, meemaa lahia gi di gowaa daumaha. Tangada dela ga hagiaga go God bolo e hala, le e hui holongo lua gi tangada dela i golo.
\p 
\v 10 “Maa tangada ga hiihai e benebene di manu a tangada: di ‘donkey’, kau, siibi, be di manu dela i golo, gei di manu deelaa la gaa made be ga lauwa be gaa kae go digau gaiaa, gei tangada ne gidee ai,
\v 11 tangada nogo benebene di manu le e hana gi di gowaa hai daumaha e hai dana hagamodu bolo ia digi gaiaa ina di manu. Maa di manu la digi gaiaa ina, tangada donu dana manu gii baba hua gi dana manu dela ne ngala, gei tangada nogo benebene di manu e hagalee hui gi mee.
\v 12 Maa di manu la ne gaiaa, taane dela le e hai loo gii hui gi tangada dana manu.
\v 13 Maa di manu la ne daaligi go nia manu lodo geinga, taane deelaa e gaamai nia mee ne dubu i di gili di manu e hai ai di hagadootonu; mee hagalee belee hui di mee dela ne daaligi go nia manu lodo geinga.
\p 
\v 14 “Maa tangada ga hai hegau gi di manu tuai dangada ga gaamai laa, gei di manu deelaa ga lauwa be gaa made gei tangada dana manu le hagalee i golo, taane ne begii di manu e hai loo gii hui di maa.
\v 15 Maa di mee deenei ne hai gei tangada dana manu la i golo, mee hagalee hui di maa. Maa di manu le e huihui e hai hegau ai nia daangada, malaa di hui dela ne gila mai di huihui gi daha di manu deelaa, le e hui di manu deelaa ma gaa made.
\s1 Nnaganoho daumaha mo nnaganoho o tenua
\p 
\v 16 “Maa taane ga halahalau dana ahina de iloo taane, gei digi hagababa gi dahi daane, gaa hai di hai be di manu gi di ahina deelaa, mee e hai loo gii hui gi di ahina deelaa di hui o di ahina, ga hai lodo laa gi mee.\x * \xo 22.16 \xt Deuteronomy 22.28-29\x*
\v 17 Maa tamana o di ahina le e de hiihai gi taane deelaa e lodo gi dana dama ahina, taane deelaa e hai gii hui gi tamana o di ahina di hulu hadu e tau ang gi di hui o di lodo gi tama ahina digi iloo ia taane.
\p 
\v 18 “Di ahina dela e hai ana buubuu le e daaligi gii made.\x * \xo 22.18 \xt Deuteronomy 18.10,11\x*
\p 
\v 19 “Daaligidia gii made taane dela e mouli taga hai lodo gi nia manu.\x * \xo 22.19 \xt Leviticus 18.23; 20.15-16; Deuteronomy 27.21\x*
\p 
\v 20 “Daaligidia gii made tangada dela e tigidaumaha gi di ingoo hua di god i daha mo Au go Dimaadua.\x * \xo 22.20 \xt Deuteronomy 17.2-7\x*
\p 
\v 21 “Hudee hagahuaidu ina, ge hudee hagaduadua ina digau tuadimee, goodou gi langahia di godou hai digau tuadimee i Egypt.\x * \xo 22.21 \xt Exodus 23.9; Leviticus 19.33-34; Deuteronomy 24.17-18; 27.19\x*
\v 22 Hudee heia hagahuaidu di ahina guu made dono lodo be di tama guu mmade ono maadua.
\v 23 Maa goodou gaa hai haga huaidu digaula, Au go Dimaadua ga hagalongo gi nia dangidangi digaula mai gi di Au i di hagamaamaa,
\v 24 gei Au ga hagawelewele ga daaligi goodou i lodo tauwa. Godou lodo ahina ga nadau lodo ai, godou dama ga nadau damana ai.
\p 
\v 25 “Maa goe gaa wanga au bahihadu e boibana go tangada i agu daangada ala hagaloale, goe hudee hai bolo mee gi gowadu gi di goe di wiini o ana bahihadu.\x * \xo 22.25 \xt Leviticus 25.35-38; Deuteronomy 15.7-11; 23.19-20\x*
\v 26 Maa goe gaa kae di gahu tangada e hai di hagamodongoohia o dono boibana adu gi di goe, goe e hai loo gi kae gi muli di gahu o maa gi mee i mua di ulu di laa,\x * \xo 22.26 \xt Deuteronomy 24.10-13\x*
\v 27 idimaa ma deelaa hua di gahu o maa e haga mahanahana ai. Ma di aha i golo e mee di haga mahanahana a mee? Di madagoaa a mee ma ga dangi mai i di hagamaamaa, Au e hagalongo gi tangidangi a maa idimaa Au e dumaalia.
\p 
\v 28 “Hudee helekai huaidu i God, hudee hagahuaidu ina di tagi o godou daangada.\x * \xo 22.28 \xt Acts 23.5\x*
\p 
\v 29 “Tigidaumaha ina mai gi di Au godou huwa laagau, godou waini, mo godou lolo olib i di madagoaa nia maa gu togomaalia.
\p “Gaamai gi di Au godou dama daane ulu mmaadua.
\v 30 Gaamai gi di Au di ulu madua o godou kau mo godou siibi. Dugu ang gi di ulu madua gii noho i baahi dono dinana i nia laangi e hidu, gei di walu laangi, tigidaumaha ina mai gi di Au.
\p 
\v 31 “Goodou go agu daangada, deenei laa goodou hudee geina loo nia goneiga o dahi manu ma ga daaligi go nia manu lodo geinga; malaa, wanga ina gi nia paana.\x * \xo 22.31 \xt Leviticus 17.15\x*
\c 23
\s1 Tonu mo di hagahumalia ngaadahi
\p 
\v 1 “Hudee hagadele ina nnelekai dilikai, hudee hagamaamaa ina tangada e hala gi di hai hegau gi nnelekai hagalee donu.\x * \xo 23.1 \xt Exodus 20.16; Leviticus 19.11-12; Deuteronomy 5.20\x*
\v 2 Hudee daudalia di baahi dogologo ma ga hai gee be e hai nadau helekai hai gee e hagahuaidu nia donu.
\v 3 Hudee hai baahi hala gi tangada hagaloale i lodo dono gabunga.\x * \xo 23.3 \xt Leviticus 19.15\x*
\p 
\v 4 “Maa goe ga gidee di kau be di manu ‘donkey’ o do hagadaumee e heehee i daha, lahia a mee gi muli gi tangada dana manu.\x * \xo 23.4 \xt Deuteronomy 22.1-4\x*
\v 5 Maa dana ‘donkey’ ga daamaha di kae ana mee gaa hinga, hagamaamaa ina di ‘donkey’ deelaa, hudee hana hua gi mua.
\p 
\v 6 “Hudee haga deiloo ina goe nia donu o tangada hagaloale i lodo di gabunga.\x * \xo 23.6 \xt Leviticus 19.15; Deuteronomy 16.19\x*
\v 7 Hudee dilikai hagahuaidu tangada, hudee wanga ina tangada ono hala ai gi di made, idimaa Au ga haga huaidu laa tangada dela e hai beenei.
\v 8 Hudee kaina bahihadu mai tangada dela belee hai goe gii hai di mee dela hagalee donu; idimaa di hai deenei e hai nia daangada gi de gidee di hai dela e donu, gei e hagahuaidu nia hai o digau humalia.
\p 
\v 9 “Hudee hagahuaidu ina tangada mai daha, goodou e iloo di manawa o tangada henua gee, idimaa, goodou nogo hai digau henua gee i Egypt.\x * \xo 23.9 \xt Exodus 22.21; Leviticus 19.33-34; Deuteronomy 24.17-18; 27.19\x*
\s1 Di hidu ngadau mo di hidu laangi
\p 
\v 10 “I lodo nia ngadau e ono, dogia dau gowaa ga hagabudu mai nia huwa huogodoo o dau gowaa.
\v 11 Gei di hidu ngadau, heia do henua gi hagamolooloo, hudee haadia nia mee ala e tomo i ono nua. Digau hagaloale gi miami i nia mee ala e tomo i golo, nia manu lodo geinga gaa kae nia mee ala e dubu. Heia labelaa beelaa gi dau hadagee waini mo au laagau olib.
\p 
\v 12 “Ngalua i nia laangi e ono i lodo di tabu e dahi, hudee ngalua i di hidu laangi, gei au hege mo au gau henua gee ala e ngalua adu mono manu hogi gaa mee di hagamolooloo.\x * \xo 23.12 \xt Exodus 20.9-11; 31.15; 34.21; 35.2; Leviticus 23.3; Deuteronomy 5.13-14\x*
\p 
\v 13 “Au go Dimaadua, hagalongo gi nia mee huogodoo ala e helekai iei Au adu gi goodou. Hudee dalodalo gi nia balu ieidu, hudee gahigahia nadau ingoo.
\s1 Nia laangi llauehe e dolu
\r (Exodus 34.18-26; Deuteronomy 16.1-17)
\p 
\v 14 “Budu ina nia laangi llauehe e dolu i lodo di ngadau e dahi e hagalaamua Au.
\v 15 I lodo di malama Abib dela ne hagatanga goodou i Egypt, budu ina Tagamiami o di Palaawaa Digi Hagatanga be dagu hai ne hagi adu gi goodou. Hudee geina di palaawaa gu hagatanga gi nia ‘yeast’ i lodo nia laangi e hidu o tagamiami deenei.
\p “Hudee hanimoi e daumaha mai gi di Au maa goe digi gaamai dau tigidaumaha.\x * \xo 23.15 \xt Exodus 12.14-20; Leviticus 23.6-8; Numbers 28.17-25\x*
\p 
\v 16 “Budu ina Tagamiami o di Hadi nia Huwa Laagau i di godou madagoaa ma ga daamada gaa hadi godou huwa laagau.\x * \xo 23.16 \xt Leviticus 23.15-21; 23.39-43; Numbers 28.26-31\x*
\p “Nia hagaodi o nia ngadau, budu ina nia laangi o Tagamiami o nia Damaa hale Hagaabili i di godou madagoaa ma ga hagabudu nia huwa laagau mai godou hadagee waini mo godou huwa laagau ala i golo.
\v 17 Nia ngadau huogodoo, nia daane huogodoo e hai loo gi lloomoi e daumaha mai gi di Au, go Dimaadua go di godou God, i nia laangi llauehe e dolu aanei.
\p 
\v 18 “Hudee hai hegau gi nia palaawaa gu hagatanga i di godou madagoaa ga tigidaumaha dahi manu mai gi di Au. Nia kiliidi o nia manu ne tigidaumaha mai gi di Au i lodo nia laangi llauehe e hagalee hai gii dae gi di luada dono daiaa.
\p 
\v 19 “Nia ngadau dagidahi huogodoo, goodou gaamai gi di hale o Dimaadua go di godou God, nia huwa laagau ala ma gaa hadi go goodou matagidagi.\x * \xo 23.19 \xt Exodus 34.26; Deuteronomy 14.21; 26.2\x*
\p “Hudee dunu ina tama siibi be tamaa kuudi i lodo nia weuu o dono dinana.
\s1 Nia hagababa mo nnelekai hagamaamaa
\p 
\v 20 “Au ga hagau dagu dangada di langi i godou mua e madamada humalia i goodou i di godou hula, mo e lahi goodou gi di gowaa ne hagatogomaalia ko Au.
\v 21 Hagalongo gi mee mo di daudali ana helekai. Goodou hudee hai baahi gi mee, idimaa mee ne hagau adu ko Au, gei mee e hagalee dumaalia gi godou de hagalongo.
\v 22 Maa goodou ga hagalongo gi mee, gaa hai nia mee huogodoo ala ne helekai iei Au, Au ga heebagi gi godou hagadaumee huogodoo.
\v 23 Dagu dangada di langi gaa hana i godou mua, gaa lahi goodou gi tenua digau Amor, Hittite, Perizzite, Canaan, Hivite mo Jebus, gei Au ga daaligi digaula.
\v 24 Hudee pala ang gi nadau god, hudee daumaha gi nia maa, hudee hai mee gi nadau hai daumaha. Ohaa ina nia god digaula, ohaa ina nia waduu hadugalaa hagamadagu digaula.
\v 25 Maa goodou ga daumaha mai gi di Au, go Dimaadua di godou God, Au ga hagahumalia goodou gi nia meegai mono wai, gei Au ga daa gi daha godou magi huogodoo.
\v 26 I lodo di godou henua, ga deai di ahina e made dana dama i lodo dono dinae ai, ge deai di ahina dana dama ai. Au ga gowadu gi goodou di mouli waalooloo.
\p 
\v 27 “Au gaa hai nia daangada ala e hai baahi adu gi goodou gi mmaadagu i di Au. Au ga hagahinihini nia daangada ala e heebagi adu, gaa hai digaula gii huli ge gii llele gi daha mo goodou.
\v 28 Au gaa hai godou hagadaumee gii llele gi daha mo di mmaadagu huoloo, Au ga hagabagi digau Hivite, Canaan, mo digau Hittite gi daha mo godou mua.
\v 29 Au e hagalee hagabagi digaula i lodo di ngadau e dahi. Maa nei bolo Au gaa hai beelaa, gei nia henua ga ono daangada ai, gei nia manu lodo geinga gaa logo balua adu gi goodou.
\v 30 Au e hagabagibagi digaula dagi hogoohi, gaa dae loo gi di godou dohu di noho i hongo nnenua.
\v 31 Au gaa hai taalinga di godou gowaa gi daamada i di Malua o Aqaba, gaa hana gi di tai o Mediterranean, ge mai di anggowaa gaa hana gi di monowai Euphrates. Au ga gowadu di mogobuna i hongo nia daangada o tenua, gei goodou e mee di hagabagi digaula i di godou llooadu.
\v 32 Hudee hai hagababa gi digaula be gi nadau god.
\v 33 Hudee heia digaula gii noho i lodo godou henua. Maa goodou gaa hai beelaa, digaula gaa hai goodou gii hala mai gi di Au. Maa goodou ga daumaha gi nadau god, deelaa la di hele huaidu adu gi goodou.”
\c 24
\s1 Di haga mogobuna o di hagababa
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hanaga gi di Au i hongo di gonduu, goodou mo Aaron, Nadab, Abihu mo nia dagi o Israel e mada hidu, lloo aga gi mada tanga, ga daumaha mai gi di Au.
\v 2 Kooe hua modogoe dela e hanaga gi hoohoo mai gi di Au, gei digau ala i golo, hudee lloo aga gi hongo di gonduu deenei.”
\p 
\v 3 Moses guu hana gu hagi anga gi digaula nia helekai mono haganoho a Dimaadua ne hai ang gi deia, gei nia daangada guu hai huogodoo di nadau kai hua e dahi boloo, “Gimaadou ga hagakila nia haganoho huogodoo a Dimaadua ala gu helekai ai.”
\v 4 Moses gaa hihi gi lala nnelekai huogodoo a Dimaadua.
\p Hagaluada loo dono daiaa, gei mee ga haga duu dana gowaa dudu tigidaumaha i tono di gonduu deelaa, ga haga noho ana hadu e madangaholu maa lua i di gowaa deelaa, e pono nia madawaawa Israel e madangaholu maa lua.
\v 5 Geia ga hagau ana dama daane, e dudu nadau mee e tigidaumaha gi Dimaadua, ge e daaligi nia kau daane lligi be nnangaahai o tigidaumaha hagadaubuni.
\v 6 Moses ga haga hau dahi baahi e lua o nia dodo o nia manu aalaa gi lodo nia baisin, gei di baahi dela i golo gaa dui go mee gi hongo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha deelaa.
\v 7 Nomuli gei mee ga dahi aga di Beebaa Haganoho gaa dau gi digau dogologo aalaa, gei digaula ga helekai, “Uaa, gimaadou ga hai hegau gi nia haganoho huogodoo ala guu hai go Dimaadua.”
\v 8 Moses guu kae nia dodo ala nogo i lodo nia baisin ga hagatulutulu digaula gi nia maa ga helekai, “Aanei nia dodo ala e hagamodongoohia bolo di hagababa le e donu, dela ne hai adu go Dimaadua i dana gowadu nia haganoho huogodoo aanei gi goodou.”\x * \xo 24.8 \xt Matthew 26.28; Mark 14.24; Luke 22.20; 1-Corinthians 11.25; Hebrews 9.19-20; 10.29\x*
\p 
\v 9 Moses, Aaron, Nadab, Abihu mo nia dagi e mada hidu o digau Israel ga kaga aga i di gonduu,
\v 10 gei digaula gu gidee ginaadou di God o Israel. Lala nia babaawae o Maa e hai gadoo be di ala hadu dela ne hai gi nia hadu hagalabagau go nia ‘sapphire’, e halatee be di langi malamalama.
\v 11 God digi hagahuaidu ina nia dagi o Israel aalaa. Digaula ne mmada gi God, gei nomuli ga miami ngaadahi.
\s1 Moses i hongo di Gonduu Sinai
\p 
\v 12 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hanaga gi di Au i hongo di gonduu deenei. Au ga gowadu agu baahi hadu e lua ala guu hihi ginai agu haganoho e aago kooe ang gi nia daangada.”
\v 13 Moses ga hagatogomaalia ia mo dono dangada hagamaamaa go Joshua, gei Moses gaa hana gi hongo di gonduu haga madagu a God.
\v 14 Moses ga helekai gi nia dagi aalaa, “Goodou daalia i ginei, gaa dae loo gi di madagoaa dela ga lloomoi ai gimaua. Aaron mo Hur gaa noho goodou, maa iai tangada e hai dana mee haingadaa, geia gii hana gi meemaa.”
\p 
\v 15 Moses gaa hana gi hongo di Gonduu Sinai, gei di gonduu la guu gahu go di gololangi.
\v 16 Di maahina o Dimaadua gu i hongo di Gonduu Sinai, gei di gonduu le e gahu hua go di gololangi i lodo nia laangi e ono, gei di hidu laangi, gei Dimaadua ga gahigahi a Moses mai i lodo di gololangi.
\v 17 Di maahina o Dimaadua le e hai gadoo be di ahi e ulaula e wele i tomo di gonduu deelaa ang gi digau Israel.
\v 18 Malaa, Moses ne hana hua gi lodo di gololangi i tomo di gonduu. Mee ne noho i golo nia laangi e mada haa, ge mada haa boo.\x * \xo 24.18 \xt Deuteronomy 9.9\x*
\c 25
\s1 Wanga dehuia gi di Hale laa Dimaadua
\r (Exodus 35.4-9)
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses,
\v 2 “Helekai gi digau Israel gi heia di tigidaumaha mai gi di Au. Gumidia di ingoo hua tigidaumaha dela gu hagamaanadu go tangada belee tigidaumaha ai.
\v 3 Nia tigidaumaha aanei la nia goolo, silber mo nia baalanga mmee;
\v 4 nia gahu linen humalia nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee; nia gahu ne hai gi nia ngaahulu kuudi;
\v 5 nia gili siibi daane guu hunu gii mmee, nia gili kau, nia laagau ‘acacia’.
\v 6 Nia lolo ang gi nia malama, nia mee hagakala nia lolo hagatulu mo e hagakala di hauiha gii kala;
\v 7 nia hadu hagalabagau ‘onyx’ mono hadu hagamadamada ala i golo, nia mee e humu di ‘ephod’ \f + \fr 25.7 \fk ‘ephod’ \ft di gahu bodobodo e ulu i nia bakau ma gaa hai ana hegau dabu e halahala ai di manawa Dimaadua\f* ge e humu di mee gahu hadahada di tagi aamua hai mee dabu.
\v 8 Nia daangada e hai loo gii hau di hale laa dabu mai gi di Au, gii mee Au di noho i nadau baahi.
\v 9 Hau hia di maa mono goloo di hale gii hai gadoo be dagu bilaan dela ga hagi adu gi di goe.
\s1 Tebedebe o di Hagababa Dimaadua
\r (Exodus 37.1-9)
\p 
\v 10 “Hauhia tebedebe gi di laagau ‘acacia’, nia ‘inch’ 45 di looloo, 27 ‘inch’ palaha, 27 ‘inch’ tuuduu gi nua.
\v 11 Hii ina gi nia goolo madammaa i lodo mo i tua, heia dono daalinga gi nia goolo e haganiga di maa.
\v 12 Heia nia buulei dagidagi goolo e haa e dagidagi di maa, hauhia gi nia wae e haa, nia buulei e lua i di baahi e dahi.
\v 13 Heia nia laagau e aamo di maa gi nia laagau ‘acacia’, gaa hii nia maa gi nia goolo,
\v 14 ga daalo nia maa gi lodo nia buulei i nia baahi dagidahi o Tebedebe.
\v 15 Nia laagau e dugu hua i lodo nia buulei e hagalee daa gi daha.
\v 16 Wanga ina gi lodo tebedebe nia hadu e lua guu hihi ginai nia haganoho nonua ala ga gowadu ko Au.
\p 
\v 17 “Heia di uhi gi nia goolo madammaa, 45 ‘inch’ looloo, 37 ‘inch’ palaha.\x * \xo 25.17 \xt Hebrews 9.5\x*
\v 18 Heia nia manu goolo e lua e hai nau bakau.
\v 19 e dahi ang gi di bida e dahi o di uhi. Heia nia manu gi buni anga gi di uhi, gii hai be di mee e dahi.
\v 20 Nia manu nau bakau le e huli mai nau hadumada gi lodo i hongo di uhi, gei nau bakau moholo le e gahu di uhi.
\v 21 Wanga ina nia hadu e lua gi lodo tebedebe, pono ina di uhi gi ono nua.
\v 22 Au ga heetugi adu gi di goe i golo, gei Au ga gowadu agu haganoho huogodoo ang gi digau Israel mai i hongo di uhi i mehanga nia manu e lua.
\s1 Teebele di palaawaa tigidaumaha gi God
\r (Exodus 37.10-16)
\p 
\v 23 “Heia teebele gi nia laagau ‘acacia’, 36 ‘inch’ looloo, 18 ‘inch’ palaha, ge 27 ‘inch’ tuuduu gi nua.
\v 24 Hii ina di maa gi nia goolo madammaa, heia dono daalinga gi nia goolo e haganiga di maa.
\v 25 Heia dono daalinga nia ‘inch’ e 3 palaha mo dono hagageinga goolo i tua taalinga.
\v 26 Heia nia buulei goolo e haa e dagidagi di maa, hagamau ina nia maa gi nia madaaduge e haa gi nia wae.
\v 27 Nia buulei ala e daahi nia laagau aamo teebele le e dugu hoohoo gi taalinga di haganiga.
\v 28 Heia nia laagau aamo gi nia laagau ‘acacia’ e hii gi nia goolo.
\v 29 Heia nia pileedi, nia ibu, ibu mangalloo, mo nia boolo ang gi nia waini tigidaumaha. Nia mee aanei e hai huogodoo gi nia goolo madammaa.
\v 30 Teebele le e dugu i mua Tebedebe di Hagababa, gei i hongo teebele e dugu di palaawaa i nia madagoaa huogodoo e tigidaumaha mai gi di Au.\x * \xo 25.30 \xt Leviticus 24.5-8\x*
\s1 Di Lohongo Malama
\r (Exodus 37.17-24)
\p 
\v 31 “Heia di Lohongo Malama gi nia goolo madammaa. Di tono mo tuaidina di Lohongo Malama le e hai gi nia goolo ne tugi. Ono akai humu mo nia lau o nia akai le e hau gii hai di mee e dahi gi di Lohongo Malama.
\v 32 Nia manga e ono le e tolo gi daha, e dolu i di baahi e dahi, ge e dolu i di baahi i golo.
\v 33 Nia manga e ono aalaa, e hai ono akai humu dagi dolu, dono ada e hai be di akai ‘almond’ ma ga moholoholo.
\v 34 Tuaidina o di Lohongo Malama le e hai ono akai humu e haa, dono ada e hai be di akai ‘almond’ ma ga moholoholo.
\v 35 I baahi lala nia manga dagi dolu heia di akai e daamada e moholoholo.
\v 36 Nia akai e daamada e moholoholo, nia manga mo tuaidina di Lohongo Malama, e dugidugi gii hai be di mee e dahi ne hau haga dahi gi nia goolo madammaa.
\v 37 Heia nia malama e hidu ang gi di Lohongo Malama, ga hai nia maa gi maahina gi mua.
\v 38 Heia nia mee gumigumi mono mee dugu ahi gi nia goolo madammaa.
\v 39 Hai hegau gi nia pauna goolo madammaa 75 e hai di Lohongo Malama mono mee ala i golo huogodoo.
\v 40 Heia nia maa gii hai be dagu hagatau ne hagi adu i hongo di gonduu.\x * \xo 25.40 \xt Acts 7.44; Hebrews 8.5\x*
\c 26
\s1 Di Hale laa Dimaadua
\r (Exodus 36.8-38)
\p 
\v 1 “Heia di Hale laa Koia e Dabuaahia gi nia bida gahu linen e madangaholu e dui gi nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee. Humu ina nia maa gi nia ada duain o nia manu ono bakau.
\v 2 Nia bida gahu e hai gi tongaadahi 14 ‘yard’ looloo, ge 2 ‘yard’ palaha.
\v 3 Duia nia bida gahu e lima gi di gunga gahu e dahi, heia labelaa beelaa gi nia gahu e lima ala i golo.
\v 4 Heia nia ada haganiga gi nia bida gahu halatee i taalinga di tua o nia gunga gahu aalaa.
\v 5 Dugu ina nia ada haganiga e madalima i taalinga di gahu matagidagi o nia gahu ala ne hagapuni matagidagi, ge mada lima ada haganiga i taalinga di gahu hagamuliagina o di gunga gahu dela i golo.
\v 6 Heia nia maadau goolo e 50 e hagapuni nia gunga gahu e lua gii hai di gahu e dahi.
\p 
\v 7 “Heia di gahu di Hale laa gi nia bida gahu e 11 ala ne hai gi nia ngaahulu kuudi.
\v 8 Heia nia maa gi tongaadahi, 15 ‘yard’ looloo, 2 ‘yard’ di palaha.
\v 9 Duia nia gahu e lima o nia maa gii hai di gunga gahu e dahi, ge ono e hai tuai gunga gahu. Haduu ina hagalua di ono baahi mee holongo lua i mua di Hale laa.
\v 10 Hagabongo ina nia lohongo buulei e 50 i taalinga di gunga gahu muliagi, ge 50 lohongo buulei e haganiga i taalinga di hoo di maa.
\v 11 Heia nia maadau baalanga mmee e 50, ga daalo nia maa gi lodo nia bongoo buulei e duudagi nia gunga gahu e lua e hai di uhi e dahi.
\v 12 Daudau ina di baahi mee ne dubu gi hongo di tua di Hale laa.
\v 13 Di baahi ‘yard’ o di gahu dela e dubu i nia baahi e lua le e daudau i nia baahi di Hale laa e gahu di maa hagatau.
\p 
\v 14 “Heia nia gahu labelaa e lua, e dahi e hai gi nia gili siibi daane gu haga mmee, gei i hongo di maa la di hoo di maa ne hai gi nia gili kau humalia, e daudau gi nua i taalinga di Hale laa e gahu di maa.
\p 
\v 15 “Heia nia waduu o di Hale laa gi nia laagau ‘acacia’.
\v 16 Di laagau waduu e dahi e 15 piidi looloo, ge 27 ‘inch’ palaha.
\v 17 Nia waduu e lua e hagalloo ono bida gi daha gii mee di duudagi nia maa, gii hai be di mee e dahi. Nia waduu huogodoo e hai ono duudagi beenei.
\v 18 Heia nia waduu e madalua gi di baahi ngeia,
\v 19 e haaligi no lala gi nia silber e madahaa, nia haaligi i lala di waduu e dahi e daahi nia baahi e lua ala ne hagalloo.
\v 20 Heia nia waduu e 20 gi di baahi ngaaga o di Hale laa,
\v 21 ge nia haaligi silber e 40, e lua haaligi i lala di waduu e dahi.
\v 22 Heia nia waduu e ono gi tua di Hale laa dela i bahi i dai di maa,
\v 23 mo nia waduu e lua ang gi nia madaaduge e lua i baahi i tua.
\v 24 Nia waduu o nia madaaduge e duudagi i baahi lala gaa hana gaa tugi gi tahuhu. Nia waduu e lua ala e hai nia madaaduge e lua e hai gii hai beenei.
\v 25 Huogodoo ga iai nia waduu e 8, ono haaligi silber e 16, e lua e haaligi di waduu e dahi.
\p 
\v 26 “Heia nia giodo laagau ‘acacia’ e 15, e lima ang gi nia waduu i di baahi e dahi di Hale laa,
\v 27 e lima ang gi nia waduu i di baahi dela i golo, ge e lima gi nia waduu i baahi dai, dela i tua di Hale laa.
\v 28 Di giodo tungaalodo e dugu i baahi di waduu e duudagi nia bida di Hale laa.
\v 29 Hii ina nia waduu gi nia goolo e hai labelaa nadau buulei goolo e daahi nia giodo laagau ala e hii labelaa gi nia goolo.
\v 30 Hagaduu ina di Hale laa be dagu bilaan ne hagi adu i hongo di gonduu.
\p 
\v 31 “Heia di gahu linen duuli humalia halatee, e dui gi nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo e mmee. Humu ina nia maa gi nia ada manu nadau bakau.
\v 32 Daudaulia gi nia waduu ‘acacia’ e haa e hii gi nia goolo, guu hau gi nia maadau, gu haganoho i hongo nia haaligi silber e haa.
\v 33 Dugu ina di gahu duuli gi lala di goolongo maadau i hongo tuatala di Hale laa, dugu ina Tebedebe di Hagababa dela e haa nia hadu e lua i tua di gahu duuli. Di gahu duuli e wwae di Gowaa Dabu mo di Gowaa Dabuaahia Huoloo.
\v 34 Dugu ina di uhi gi hongo Tebedebe di Hagababa.
\v 35 I tua di Gowaa Dabuaahia Huoloo, dugua teebele i baahi ngeia di Hale laa, gei di lohongo malama i baahi ngaaga.
\p 
\v 36 “Di gowaa dela e ulu gi lodo di Hale laa, dugua di gahu duuli dela e dui gi nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, ge guu humu gi nia duain.
\v 37 Ang gi di gahu duuli deenei, heia nia waduu ‘acacia’ laagau e lima e hii gi nia goolo, e hagapuni ginai nia maadau goolo. Heia nia lohongo waduu baalanga mmee e lima.
\c 27
\s1 Di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha
\r (Exodus 38.1-7)
\p 
\v 1 “Heia di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha gi di laagau ‘acacia’, gi looloo nia piidi e hidu mo di baahi, ge palaha nia piidi e hidu mo di baahi, ge duuduu i nua nia piidi e haa mo di baahi.
\v 2 Heia nia madaagoo gi nua i nia madaaduge e haa. Nia maa e hau hua gi di laagau e dahi mo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha, e hii hagatau gi di baalanga mmee.
\v 3 Heia nia baalanga dunu meegai ang gi nia luaahi kiliidi, heia nia daawolo, nia boolo, nia poogi, mo nia mee dugu ahi. Nia goloo huogodoo aanei le e hai gi nia baalanga mmee.
\v 4 Hagataulia nia amu e hai di hada baalanga mmee, wanga ina nia buulei baalanga mmee e haa i nia madaaduge e haa.
\v 5 Hagaulu ina di hada gii tugi gii duu lua i baahi gi lala taalinga di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha.
\v 6 Heia nia laagau aamo mee gi nia laagau ‘acacia’, hii ina nia maa gi nia baalanga mmee.
\v 7 Daalo ina nia maa gi lodo nia buulei ala i nia baahi, i di madagoaa di maa ga aamo.
\v 8 Heia di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha gi nia laubaba, heia di maa gi bongoo laa lodo gii hai be dagu bilaan ne hagi adu i hongo di gonduu.
\s1 Di abaaba e duuli di Hale laa Dimaadua
\r (Exodus 38.9-20)
\p 
\v 9 “Heia di abaaba e duuli di Hale laa dela e noho iei Au, gahudia gi nia gahu duuli lenge humalia. I di baahi gi ngaaga di Hale laa, nia gahu duuli le e hai gii lloo nia ‘yard’ e 50,
\v 10 e daahi go nia duludulu baalanga mmee e 20 ala e haganoho gi lodo nadau lohongo duludulu baalanga mmee e 20, dalia nia maadau mono amu daahi ne hai gi nia silber.
\v 11 Heia di hai la hua gi di baahi gi ngeia.
\v 12 I di baahi gi dai, nia gahu duuli e looloo nia ‘yard’ e 25, ono waduu e 10 ge 10 lohongo waduu.
\v 13 I di baahi gi dua, i di gowaa dela iai di bontai, di abaaba e hai labelaa nia ‘yard’ e 25.
\v 14-15 I nia baahi e lua o di bontai, nia ‘yard’ e hidu mo di baahi o di gahu duuli, e daahi go nia waduu e dolu mo nadau lohongo waduu e dolu.
\v 16 Ang gi di bontai, llanga ina di gahu habuihabula duuli e looloo nia ‘yard’ e 10 ne dui gi nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, ge guu humu gi nia duain. Tuuli deenei e daudau gi nia waduu e haa ala e tuu i hongo nia lohongo waduu e haa.
\v 17 Nia waduu huogodoo e haganiga di malae e hai gi duudagi ang gi nia amu silber mo nadau lohongo waduu baalanga mmee.
\v 18 Di abaaba e duuli di Hale laa le e looloo nia ‘yard’ e 50, 25 ‘yard’ palaha, ge lua mo di baahi ‘yard’ tuuduu i nua. Nia gahu duuli le e hai gi nia gahu humalia, ge dono baba e hai gi nia baalanga mmee.
\v 19 Nia goloo huogodoo nogo hai hegau i lodo di Hale laa mo nia daula di Hale laa mo nia daula o di abaaba le e hai gi nia baalanga mmee.
\s1 Benebene di malama
\r (Leviticus 24.1-4)
\p 
\v 20 “Helekai gi digau Israel gi gaamai nia lolo humalia gii mee di dudu di malama i nia hiahi huogodoo.
\v 21 Aaron mo ana dama e haganoho di malama i lodo dogu Hale laa i tua di gahu duuli dela i mua Tebedebe di Hagababa. Di malama e hai gi ulaula i ogu mua mai di hiahi gaa tugi di luada. Telekai deenei e daahi go digau Israel mo nadau hagadili gaa hana hua beelaa.
\c 28
\s1 Nia gahu digau hai mee dabu
\r (Exodus 39.1-7)
\p 
\v 1 “Gahia mai do duaahina Aaron mo ana dama daane: Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar mo Ithamar. Dugua digaula gi daha mo digau Israel ala i golo, e hai hegau mai be digau hai mee dabu.
\v 2 Duia nia gahu dangada hai mee dabu o do duaahina Aaron e hagamadagu ge e haga madamada a mee.
\v 3 Gahia mai digau ngalua huogodoo ala ne wanga ginai ogu iloo di ngalua, helekai gi digaula gi heia nia gahu Aaron gii mee ai di hagadabu a mee e hai agu hegau dabu.
\v 4 Helekai gi digaula gi heia di mee gahu hadahada, di gahu ‘ephod’, di gahu looloo, di gahu uluulu guu humu gi nia duain, di gahu ‘turban’, mo di tuu nnoo gahu. Digaula e hai gii hai nia gahu o Aaron mo ana dama daane, gii mee ai digaula di hai hegau mai be digau hai mee dabu.
\v 5 Digau ngalua aanei e hai hegau gi nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee ge gu hagahabuihabula,
\p 
\v 6 “Digaula gi heia di ‘ephod’ gi nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, nia duain goolo mo nia linen hagahumalia, ge guu humu gi nia duain.
\v 7 Nia tuu hagamau daudau i nia bakau e lua e wanga gi nia baahi o di gahu.
\v 8 Di tuu guu llanga hagalligi gi humalia e hagapuni gi di ‘ephod’, gii hai di mee e dahi.
\v 9 Hihia nia ingoo nia dama dilongoholu maa lua Jacob i hongo nia hadu ‘onyx’ e lua,
\v 10 e hagatau gi nadau mmaadua, e ono e hihi gi hongo di hadu e dahi, ge e ono e hihi i hongo di hadu dela i golo.
\v 11 Wanga ina gi tangada e iloo di ngalua gi nia hadu hagalabagau gi hihia nia ingoo nia dama Jacob gi hongo nia hadu e lua, hagataulia nia hadu gi nia goolo.
\v 12 Dugua nia maa gi hongo nia hagamau ‘ephod’ e pono nia madawaawa e 12 o Israel. Deenei di hai gei Aaron gaa mee di dagidagi nadau ingoo i hongo ono bakau, gei Au go Dimaadua ga mamaanadu agu daangada i nia madagoaa huogodoo.
\v 13 Heia nia lohongo goolo e lua,
\v 14 gei nia daula baalanga goolo madammaa e lua e hai be nia loahi ga hagapuni nia maa gii hai be di mee e dahi.
\s1 Di mee gahu hadahada
\r (Exodus 39.8-21)
\p 
\v 15 “Heia di mee gahu hadahada gi di tagi aamua hai mee dabu e hai hegau ai e halahala di hiihai a God. Di gahu deenei e hai hua gi nia mee ala ne hai di ‘ephod’, e humu gi nia duain be di maa.
\v 16 Di hagatau o di mee deenei e hai ono madaaduge be di mee e dahi, ge hadui hagalua; dono palaha mo dono looloo e 9 ‘inch’.
\v 17 Hagataulia nia goolongo hadu hagalabagau e haa gi hongo di maa. Di goolongo matagidagi, hagataulia gi nia ‘ruby’, ‘topaz’ mo di ‘garnet’.
\v 18 Di lua goolongo, hagataulia nia ‘emerald’, ‘sapphire’, mo di ‘diamond’.
\v 19 Togodolu goolongo, hagataulia nia ‘turquoise’, ‘agate’, mo di ‘amethyst’.
\v 20 Togohaa goolongo, hagataulia nia ‘beryl’, ‘onyx’, mo di ‘jasper’. Nia mee aanei e haganoho gi nia goolo.
\v 21 Nia hadu dagidahi e 12 aanei la gi hihia ginai nia ingoo nia dama daane Jacob, e pono nia madawaawa e 12 Israel.
\v 22 Di mee gahu hadahada e hai ono daula goolo madammaa, e bini be di loahi.
\v 23 Heia nia buulei goolo e lua ga daudau gi nia madaaduge bahi i nua o di mee gahu hadahada.
\v 24 Nnoodia nia uga goolo e lua gi nia buulei e lua aalaa.
\v 25 Hagapigi ina nia mada e lua o di loahi ang gi di gahu hadahada e hagamau di maa i mua di hagapuni gi di ‘ephod’.
\v 26 Heia nia buulei goolo e lua, hagapigi ina gi nia madaaduge baahi lala o di mee gahu hadahada i taalinga baahi gi lodo i baahi e tale gi di ‘ephod’.
\v 27 Heia labelaa nia buulei goolo e lua, ga hagapigi gi baahi lala i mua nia daulagi bakau e lua o di ‘ephod’, hoohoo gi tuudagi, ge baahi nua di tuu guu llanga hagalligi gi humalia.
\v 28 Nnoodia nia buulei o di mee gahu hadahada gi nia buulei di ‘ephod’ gi di uga halatee, ge di mee gahu hadahada gii noho i baahi nua di tuu, ge hagalee mehede.
\p 
\v 29 “Di madagoaa Aaron ma ga ulu gi lodo di Gowaa Dabu, mee ga ulu di mee gahu hadahada guu hihi ginai nia ingoo o nia madawaawa Israel, gei Au, go Dimaadua, ga langahia agu daangada i nia madagoaa huogodoo.
\v 30 Dugua nia hadu hagalabagau ‘Urim’ mo ‘Thummim’\f + \fr 28.30 \fk ‘Urim’ mo ‘Thummim’: \ft Aanei la nia mee ala ne hai hegau ai tangada hai mee dabu belee iloo ai di manawa o God. Gidaadou e de iloo hagahumalia be ne hai hegau behee. \f* gi lodo di mee gahu hadahada, gii mee Aaron di kae nia maa i di madagoaa a mee ga ulu gi lodo dogu gowaa dabuaahia. I di madagoaa deelaa, mee e hai loo gi ulu di mee gahu hadahada deenei i nia madagoaa huogodoo, gii mee a mee di iloo dogu hiihai ang gi nia daangada Israel.
\s1 Nia gahu digau hai mee dabu ala i golo
\r (Exodus 39.22-31)
\p 
\v 31 “Di gahu looloo dela e ulu gi baahi gi lodo di ‘ephod’ le e hai gi di gahu halatee.
\v 32 E hai gii hai dono bongoo ang gi di libogo; di bongoo deenei le e dui gi nia gahu llanga maadolu e duuli di maa gi hagalee mahaa.
\v 33-34 Heia taalinga di gahu gi lala hagatau nia ada ‘pomegranate’ ne hai gi nia gahu gili siibi humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, e wanga hagadau gi nia beele goolo i nadau mehanga.
\v 35 Aaron la gi ulu di gahu ‘robe’ deenei ma gaa hai ana hegau be tangada hai mee dabu. Mee ma ga hanimoi gi ogu mua i lodo di Gowaa Dabu be dono hagatanga gi daha, di beele e tangi gei mee ga hagalee daaligi gii made.
\p 
\v 36 “Heia di mee humu mee gi madamada gi nia goolo madammaa, maaga ina di maa gi ono nua ‘Hagadabu ang gi Dimaadua’.
\v 37 Nnoo ina di maa gi di loahi halatee gi mua di gahu libogo.
\v 38 Aaron e hai gi ulu di maa i hongo dono libogo, gei Au go Dimaadua gaa kumi nia tigidaumaha huogodoo digau Israel ma ga hai mai gi di Au, eimaha hogi maa digaula gu ihala i di hai tigidaumaha.
\p 
\v 39 “Heia di gahu Aaron gi humalia, heia di goobai ‘turban’ gi di gahu humalia, mo di tuu nnoo gahu e humu gi nia duain.
\p 
\v 40 “Heia nia gahu, nia tuu nnoo gahu, mono goobai ang gi nia dama daane Aaron e hagalaamua mo di hagamadamada digaula.
\v 41 Dugua nia gahu aanei gi hongo do duaahina go Aaron mo ana dama daane. Hagatulu ina digaula gi nia lolo laagau olib ga hagamenege aga digaula e hai agu gau hai mee dabu.
\v 42 Heia nadau bida gahu wae e ulu digaula, e hai gi tugi nadau duli, gi dee gila mai nadau huaidina.
\v 43 Aaron mo ana dama e hai gi ulu nia gahu aanei i nia madagoaa huogodoo ma gaa hula gi lodo di Hale laa e noho iei Au, be gi di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha e hai nadau hegau i lodo di Gowaa Dabu, gi de daaligi digaula gii mmade i di nadau hagakila mai nadau huaidina. Deenei la taganoho e noho mau ang gi Aaron mo ono hagadili.
\c 29
\s1 Nnelekai e hagadabu Aaron mo ana dama gii hai digau hai mee dabu
\r (Leviticus 8.1-36)
\p 
\v 1 “Deenei dau hai e hai gi Aaron mo ana dama gii hai digau hai mee dabu e hai hegau mai gi di Au. Kaina tamaa kau daane e dahi ge lua dama siibi daane ala e humalia ge madammaa.
\v 2 Hai hegau gi nia palaawaa kaedahi humalia, hagalee wanga ginai nia ‘yeast’, heia hunu palaawaa gi nia lolo olib, hunu palaawaa hagalee hai gi nia lolo olib, hunu maa heia nia bagu lahilahi e hunu gi nia lolo olib.
\v 3 Haawa ina nia maa gi lodo di gada ga gaamai e tigidaumaha dalia tigidaumaha di kau daane mo nia siibi daane e lua.
\p 
\v 4 “Laha mai Aaron mo ana dama gi di bontai o dogu Hale laa, gaugaulia digaula gi madammaa.
\v 5 Haga ulu ina Aaron gi ono gahu hai mee dabu; di gahu, di gahu looloo dela e hana gi baahi i lala di ‘ephod’, mo di ‘ephod’, di mee gahu hadahada, mo di tuu.
\v 6 Gahu ina a mee gi di gahu libogo, gaa nnoo gi di maa di ada hagailoo dabu hagalangahia, e maaga boloo ‘Hagadabu ang gi Dimaadua.’
\v 7 Nomuli gaa kae di lolo hagatulu, gaa dui gi hongo di libogo o maa, ga hagatulu a mee.
\p 
\v 8 “Laha mai nia dama a maa, ga hagaulu gi nia gahu.
\v 9 Heia nadau tuu nnoo gahu i nadau huaidina mo nnoodia nia goobai i hongo nadau libogo. Deenei di hai e hagadabu Aaron mo ana dama daane. Digaula mo nadau hagadili e hai digau hai mee dabu gaa hana hua beelaa.
\p 
\v 10 “Gaamai di kau daane gi mua dogu Hale laa, hai gi Aaron mo ana dama daane gi dugua nadau lima gi hongo di libogo di maa.
\v 11 Daaligidia di manu deelaa i ogu mua i di bontai di Hale laa.
\v 12 Hagatiu ina do madaalima gi nia dodo o di kau, gaa wanga gi nia madaagoo gi nua i nia madaaduge di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha, gaa dui nia dodo ala e dubu gi taalinga tono di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha.
\v 13 Nomuli, kaina nia kiliidi huogodoo ala e gahu nia manga o lodo tuaidina, di baahi dela e humalia huoloo i di ade, mo nia ‘kidney’ e lua mo nadau kiliidi, duduina nia maa i hongo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha e tigidaumaha mai gi di Au.
\v 14 Gei nia goneiga o di kau deelaa, mo dono gili, mo dono geiga duungia i tua di waahale laa e noho ai digaula. Deenei tigidaumaha dela e wwede nia hala o digau hai mee dabu.
\p 
\v 15 “Kaina siibi daane e dahi, hai gi Aaron mo ana dama gi dugua nadau lima gi hongo di libogo di maa.
\v 16 Daaligidia di maa gii made, kaina nia dodo ga magamaga gi di gili o nia baahi e haa o di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha.
\v 17 Duduu dia tama siibi daane hagaligiligi, gaugaulia ono baahi mo ono wae, gaa dugu nia maa gi hongo di ulu dono libogo mo i hongo ono baahi ala i golo.
\v 18 Duungia di manu dogomaalia i hongo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha e hai ai tigidaumaha meegai. Di llamu tigidaumaha deenei le e hagatenetene Au.\x * \xo 29.18 \xt Ephesians 5.2; Philippians 4.18\x*
\p 
\v 19 “Kaina tama siibi daane dela i golo, di manu dela e hai di hagadabu, helekai gi Aaron mo ana dama daane gi dugua nadau lima gi hongo di libogo di maa.
\v 20 Daaligidia di manu deelaa gii made, kaina nia dodo o di maa, hunu ina gi hongo nia dalinga gau donu Aaron mo ana dama, mo i hongo nia madaalima mmaadua o nadau lima gau donu, mo i hongo nia madaawae mmaadua o nadau wae gau donu. Kaina nia dodo ala e dubu, ga magamaga gi di gili o nia baahi e haa o di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha.
\v 21 Kae ina hunu dodo ala i hongo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha mo hunu lolo hagatulu, haga tulu tulu ina gi hongo Aaron mo hongo ono gahu mo i hongo ana dama mo nadau gahu. Gei mee mo ana dama mo nadau gahu gu hagadabu mai gi di Au.
\p 
\v 22 “Duudia gi daha nia kiliidi o tama siibi daane, kiliidi di hugu, nia kiliidi ala e gahu nia dudaginga laa lodo, di gowaa humalia huoloo o di ade, nia ‘kidney’ e lua ala ono kiliidi ono gili, mo di gadawae baahi gau donu.
\v 23 Mai di gada palaawaa dela ne tigidaumaha mai gi di Au, daawaa ina gi daha tagadilinga palaawaa e dahi mai nia palaawaa aalaa: di palaawaa e dahi ne hai gi nia lolo olib, di palaawaa e dahi digi wanga ginai nia lolo olib, mo di bagu baabaa e dahi.
\v 24 Wanga ina nia meegai huogodoo aanei gi lodo nia lima o Aaron mo ana dama daane e hagadabu mai gi di Au, e hai ai di wanga dehuia hagalabagau.
\v 25 Nomuli, kaina nia maa mai nadau lima, duungia i hongo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha, e hagapuni ang gi tigidaumaha dudu, e hai ai tigidaumaha meegai mai gi di Au. Di hauiha o tigidaumaha deenei e hagatenetene Au.
\p 
\v 26 “Kaina tadahada o tama siibi daane ga hagadabu mai be tigidaumaha hagalabagau. Di baahi o di manu deenei la ni goodou.
\p 
\v 27 “Di madagoaa tangada hai mee dabu ga hagadabu, tadahada mo di gadawae o tama siibi dela nogo hai hegau gi di hagadabu e tigidaumaha mai gi di Au e hai ai tigidaumaha hagalabagau, gei e dugu gi daha gi digau hai mee dabu.
\v 28 Ma go dagu hilihili e deemee di huli dela e hai bolo di madagoaa agu daangada ma gaa hai nadau tigidaumaha hagadaubuni, tadahada mo di gadawae gau donu la nia mee ni digau hai mee dabu. Deenei di wanga dehuia o nia daangada mai gi di Au, go Dimaadua.
\p 
\v 29 “Nia gahu hai hegau dabu Aaron e wanga gi ana dama i muli dono made, e ulu digaula ma ga hagadabu gi digau hai mee dabu.
\v 30 Tama daane Aaron dela e pono dono lohongo e ulu gi lodo dogu Hale laa e hai hegau i lodo di Gowaa Dabu e ulu nia gahu aanei i nia laangi e hidu.
\p 
\v 31 “Kaina nia goneiga o tama siibi daane dela nogo hai di hagadabu a Aaron mo ana dama daane, gaa dunu i lodo di gowaa dabu.
\v 32 Digaula e gai nia maa mo nia palaawaa ala ne dubu i lodo di gada i di ngudu di bontai o dogu Hale laa.
\v 33 Digaula e gai nia meegai ala nogo hai hegau ai i di nadau hegau o tumaalia ang gi di nadau hagadabu. Digau hai mee dabu la hua e mee di gai nia meegai aanei, idimaa nia maa le e dabuaahia.
\v 34 Maa hunu goneiga be hunu palaawaa gaa dubu gi dono daiaa, nia maa le e dudu, nia maa e hagalee gai, idimaa nia maa le e dabu.
\p 
\v 35 “Heia di hagadabu a Aaron mo ana dama daane i lodo nia laangi e hidu dogomaalia be dagu hai ne hagamodongoohia adu.
\v 36 I nia laangi huogodoo, goe e hai loo gi tigidaumaha dau kau daane e hagamehede ai nia hala. Di mee deenei e hagamadammaa di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha. Nomuli, hagatulu ina di maa gi di lolo olib e hai di maa gii dabu.
\v 37 Heia beenei i nia laangi huogodoo i lodo nia laangi e hidu. Di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha ga hagahuaidu hagatau, tangada be dahi mee ma gaa bili gi di maa la ga hagamadagu go nia mogobuna o dono hagamadagu.
\s1 Tigidaumaha i nia laangi huogodoo
\p 
\v 38 “Nia laangi huogodoo gi muli, tigidaumaha ina i hongo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha nia dama siibi e lua e dagi dahi nau ngadau.
\v 39 Tigidaumaha ina tama siibi e dahi luada, ge tama siibi i golo i di hiahi.
\v 40 Tigidaumaha ina dalia tama siibi matagidagi nia pauna palaawaa ‘wheat’ e lua e unugi gi dahi baahi e haa galon waini.
\v 41 Tigidaumaha ina togolua dama siibi i di hiahi dalia nia palaawaa, lolo olib, mono waini gii hai be di hai dela ne hai i di luada. Deenei tigidaumaha humalia mai gi di Au, ge dono hauiha e hagatenetene Au.
\v 42 I nia madagoaa huogodoo ala ga loomoi, tigidaumaha dudu deenei e hai i ogu mua i di bontai o dogu Hale laa. Deelaa di gowaa e heetugi iei Au gi agu daangada ge ga helekai adu.
\v 43 Au ga heetugi gi digau Israel i di gowaa deelaa, gei dogu maahina maaloo gaa hai di gowaa gi hagamadagu.
\v 44 Au gaa hai di Hale laa mo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha gi hagamadagu, gei Au gaa dugu gi daha Aaron mo ana dama e hai nadau hegau be digau hai mee dabu.
\v 45 Au gaa noho i lodo digau Israel e hai di nadau God.
\v 46 Digaula ga iloo laa bolo Au go Dimaadua go di nadau God dela ne laha mai ginaadou gi daha mo Egypt, bolo gii noho Au i nadau baahi. Au go Dimaadua di nadau God.
\c 30
\s1 Di gowaa dudu mee tigidaumaha lolo kala
\r (Exodus 37.25-28)
\p 
\v 1 “Heia di gowaa tigidaumaha gi nia laagau ‘acacia’ e dudu nia ‘incense’.
\v 2 Di looloo mo di palaha e hagatau be di mee e dahi, nia ‘inch’ e 18 gei tuuduu gi nua nia ‘inch’ e 36. Heia nia madaagoo e haa ala e tolo gi daha i nia madaaduge gii hai di mee e dahi gi tuaidina di maa.
\v 3 Hii ina di ulu gi nua di maa mo ono baahi e haa, mo ono gowaa ala e tolo gi daha gi nia goolo madammaa, haganiga ina taalinga di maa gi nia goolo.
\v 4 Heia ono buulei aamo mee e lua gi nia goolo, hauhia nia maa gi baahi lala taalinga o nia baahi e lua, e daahi laagau aamo.
\v 5 Heia nia laagau aamo gi nia laagau ‘acacia’, gaa hii nia maa gi nia goolo.
\v 6 Duguina di mee dudu tigidaumaha gi tua di gahu duuli dela e daudau i mua Tebedebe di Hagababa. Deelaa di gowaa e heetugi iei Au adu gi di goe.
\v 7 I nia luada huogodoo, i di madagoaa Aaron ga hanimoi e benebene nia malama, mee e hai loo gii dudu dana mee hagakala ‘incense’ gi hongo di maa.
\v 8 Mee e hai loo gii hai be dana hai i di madagoaa mee gaa dudu nia malama i di hiahi. Tigidaumaha o nia ‘incense’ deenei e hai gii hai gi muli i lodo nia madagoaa huogodoo ala ga lloomoi.
\v 9 Hudee hai tigidaumaha i hongo di gowaa tigidaumaha deenei nia ‘incense’ ala guu bule, be tigidaumaha manu, be tigidaumaha huwa laagau, gei hudee dui ina nia waini gi hongo di maa.
\v 10 Di laangi e dahi i lodo di ngadau e dahi, Aaron gi heia dana hegau dabu e hagamadammaa di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha i dana dui nia dodo o di manu dela ne tigidaumaha gi nia hala la gi hongo nia madaagoo e haa ala e tolo mai gi daha. Di mee deenei e hai i lodo nia ngadau dagidahi o nia madagoaa huogodoo ala e lloomoi. Di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha deenei le e hai gi dabuaahia, e hagadabu mai gi di Au, go Dimaadua.”
\s1 Dagitedi gi di Hale laa Dimaadua
\p 
\v 11 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses,
\v 12 “Di madagoaa ma gaa hai di dau o nia daangada Israel, nia daangada dagi dahi e hui mai gi di Au di hui o dono mouli, gei nia haingadaa llauehe ga hagalee tale ang gi deia i di madagoaa di dau o nia daangada e hai.
\v 13 Nia daangada huogodoo i lodo di dau dangada e hai gi dahi aga nia pauna bahihadu ala gu haganoho bolo e dahi aga, e pauna be di hai nia daangada e pauna ai. Nia daangada huogodoo e hai gii hui e tigidaumaha mai gi di Au.\x * \xo 30.13 \xt Exodus 38.25,26; Matthew 17.24\x*
\v 14 Nia daangada huogodoo ala nadau ngadau e madalua be mada mmaadua nadau ngadau i lodo di dau le e hui mai di hulu deenei.
\v 15 Tangada maluagina e hagalee hui gii logo, gei tangada hagaloale e hagalee hui hagahogoohi i di madagoaa ginaadou gaa hui di hulu deenei ang gi nadau mouli.
\v 16 Hagabudu ina nia bahihadu aanei mai digau Israel, hai hegau gi nia maa e benebene gi humalia dogu Hale laa. Dagitedi deenei la di hui o nadau mouli, gei Au ga langahia di benebene nadau mouli.”
\s1 Di baisin baalanga mmee
\p 
\v 17 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses,
\v 18 “Heia di baisin baalanga mmee mo dono lohongo baalanga mmee. Dugua i mehanga di Hale laa mo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha, wanga ina nia wai gi lodo. \x * \xo 30.18 \xt Exodus 38.8\x*
\v 19 Aaron mo ana dama daane e tonotono nadau lima mo nadau wae gi nia maa,
\v 20 i mua di nadau hula gi lodo di Hale laa be e loomoi gi di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha e hai tigidaumaha meegai. Ma gaa hai beenei, gei digaula hagalee daaligi gii mmade.
\v 21 Digaula e hai loo gii tono nadau lima mo nadau wae gi dee mmade ginaadou. Deenei taganoho e hai loo gi daudali go digaula mo nadau hagadili gaa hana hua beelaa.”
\s1 Nia lolo hagatulu
\r (Exodus 37.29)
\p 
\v 22 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses,
\v 23 “Kaina nia mee unugi mee hagakala humalia huogodoo, nia pauna 12 wai ‘myrrh’, 6 pauna ‘cinnamon’ kala, 6 pauna mee ngau llamu kala,
\v 24 ge 12 pauna gili laagau ‘cassia’, e pauna be di hai nia daangada e pauna ai. Hagapunia gi di galon lolo olib.
\v 25 Heia nia lolo hagatulu e unugi gi nia lolo hagakala.
\v 26 Hai hegau gi di maa e hagatulu dogu Hale laa, Tebedebe di Hagababa,
\v 27 teebele mo nia mee hai hegau huogodoo, di lohongo malama mo ono goloo, di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha lolo kala,
\v 28 di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha mo ono goloo huogodoo, di baisin tonotono mo dono lohongo.
\v 29 Hagadabu ina nia mee aanei, gei nia maa ga hagamadagu huogodoo, gei tangada be di mee ma gaa bili gi nia maa ga hagamadagu go di mogobuna o dono hagamadagu.
\v 30 Hagatulu ina Aaron mo ana dama daane, heia digaula gii hai digau hai mee dabu i lodo agu hegau.
\v 31 Helekai gi digau Israel bolo nia lolo hagatulu e hai hegau ai i lodo agu hegau i nia madagoaa huogodoo ma ga dau mai.
\v 32 Nia lolo e hagalee hagatulu gi hongo di ingoo hua tangada, gei goe hude hai lolo gii hai be di maa. Ma e dabuaahia, goe heia di maa be di mee dabuaahia.
\v 33 Tangada ma gaa hai ana lolo be nia maa, be e hai hegau nia maa gi di ingoo tangada dela hagalee tangada hai mee dabu, ga hagalee hai tangada ni aagu.”
\s1 Nia ‘incense’
\p 
\v 34 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Kaina di baahi be di mee e dahi o nia mee hagakala meegai ‘spice’ aanei: nia ‘stacte’, ‘onycha’, ‘galbanum’, mo ‘frankincense’ madammaa.
\v 35 Heia nia maa gii hai nia ‘incense’, e unugi be nia lolo kala. Hagapuni anga gi nia toolo gi humalia ge gi hagamadagu.
\v 36 Tuugia hunu mee i nia maa gii lligi be nia luaahi, kaina gi dogu Hale laa ga hagatulu i mua Tebedebe di Hagababa. Heia nia ‘incense’ bolo di mee hagamadagu dogomaalia.
\v 37 Hudee hai hegau gi nia ‘incense’ be di maa adu gi goodou. Heia di maa be di mee dabu mai gi di Au.
\v 38 Maa tangada gaa hai dana mee be di maa e hai hegau ai be di lolokala, mee ga hagalee hai tangada ni aagu.”
\c 31
\s1 Digau hau Hale laa Dimaadua
\r (Exodus 35.30—36.1)
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses,
\v 2 “Au gu hilihili Bezalel, tama daane a Uri go tama daane a Hur, mai di madawaawa Judah,
\v 3 gei Au gu hagahonu a mee gi ogu mogobuna, Au guu wanga ono iloo di hai nia mee mo dono iloo di hai nnagadilinga moomee hagamadamada mee,
\v 4 ang gi nia bilaan nia mee humalia e haga hai hegau nia maa gi nia goolo, silber mo nia baalanga mmee;
\v 5 e tuu nia hadu hagalabagau ala belee haganoho; e iloo di paa nia laagau, mo nia hagadilinga moomee hagamadamada mee ala i golo.
\v 6 Au gu hilihili labelaa Oholiab, tama daane Ahisamach, mai di madawaawa Dan belee ngalua dalia a mee. Au guu wanga labelaa di iloo di hai mee gi digau huogodoo ala i golo, gii mee di hai agu mee aanei ala bolo gi heia:
\v 7 Dogu Hale laa, Tebedebe di Hagababa mo dono uhi, nia mee huogodoo i lodo di Hale laa,
\v 8 teebele mo nia mee hai hegau huogodoo, di lohongo malama ne hai gi nia goolo madammaa mo ono goloo, di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha lolo kala,
\v 9 di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha, baisin tonotono llauehe mo dono lohongo,
\v 10 nia gahu dangada hai mee dabu ang gi Aaron mo ana dama daane e hai hegau digaula ma ga ngalua,
\v 11 nia lolo hagatulu, mo nia ‘incense’ ang gi di Gowaa Dabu. Digaula la gi heia nia mee aanei huogodoo gii hai be agu helekai ne hai adu.”
\s1 Di Laangi Sabad la di laangi hagamolooloo
\p 
\v 12 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses bolo
\v 13 gi helekai gi digau Israel boloo, “Hagalabagau ina di Laangi Sabad bolo di laangi hagamolooloo ni aagu, idimaa ma di haga modongoohia i mehanga goodou mo Au ang gi nia madagoaa huogodoo ala e loomoi, e hagamodongoohia bolo ma ko Au go Dimaadua ne hai goodou gii hai agu daangada donu.
\v 14 Goodou e hai loo gi hagalabagau ina di laangi hagamolooloo, idimaa ma e hagamadagu. Tangada ma ga hagalee hagadabuaahia di maa gei e ngalua hua le e daaligi gii made.
\v 15 Nia laangi e ono e hai au moomee, di hidu laangi la di laangi hagamadagu dela ne hagadabu mai gi di Au. Tangada ma ga ngalua i di laangi deelaa le e daaligi gii made.\x * \xo 31.15 \xt Exodus 20.8-11; 23.12; 34.21; 35.2; Leviticus 23.3; Deuteronomy 5.12-14\x*
\v 16 Digau Israel e hai loo gi daahi di laangi deenei bolo ma di haga modongoohia ni di hagababa.
\v 17 Ma di hagamodongoohia e noho beelaa gi muli i mehanga digau Israel mo Au, idimaa Au go Dimaadua ne hai di langi mo henuailala i lodo nia laangi e ono, di hidu laangi Au ne dugu dagu moomee ga hagamolooloo.”\x * \xo 31.17 \xt Exodus 20.11\x*
\p 
\v 18 I muli o God ne haga lawa ana helekai nogo hai gi Moses i hongo di Gonduu Sinai, gei Mee gaa wanga ana baahi hadu e lua gi Moses, ala guu lawa dana hihi ginai ana haganoho gi dono madaalima donu.
\c 32
\s1 Di kau daane ne hai gi nia goolo
\r (Deuteronomy 9.6-29)
\p 
\v 1 Nia daangada ne iloo bolo Moses gu duai i di gonduu, gei digaula ga dagabuli mai gi Aaron ga helekai gi mee, “Heia dau god e lahi gidaadou, idimaa gimaadou e de iloo be Moses go taane dela ne laha mai gimaadou gi daha mo Egypt la gu aha?”\x * \xo 32.1 \xt Acts 7.40\x*
\p 
\v 2 Gei Aaron ga helekai gi digaula, “Hagabudu ina mai laa nia akai dabadaba goolo ala i nia dalinga o godou lodo mo godou dama daane mo godou dama ahina, gaamai gi di au.”
\v 3 Gei digaula ga hagabudu nia maa gi mee.
\v 4 Geia gaa kae nia maa, gaa dunu gi waiwai, gaa dui gi lodo di mee gii hai di kau daane goolo.
\p Nia daangada gu wwolo loo gi nua boloo, “Digau Israel nei, deenei tadau god ne dagi mai gidaadou gi daha mo Egypt!”\x * \xo 32.4 \xt 1-Kings 12.28; Acts 7.41\x*
\p 
\v 5 Aaron ga haga duu dana gowaa dudu tigidaumaha i mua di ada kau daane goolo deelaa, geia ga haga iloo ang gi digaula, “Daiaa gei gidaadou gaa hai taumaha hagalaamua a Dimaadua.”
\v 6 Hooaga dono daiaa, gei digaula ga tigidaumaha nadau manu ne dudu, mo di gai nia tigidaumaha hagadaubuni. Digaula ga noho mai ga miami, nomuli ga inu nadau dagaao gu libaliba, ga haihai nadau hai lodo manu i nadau mehanga.\x * \xo 32.6 \xt 1-Corinthians 10.7\x*
\p 
\v 7 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hana gi lala hagalimalima gi au daangada ala ne laha mai i Egypt, i digaula gu ihala, gu hai baahi mai gi di Au.
\v 8 Digaula gu limalima hua di hula laa daha mo nia mee ala ne hai ko Au bolo gi heia. Digaula guu dunu nadau goolo guu hai di nadau kau daane, gu dadaumaha ge gu tigitigidaumaha ginai digaula, gei guu hai bolo deelaa di nadau god, dela ne laha mai ginaadou i Egypt.
\v 9 Au e iloo bolo digaula digau hamaaloo nadau lodo.
\v 10 Goe hudee haga madugidugia ina Au. Au gu hagawelewele gi digaula, Au ga hagahuaidu digaula, gei Au gaa hai goe mo do hagadili gii hai di golohenua aamua.”
\p 
\v 11 Moses ga dangidangi hagamahi gi Dimaadua go dono God, ga helekai, “Meenei Dimaadua, goe e aha dela e hagawelewele gi au dama ala ne haga dagaloaha Kooe mai gi daha mo Egypt gi o mogobuna llauehaa?\x * \xo 32.11 \xt Numbers 14.13-19\x*
\v 12 Hudee heia digau Egypt gii hai bolo goe ne laha mai au dama gi daha mo Egypt, gaa lawa gaa kili gi daha digaula gii mmade i lodo nia gonduu aanei! Dugua ia do manawa hagawelewele, aloho gi au dama, hudee hagahuaidu ina digaula.
\v 13 Goe gi maanadu ina dau hagababa hagalabagau dela ne hagababa gi au gau hai hegau go Abraham, Jacob mo Isaac, bolo Goe ga haga dogologo nia madawaawa digaula, gii logo be nia heduu ala i di langi, gaa wanga ginai dau henua dela ne hagababa Kooe bolo e noho ai digaula gaa hana hua beelaa.”\x * \xo 32.13 \xt Genesis 22.16,17; Genesis 17.8\x*
\v 14 Gei Dimaadua guu huli dono manawa, gu hagalee hagahuaidu digaula be ana helekai ala ne hai.
\p 
\v 15 Moses ga haneia i di gonduu mo ana baahi hadu e lua ala guu hihi ginai nia haganoho gi nia baahi e lua.
\v 16 Nia hadu baabaa aanei la nia mee hua ni God ne hai gi ono lima, gei nia mee ala ne hihi dono gili la ni God donu hua ne hihi.
\p 
\v 17 Joshua ga longono ia di lee gau dogologo e moogo, geia ga helekai gi Moses, “Ma di mee be di lee dauwa e hai i lodo di waahale laa.”
\p 
\v 18 Gei Moses ga helekai, “Ma hagalee di lee tenetene ne maaloo, be di lee manawa gee ne magedaa. Au e hagalongo bolo ma digau e huwa nadau daahili.”
\p 
\v 19 Di madagoaa o Moses ne hoohoo adu gi di waahale laa, gei mee ga gidee ia di kau daane, mo nia daangada ala e gagaalege, gei mee gu hagawelewele huoloo, gaa kili nia hadu baabaa gi lala gu mahaahaa.
\v 20 Geia gaa kae di kau daane goolo dela ne hai go digaula, gaa hudu gi lodo di ahi, gaa lawa gaa olo gii lligi be nia luaahi, ga unugi gi nia wai, gaa wanga gi digau Israel bolo gi inumia.
\v 21 Gei mee ga helekai gi Aaron, “Ma di aha dela ne hai go digau aanei adu gi di goe, dela goe gaa hai digaula gii hala i di huaidu damanaiee beenei?”
\p 
\v 22 Aaron ga helekai gi Moses, “Goe hudee hagawelewele mai gi di au. Goe e iloo hua bolo digau aanei digau hua e hiihai e hai nia mee huaidu.
\v 23 Digaula ne helekai mai boloo, ‘Heia mai gi gimaadou di madau god e dagi gimaadou, idimaa, gimaadou gu de iloo be taane dela nogo dagi mai gimaadou i Egypt la gu aha.’
\v 24 Gei au gaa hai gi digaula bolo gi hagabudulia mai nadau goolo, malaa digau ala nadau akai dabadaba goolo i golo ga hagabudu mai, gei au gaa kili nia maa gi lodo di ahi, gei di ada kau daane deenei la ga ulu mai!”
\p 
\v 25 Gei Moses gu iloo ia bolo nia daangada la gu hinihini hua i di hai a Aaron ne dumaalia digaula gi heia nadau mee huaidu ala e hiihai ginai, digaula guu hai digau haga gadagada dangada i mua nadau hagadaumee.
\v 26 Geia gaa duu i baahi di bontai di abaaba o di waahale gaa wolo gi nua, “Tangada dela bolo ia e hai tangada ni Dimaadua, geia gi hanimoi gi di au!” Gei digau Levi ga mmui mai, ga hii mai dono gili.
\v 27 Gei mee ga helekai gi digaula, “Aanei la nnelekai Dimaadua ala ne hai: tangada nei mo tangada nei i goodou gi iai dana hulumanu dauwa, hula laa lodo di waahale laa deenei, daamada i di bontai deenei gaa dau loo gi di bontai dela i golo, hula daaligidia godou duaahina mo godou ihoo mo digau ala e noho hoohoo adu gi goodou.”
\v 28 Digau Levi gu daudali nia helekai a Moses, gei di laangi deelaa nia daane holongo e dolu mana (3,000) ne daaligi gii mmade.
\v 29 Moses ga helekai gi digau Levi, “Dangi nei goodou guu bida haga dabu hua goodou gi nia hegau dabu a Dimaadua, i di godou hai dela ne daaligi godou dama daane mo godou duaahina daane. Malaa, Dimaadua gu dugu adu dono maluagina gi goodou dangi nei.”
\p 
\v 30 Dono daiaa, gei Moses ga helekai gi digau Israel, “Goodou guu hai di godou mee huaidu huoloo. Au gaa hana labelaa gi Dimaadua i hongo di gonduu, e dangi gi Mee be Mee e dumaalia gi godou haihai huaidu ne hai.”
\v 31 Moses gaa hana gi baahi o Dimaadua ga helekai, “Meenei, nia daangada aanei guu hai nadau mee hala huaidu huoloo, guu hai di nadau god goolo belee dadaumaha ginai.
\v 32 Dumaalia mua gi digaula. Maa goe ga hagalee dumaalia laa, tono ina dogu ingoo gi daha mo di beebaa dela ne hihi Kooe nia ingoo o au daangada.”\x * \xo 32.32 \xt Pisalem 69.28; Revelation 3.5\x*
\p 
\v 33 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Tangada dela ne hai dana huaidu, deelaa dagu dangada e tono dono ingoo gi daha mo dagu beebaa.
\v 34 Malaa, hana, lahia agu daangada gi di gowaa dela ne hagi adu. Goe gi langahia bolo dagu dangada di langi gaa dagi goe. Gei di madagoaa o di hagaduadua ga dau mai, gei Au ga hagaduadua digaula i di nadau huaidu dela ne hai.”
\p 
\v 35 Dimaadua gu hagaduadua digaula gii hai nadau magi huaidu huoloo, idimaa, digaula ne hai a Aaron gii hai dana kau daane goolo.
\c 33
\s1 Dimaadua guu hai gi digau Israel gi hagatanga i di Gonduu Sinai
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hagatanga i ginei mo au gau ala ne dagi mai i Egypt. Goodou hula gi dagu henua dela ne hagababa ang gi Abraham, Isaac mo Jacob mo ang gi nadau madahaanau. \x * \xo 33.1 \xt Genesis 12.7; \xt Genesis 26.3; \xt Genesis 28.13\x*
\v 2 Au ga hagau ia dagu dangada di langi e dagi goodou, gei Au ga hagabagi laa digau Canaan, Amor, Hittite, Perizzite, Hivite mo Jebus.
\v 3 Goodou e hula gi tenua tomo ge logo ono meegai. Gei Au hagalee hana dalia goodou, idimaa goodou e aago ngadaa, gi dee hana hua Au, ga hagahuaidu goodou i hongo di ala deelaa.”
\p 
\v 4 Di madagoaa nia daangada ne longono ginaadou di longo hagahuaidu lodo dangada deenei, gei digaula gu tangitangi gu hagalee ulu nadau goloo humu dangada.
\v 5 Idimaa, Dimaadua la ne helekai gi Moses bolo gi helekai gi digau aalaa boloo: “Goodou digau hamaaloo godou lodo. Maa nei bolo Au gaa hana dalia goodou tei madagoaa hua, gei Au ga daaligi goodou huogodoo. Dolomeenei gei goodou aauina gi daha nia goloo humu dangada ala i goodou, gei Au ga hagamamaanadu agu mee ala gaa hai adu gi goodou.”
\v 6 Malaa, i muli di nadau hagatanga i di Gonduu Sinai, digau Israel gu hagalee ulu nadau goloo laagei.
\s1 Di Hale laa a Dimaadua
\p 
\v 7 Nia madagoaa huogodoo, digaula ma ga haga duu aga nadau hale laa, gei Moses e haga duu di Hale laa Dimaadua gi mada tanga i daha mo di waahale laa. Di Hale laa deelaa e haga ingoo bolo di Hale laa Dimaadua. Tangada ma ga iai dana mee e hagadonu mai Dimaadua le e hana gi golo.
\v 8 Nia holongo huogodoo a Moses ma gaa hana gi di Hale laa deelaa, gei digau huogodoo le e tuu i di ngudu nia bontai o nadau hale laa, e daumada a mee gaa dae loo gi dono ulu gi lodo di Hale laa deelaa.
\v 9 Di madagoaa Moses ne ulu gi lodo di Hale laa, gei di waduu gololangi ga haneia gaa uhi di bontai di Hale laa deelaa, gei Dimaadua ga leelee gi Moses.
\v 10 Di nadau mmada gi di waduu gololangi deelaa e duu i di ngudu di bontai di Hale laa, digaula huogodoo ga dogoduli.
\v 11 Dimaadua e leelee gi Moses hua hagammaa gadoo be tangada e ngudukai gi dono ehoo. Nomuli hua, gei Moses gaa hana gi muli gi lodo di waahale laa, gei dana dangada hai hegau go Joshua, tama daane a Nun, e noho hua i golo i lodo di Hale laa deelaa.
\s1 Dimaadua gu hagababa bolo Ia e madalia ana daangada
\p 
\v 12 Moses ga helekai gi Dimaadua, “Goe ne helekai mai gi di au bolo au gi dagia mai au daangada, gei Goe digi hagia mai be ma koai dela e hula gimaua. Gei Goe guu hai bolo Goe e iloo dogu ingoo, ge e tene mai.
\v 13 Maa Goe e tene mai gi di au, gei au e dangi adu bolo Goe gi hagia mai do manawa, gei au gaa mee di hai hegau e haga tenetene Goe. Gei Goe gi langahia bolo aanei digau ne hilihili Kooe belee hai au dama.”
\p 
\v 14 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai, “Au e hana madalia goe, e hai goe gi maaloo i nia dauwa.”
\p 
\v 15 Gei Moses ga helekai, “Goe ma ga hagalee hana madalia gimaadou, gei Goe hudee hagau ina gimaadou gi daha mo kinei.
\v 16 Maa Goe ga dee hana madalia gimaadou, gei au mo au daangada le e iloo di aha bolo Goe e tene mai gi gimaadou? Gei Goe gaa hana madalia gimaadou, gei gimaadou guu hai digau e dugu gee mo digau huogodoo i henuailala.”
\p 
\v 17 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Au gaa hai laa gii hai be au helekai, i di Au e tene adu gei gu iloo e Au do ingoo.”
\p 
\v 18 Gei Moses ga helekai gi Dimaadua, “Dumaalia mai, haga mmada ina mua Au gi o madamada.”
\p 
\v 19 Gei Dimaadua ga helekai gi mee, “Au ga hagau ogu madamada gii hula i oo mua, gei Au gaa gahi dogu ingoo dabuaahia i oo mua. Deenei dogu ingoo go Yihowah, dela e manawa dumaalia ge e aloho i digau ala e hilihili ko Au.\x * \xo 33.19 \xt Romans 9.15\x*
\v 20 Goe e deemee di gidee ogu golomada, idimaa, deai tangada e mee di mmada mai gi di Au gaa noho mouli ai.
\v 21 Deenei di gowaa i dogu baahi e mee di duu iei goe i hongo tadugalaa.
\v 22 Di madagoaa dogu madamada ma gaa dae mai gi kinei, gei Au gaa dugu goe gi di bongoo i lodo di hadugalaa, gaa pono o golomada gi ogu lima, gaa dae loo gi dogu hanadu laa oo mua.
\v 23 Gei Au gaa daa ogu lima gi daha, gei goe ga mmada hua gi dogu dua, hagalee go ogu hadumada.”
\c 34
\s1 Di hai haga lua nia baahi hadu e lua
\r (Deuteronomy 10.1-5)
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Heia au baahi hadu e lua be nia hadu matagidagi, gei Au gaa hihi nia maa gi nia helekai ala nogo i nia baahi hadu matagidagi ala ne haga mahaahaa kooe.
\v 2 Luada daiaa gei goe ga hagatogomaalia ga hanaga gi di Au i hongo di Gonduu Sinai.
\v 3 Tangada e hana aga goolua ai, ge deai tangada i tei gowaa i di gonduu ai, ge deai di siibi be di kau e miami i tono di gonduu deenei ai.”
\v 4 Moses gaa hai ana baahi hadu e lua be nia hadu matagidagi, luada dono daiaa, geia ga hanaga gi hongo di gonduu mo ana baahi hadu e lua, be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai.
\p 
\v 5 Gei Dimaadua ga haneia i lodo di gololangi gi mua o Moses, gaa gahi dono ingoo haga madagu go Yihowah.
\v 6 Dimaadua gaa hana laa mua o mee ga helekai, “Ko Au go Yihowah, go di God dela e manawa dumaalia ge e aloho, ge hagalee limalima di hagawelewele ngoohia, gei e honu i di aloho mo di manawa dahi.\x * \xo 34.6 \xt Exodus 20.5,6; Numbers 14.18; Deuteronomy 5.9,10; 7.9,10\x*
\v 7 Au e haga kila aga agu hagababa ang gi digau dogologowaahee, ge e dumaalia gi nia huaidu mo nia hala. Gei Au e hagahuaidu nia dama mo nadau dama gi muli, gaa dae loo gi di tolu mo di haa adu dama, i nia huaidu o nadau damana.”
\p 
\v 8 Di madagoaa hua deelaa, gei Moses ga dogoduli ga daumaha,
\v 9 ga helekai, “Meenei Dimaadua, maa e donu bolo Goe e tene mai gi di au laa, goe noho hua i madau baahi. Digau aanei la digau hua e manawa hamaaloo, gei Goe dumaalia mai gi madau hai hala mo madau huaidu, dugua hua gimaadou gi hai hua be nia dama ni aau.”
\s1 Di lua hagababa
\r (Exodus 23.14-19; Deuteronomy 7.1-5; 16.1-17)
\p 
\v 10 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Au gaa hai dagu hagababa gi digau Israel. Au gaa hai agu mee haga goboina i mua digaula, nia mee digi kila loo i tei gowaa i henuailala. Gei digau ala i do baahi gaa mmada gi nia maa, gei digaula ga iloo bolo ma ko Au go Dimaadua dela e mee di hai di mee hagamadagudia huoloo adu gi di goe.
\v 11 Goodou la gi hagalongo gi agu haganoho ala e hagi adu ko Au dangi nei. Au ga hagabagi digau Amor, Canaan, Hittite, Perizzite, Hivite mo Jebus la gi daha mo godou mua.
\v 12 Goodou hudee hai hagababa gi digau o tenua dela e hula ginai goodou, idimaa ma gaa hai beelaa, gei di maa gaa hai goodou gi paagege.
\v 13 Gei goodou la gi ohaa ina nia gowaa dudu tigidaumaha digaula mo nadau waduu haga madagu, gei goodou la gi hele ina gi lala nia ada o di god ahina go Asherah.\x * \xo 34.13 \xt Deuteronomy 16.21\x*
\p 
\v 14 “Goodou hudee daumaha gi nnuai god gee i daha mo Au, idimaa, Au go Yihowah la di God dubua.
\v 15 Goodou hudee hai hagababa gi digau o tenua deelaa, idimaa, di madagoaa digaula ma ga daumaha gi nadau balu god, ge e hai nadau tigidaumaha, digaula ga gahi mai goodou e miami i nadau mee ala nogo tigidaumaha ai.
\v 16 Dolomaa godou dama daane la ga hai lodo gi nia dama ahina digaula, gei nia ahina aalaa gaa dagi digaula gi di nadau hai daumaha gi nadau god, gaa hidi ai godou dama daane gaa huli gi daha mo Au, ga daumaha gi nia god dilikai.
\p 
\v 17 “Goodou hudee hai god baalanga belee daumaha ginai goodou.\x * \xo 34.17 \xt Exodus 20.4; Leviticus 19.4; Deuteronomy 5.8; 27.15\x*
\p 
\v 18 “Goodou heia Tagamiami o di Palaawaa Digi Hagatanga. Goodou geina go nia palaawaa digi hagatanga ina i lodo nia laangi e hidu i lodo di malama go Abib, be agu helekai ala gu hai adu, idimaa, deelaa di malama ne hagatanga goodou gi daha mo Egypt.\x * \xo 34.18 \xt Exodus 12.14-20; Leviticus 23.6-8; Numbers 28.16-25\x*
\p 
\v 19 “Nia ulu mmaadua daane huogodoo mono ulu mmaadua daane o nia manu la nia mee ni aagu.\x * \xo 34.19 \xt Exodus 13.2\x*
\v 20 Gei goodou la gi tigidaumaha ina tama siibi e pono di lohongo o di ulumadua o di ‘donkey’. Maa goodou hagalee pono di maa gi tama siibi la haadia di uwa di maa. Gei goodou la gi huia mai nia ulu mmaadua o godou dama daane.\x * \xo 34.20 \xt Exodus 13.13\x*
\p “Deai tangada e hana la ogu mua ge deai dana mee e tigidaumaha mai gi di Au ai.
\p 
\v 21 “Goodou heia hua godou moomee i lodo nia laangi e ono, gei di hidu laangi le e hagamolooloo hua, ma e aha maa di madagoaa belee hagamaluu di hadagee, be e hadi nia huwa laagau.\x * \xo 34.21 \xt Exodus 20.9,10; 23.12; 31.15; 35.2; Leviticus 23.3; Deuteronomy 5.13,14\x*
\p 
\v 22 “Goodou heia Taumaha o di Hagadogodo o nia Huwa laagau i godou madagoaa ma gaa hadi matagidagi godou huwa ‘wheat’. Goodou heia labelaa Tagamiami o nia Damaa hale Hagaabili, i di madagoaa magalillili i di godou madagoaa e hagabudu ai godou huwa laagau.\x * \xo 34.22 \xt Leviticus 23.15-21; 23.33-34; 23.39-43; Numbers 28.26-31\x*
\p 
\v 23 “Nia holongo e dolu i lodo di ngadau e dahi ge nia daane huogodoo la gi lloomoi daumaha mai gi di Au go Tagi go Yihowah, go di God o Israel.
\v 24 Au ga hagabagi digau o di guongo la gi daha i godou mua, gaa lawa ga haga damana di godou gowaa, gei deai tangada e mee di haga magedaa di godou henua ai, i di godou madagoaa dela e hai hegau ai goodou i nia Hagamiami e dolu aanei.
\p 
\v 25 “Hudee wanga ina nia palaawaa tanga ala ne unugi gi nia ‘yeast’, madalia di godou manu dela ma ga tigidaumaha mai gi di Au. Nia mee ala ne dubu i di manu dela ne daaligi gi Tagamiami o di Pasoobaa la hudee dugu ina gi dono daiaa.\x * \xo 34.25 \xt Exodus 12.10\x*
\p 
\v 26 “Godou meegai henua ala e hadi matagidagi la gi gaamai gi di Hale Daumaha o Dimaadua.
\p “Goodou hudee dunu ina tama siibi be tamaa kuudi i lodo nia weuu o dono dinana.”\x * \xo 34.26 \xt Deuteronomy 26.2; 14.21\x*
\p 
\v 27 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses, “Hihia nia mee aanei gi lala, idimaa aanei nia helekai e haga mau ai di hagababa adu gi di goe mo digau Israel.”
\v 28 Moses nogo noho i baahi o Dimaadua i nia laangi e mada haa ge mada haa boo, digi miami ge digi inu. Mee gaa hihi nia helekai o di hagababa gi di gili nia baahi hadu e lua, dela go nia Haganoho e Madangaholu.
\s1 Moses e haneia i di Gonduu Sinai
\r (2-Corinthians 3.7-16)
\p 
\v 29 Di madagoaa o Moses ne haneia i di Gonduu Sinai e gaweia di Madangaholu Haganoho, ge de iloo ia bolo ono hadumada le e maahina i deia dela nogo ngudungudu kai gi Dimaadua.
\v 30 Di madagoaa Aaron mo digau ala ne gidee ginaadou a Moses dela e maahina ono hadumada, gei digaula gu mmaadagu di mmaanege adu gi mee.
\v 31 Gei Moses ga gahi mai digaula, gei Aaron mo nia dagi digau Israel ga lloomoi gi mee, gei Moses ga helekai gi digaula.
\v 32 Nomuli gei digau Israel huogodoo gu mmaanege adu gi baahi o mee, gei mee ga haga modongoohia nia haganoho huogodoo a Dimaadua ne hai ang gi deia i hongo di Gonduu Sinai.
\v 33 Gaa lawa loo ana helekai, geia gaa uhi ono golomada gi di mee gahu hadumada.
\v 34 Nia holongo huogodoo o mee ne hana ne heetugi gi Dimaadua i lodo di Hale laa dela e noho ai Dimaadua, geia e daa di mee gahu hadumada gi daha, gei dono madagoaa ga ulu mai gi daha, geia ga hagi anga gi digau Israel nia mee huogodoo a Dimaadua ne hai anga bolo gi odia ang gi digaula.
\v 35 Gei digaula e gidee nia hadumada o maa ala e maahina, gei mee gaa gahu ono hadumada gaa dae loo gi dono madagoaa e hana labelaa e heetugi gi Dimaadua.
\c 35
\s1 Nnaganoho di Laangi Sabad
\p 
\v 1 Moses ga gahi mai digau Israel huogodoo ga helekai gi digaula boloo, “Deenei telekai Dimaadua bolo goodou gi heia:
\v 2 Nia laangi e ono e hai godou moomee, gei di hidu laangi e hagamadagu, di laangi e hagamolooloo mai gi di Au go Dimaadua. Di ingoo hua tangada ma ga ngalua e daaligi gii made.\x * \xo 35.2 \xt Exodus 20.8-11; 23.12; 31.15; 34.21; Leviticus 23.3; Deuteronomy 5.12-14\x*
\v 3 Hudee akaa ahi i godou hale i di Laangi Sabad.”
\s1 Tigidaumaha gi di Hale laa Hagamadagu
\r (Exodus 25.1-9)
\p 
\v 4 Moses ga helekai gi digau Israel huogodoo, “Deenei telekai Dimaadua ne hai:
\v 5 Heia tigidaumaha gi Dimaadua. Di ingoo hua tangada e hiihai la gi gaamai dana tigidaumaha goolo, silber, be di baalanga mmee;
\v 6 nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, luuli halatee, mo mmee, mo nia gahu ne hai gi nia ngaahulu kuudi;
\v 7 nia gili dama siibi daane gu hagammee, nia gili nia manu, nia laagau ‘acacia’;
\v 8 nia lolo gi nia malama, nia mee hagakala lolo hagatulu mo nia ‘incense’;
\v 9 nia hadu hagalabagau ‘onyx’ mono hadu hagamadamada ala i golo e humu di ‘ephod’ mo di mee gahu hadahada tagi aamua hai mee dabu.
\s1 Nia goloo di Hale laa Dimaadua
\r (Exodus 39.32-43)
\p 
\v 10 “Digau hau mee i godou lodo huogodoo e hai loo gii hai nia mee huogodoo ala ne hagi anga go Dimaadua:
\v 11 go di Hale laa, dono gahu mo gahu laa tua, ono maadau mo ono abaaba, ono giodo, duludulu mo nadau lohongo;
\v 12 Tebedebe di Hagababa, ono duludulu, dono uhi, mo di gahu duuli e duuli gi daha di maa,
\v 13 teebele, ono duludulu mo ono goloo ala i golo mo di palaawaa tigidaumaha ang gi God,
\v 14 di lohongo malama mo ono goloo, nia malama mo nadau lolo;
\v 15 di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha lolo kala mo ono duludulu; nia lolo hagatulu; nia ‘incense’, di gahu duuli di bontai di Hale laa.
\v 16 di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha mo dono haaligi mee e hagapigi anga gi ono duludulu, ono waduu amu, mo ono mee ala i golo huogodoo; di baisin tonotono mo dono lohongo,
\v 17 nia gahu duuli di abaaba mo nadau duludulu mo nadau lohongo waduu, mo tuuli o di bontai di abaaba e duuli di Hale laa,
\v 18 nia daula e daahi nia loahi di Hale laa, mo di abaaba e duuli di Hale laa,
\v 19 mo nia gahu hagalabagau o digau aamua hai mee dabu ala e ulu ai ma ga hai hegau i lodo di Gowaa Dabu, go nia gahu hagamadagu a Aaron, tangada hai mee dabu, mo ana dama daane.”
\s1 Nia daangada e gaamai nadau tigidaumaha
\p 
\v 20 Digau Israel huogodoo gu hagatanga gi daha mo Moses,
\v 21 gei digau huogodoo ala gu hiihai, ginaadou gu gaamai nadau tigidaumaha gi Dimaadua e hau ai di Hale laa Dimaadua, mo nia mee huogodoo ala e hai hegau ai i di nadau hai daumaha mo nia mee ala e hai ai nia gahu digau hai mee dabu aamua.
\v 22 Gei digau huogodoo ala gu hiihai, nia ahina mono daane gu gaamai nadau tigidaumaha biini guu humu, nia buulei dalinga, nia buulei, nia hau uwa, mo nnagadilinga goloo goolo madamada, gei gu hagadabu nia maa ang gi Dimaadua.
\v 23 Digau huogodoo ala nadau gahu humalia e logo gu gaamai nia gahu gi nnadunga halatee, luuli halatee, mo mmee, mo nia gahu ala ne hai gi nia ngaahulu kuudi.
\v 24 Huogodoo ala ne mee di dahi aga nadau baalanga silber be baalanga mmee, gu gaamai nadau tigidaumaha gi Dimaadua, ge huogodoo nadau laagau ‘acacia’ ala e mee di hai hegau ai, gu gaamai nia maa.
\v 25 Nia ahina huogodoo ala e iloo di hai nia mee, gu gaamai nia gahu gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee ala ne hagamadamada go ginaadou.
\v 26 Digaula guu hai labelaa nadau deleedu gi nia ngaahulu manu kuudi.
\v 27 Nia dagi gu gaamai nadau hadu hagalabagau ‘onyx’ mono hadu hagamadamada ala i golo belee dugu gi lodo di ‘ephod’ mo di mee gahu hadahada,
\v 28 mo nia mee hagakala mee mo nia lolo ang gi nia malama, nia lolo hagatulu mo nia ‘incense’.
\v 29 Digau Israel huogodoo ala ne hiihai gu gaamai nadau tigidaumaha gi Dimaadua ang gi dana moomee ne hagi anga go Moses bolo gi heia.
\s1 Digau ngalua di Hale laa Dimaadua
\r (Exodus 31.1-11)
\p 
\v 30 Moses ga helekai gi digau Israel bolo Dimaadua gu hilihili Bezalel, tama daane a Uri, go tama daane Hur, mai di madawaawa Judah.
\v 31 God gu hagahonu a mee gi ono mogobuna, guu wanga ono iloo di hai nia mee mo dono iloo di hai nnagadilinga moomee hagamadamada mee,
\v 32 ang gi nia bilaan nia mee humalia e haga hai hegau nia maa gi nia goolo, silber mo nia baalanga mmee;
\v 33 e duuduu nia hadu hagalabagau ala belee haganoho; e iloo di paa nia laagau, mo nia hagadilinga moomee haga madamada mee ala i golo.
\v 34 Dimaadua gu hilihili labelaa Oholiab, tama daane Ahisamach, mai di madawaawa Dan, ge guu wanga gi meemaa nia iloo di aago nau hai moomee gi digau ala i golo.
\v 35 Mee guu wanga nia iloo o nnagadilinga hai moomee nogo hai go digau paa mee, digau haganoho mee, mo digau llanga nnagadilinga gahu gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee habuihabula. Digaula e iloo di hai nnagadilinga moomee ge digau e iloo di haganoho nia mee.
\c 36
\p 
\v 1 Bezalel, Oholiab mo digau ngalua huogodoo ala i golo ne wanga nadau iloo go Dimaadua ge gu iloo di hai nia mee huogodoo ala belee hau di Hale laa hagamadagu, la belee hai nia mee huogodoo gii hai be nnelekai Dimaadua ne hai.
\s1 Nia daangada e gaamai nia wanga dehuia e logo
\p 
\v 2 Moses ga gahi mai Bezalel, Oholiab mo nia daane ala e iloo di hai nia mee ala ne wanga nadau iloo go Dimaadua, go digau ala e hiihai e hagamaamaa, gei Moses ga helekai gi digaula gi daamada di nadau moomee.
\v 3 Digaula guu kumi nia wanga dehuia huogodoo digau Israel ne gaamai ang gi di hau di Hale laa hagamadagu. Digau Israel e duudagi adu hua nadau gagaamai nadau wanga dehuia gi Moses i nia luada huogodoo.
\v 4 Nia daane nogo hai di moomee gaa hula,
\v 5 ga helekai gi Moses bolo nia daangada e gaamai nia wanga dehuia e logo balua ang gi di moomee Dimaadua bolo gi heia.
\p 
\v 6 Moses gaa hai dana hagailoo bolo tangada labelaa e gaamai dana wanga dehuia gi di Hale laa ai, gei nia daangada gu hagalee gaamai nadau mee.
\v 7 Nia mee ala gu dahi aga go nia daangada la gu dohu balua di hagalawa di moomee.
\s1 Di hau di Hale laa Dimaadua
\r (Exodus 26.1-37)
\p 
\v 8 Di Hale laa Dimaadua la ne hau go digau koia e iloo di hai moomee. Digaula ne hau di maa gi nia bida gahu e madangaholu ne llanga gi nia linen e dui gi nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, ge guu humu gi nia ada manu ono bakau.
\v 9 Nia bida gahu duuli e tongaadahi 14 ‘yard’ looloo ge 2 ‘yard’ palaha.
\v 10 Digaula guu dui nia bida gahu e lima gii hai di gunga gahu e dahi, ne hai labelaa beelaa gi nia bida gahu duuli e lima ala i golo.
\v 11 Digaula guu dui nia mee bida gahu halatee hagabungubungu gi taalinga di tua o nia gunga gahu e lua aalaa.
\v 12 Digaula guu wanga nia gahu hagabungubungu e 50 gi taalinga di gahu matagidagi o di gunga gahu dela ne hagapuni matagidagi, ge 50 gahu hagabungubungu gi taalinga di gahu hagamuliagina o di gunga gahu dela i golo.
\v 13 Digaula guu hai nia maadau goolo e 50 e nneenagi nia baahi gahu e lua gi di gowaa e dahi, e hai di mee e dahi.
\p 
\v 14 Digaula guu hai di gahu di Hale laa gi nia bida gahu e 11 ne hai gi nia ngaahulu kuudi.
\v 15 Digaula guu hai nia maa gi tongaadahi, 15 ‘yard’ looloo, 2 ‘yard’ palaha.
\v 16 Digaula guu dui nia gahu e lima gii hai di gunga gahu e dahi, mo nia gahu e ono gii hai di hoo di maa.
\v 17 Digaula e wanga nia buulei gahu e 50 gi taalinga di bida gahu muliagina ge 50 buulei gahu gi taalinga di hoo di maa.
\v 18 Digaula guu hai nia maadau baalanga mmee e 50, e nneenagi nia gunga gahu Hale laa e lua gii hai di mee e dahi.
\v 19 Digaula guu hai labelaa nia gahu Hale laa e lua, e dahi ne hai gi nia gili siibi daane gu haga mmee, ge di hoo di maa ne hai gi nia gili kau humalia e daudau gi nua i taalinga di Hale laa e gahu di maa.
\p 
\v 20 Digaula guu hai nia waduu di Hale laa gi nia laagau ‘acacia’.
\v 21 Di waduu e dahi e 15 piidi looloo, ge 27 ‘inch’ palaha.
\v 22 Nia waduu huogodoo e hagalloo ono mee e lua i nia bida gi daha gii mee di duudagi nia maa, gii hai di mee e dahi. Nia waduu huogodoo e hai ono duudagi beenei.
\v 23 Digaula guu hai nia waduu e 20 gi di baahi ngeia,
\v 24 ge 40 haaligi silber i nadau lala, nia haaligi e lua i lala di waduu e dahi, e daahi nia laagau duudagi e lua.
\v 25 Digaula ne hai nia waduu e 20 gi di baahi ngaaga,
\v 26 ge nia haaligi silber e 40, e lua haaligi i lala di waduu e dahi.
\v 27 Digaula guu hai nia waduu e ono gi tua di Hale laa dela i bahi i dai di maa,
\v 28 ge e lua waduu gi nia madaaduge.
\v 29 Nia waduu o nia madaaduge e duudagi i baahi lala gaa hana gaa tugi i di ulu gi nua. Nia waduu e lua ala e hai nia madaaduge e lua la ne hai beenei.
\v 30 Huogodoo ga iai nia waduu e 8, ge 16 haaligi baalanga silber, e lua i lala di waduu e dahi.
\p 
\v 31 Digaula guu hai nia giodo gi nia laagau ‘acacia’, e lima gi nia waduu i di baahi e dahi di Hale laa,
\v 32 e lima ang gi nia waduu i di baahi dela i golo, ge e lima gi nia waduu i baahi dai, dela i tua di Hale laa.
\v 33 Di giodo tungaalodo gu haganoho tungaalodo nia ogo e hana e tugi i nia mada di Hale laa.
\v 34 Digaula guu hii nia hagamau gi nia goolo gu hagamau nia maa gi nia buulei goolo e daahi nia ogo laagau guu hii labelaa gi nia goolo.
\p 
\v 35 Digaula guu hai di gahu duuli humalia ne dui gi nia deleedu gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, ge guu humu gi nia duain gi nia ada nia manu nadau bakau.
\v 36 Digaula guu hai nia duludulu e haa gi nia laagau ‘acacia’ e daahi nia gahu duuli aalaa, guu hii nia maa gi nia goolo, guu wanga ginai nia maadau goolo. Digaula guu hai nia haaligi baalanga silber e haa e daahi nia duludulu.
\v 37 Digaula guu dui di duuli di bontai o di Hale laa gi nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, ge guu humu gi nia duain.
\v 38 Digaula guu hai nia duludulu e lima ang gi di gahu duuli deenei, ge guu wanga ginai ono maadau; digaula guu hii ono ulu gi nua mo nia laagau e daudau di gahu gi nia goolo, ge gu hai nia lohongo duludulu e lima gi nia baalanga mmee.
\c 37
\s1 Tebedebe di Hagababa
\r (Exodus 25.10-22)
\p 
\v 1 Bezalel guu hai Tebedebe di Hagababa gi di laagau ‘acacia’, nia ‘inch’ 45 di looloo, 27 ‘inch’ palaha, 27 ‘inch’ tuuduu gi nua.
\v 2 Mee guu hii di maa gi nia goolo madammaa i lodo mo i tua, gaa hai dono daalinga gi nia goolo e haganiga di maa.
\v 3 Mee guu hai ana buulei goolo e haa e dagidagi di maa, gaa hau gi nia wae e haa, nia buulei e lua i di baahi e dahi.
\v 4 Mee guu hai nia laagau aamo gi nia laagau ‘acacia’, guu hii nia maa gi nia goolo,
\v 5 ga daalo nia maa laa lodo nia buulei i nia baahi o Tebedebe.
\v 6 Mee guu hai di uhi gi nia goolo madammaa, 45 ‘inch’ looloo mo 27 ‘inch’ palaha.
\v 7 Mee guu hai nia manu goolo e lua e hai nau bakau,
\v 8 e dahi ang gi di bida e dahi o di uhi. Mee ne hai nia manu e buni anga gi di uhi, e hai be di mee e dahi ne hai.
\v 9 Nia manu nau bakau e huli mai nau hadumada gi lodo i hongo di uhi, ge nau bakau moholo guu gahu di uhi.
\s1 Teebele ang gi nia Palaawaa Hagamadagu
\p 
\v 10 Mee ne hai teebele gi nia laagau ‘acacia’, 36 ‘inch’ looloo, 18 ‘inch’ palaha, mo 27 ‘inch’ tuuduu i nua.
\v 11 Mee guu hii di maa gi nia goolo madammaa, guu hai dono daalinga gi nia goolo e haganiga di maa.
\v 12 Mee guu hai taalinga di maa nia ‘inch’ e 3 palaha e haganiga dono gili, mo dono hagageinga goolo taalinga i tua.
\v 13 Mee guu hai nia buulei goolo e haa e dagidagi di maa, gu haganoho i nia madaaduge e haa di gowaa nia wae.
\v 14 Nia buulei ala e daahi nia laagau aamo Tebedebe la ne wanga gi hoohoo gi taalinga di haganiga.
\v 15 Mee ne hai nia laagau aamo gi nia laagau ‘acacia’ gaa hii nia maa gi nia goolo.
\v 16 Mee guu hai nia goloo deebele gi nia goolo madammaa: nia pileedi, ibu, ibu galaadi mo nia boolo ang gi tigidaumaha waini.
\s1 Di Lohongo Malama
\r (Exodus 25.31-40)
\p 
\v 17 Mee guu hai di Lohongo Malama gi nia goolo madammaa. Mee ne hai di tono di maa mo tuaidina di Lohongo Malama gi nia goolo ne tugi. Ono akai humu mo nia lau o nia akai la ne hau gii hai di mee e dahi gi di Lohongo Malama.
\v 18 Nia manga e ono e tolo gi daha, e dolu i di baahi e dahi.
\v 19 Di manga e dahi o nia manga e ono aalaa, e hai ono akai humu e dolu, dono ada e hai be di akai ‘almond’ ma ga moholoholo.
\v 20 Tuaidina o di Lohongo Malama la iai ono akai e haa, dono ada e hai be di akai ‘almond’ ma ga moholoholo.
\v 21 Di akai daamada moholoholo kala e dahi i baahi lala nia manga dagi dolu.
\v 22 Nia akai e daamada e moholoholo, nia manga, mo tuaidina di Lohongo Malama ne dugidugi gi di baahi goolo e dahi.
\v 23 Mee guu hai nia malama e hidu ang gi di Lohongo Malama. Mee ne hai nia mee hagamadammaa uga malama mono mee haaligi gi nia goolo madammaa.
\v 24 Mee ne hai hegau gi nia pauna e 75 goolo madammaa e hai di Lohongo Malama mo ono goloo huogodoo.
\s1 Di gowaa dudu mee tigidaumaha lolo kala
\r (Exodus 30.1-5)
\p 
\v 25 Mee guu hai di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha gi nia laagau ‘acacia’ e dudu nia ‘incense’. Di looloo mo di palaha e hagatau be di mee e dahi, nia ‘inch’ e 18 gei tuuduu gi nua nia ‘inch’ e 36. Nia madaagoo e haa ala e tolo gi daha i nia madaaduge la ne hai gii hai di mee e dahi gi tuaidina.
\v 26 Mee guu hii di ulu gi nua, nia baahi e haa mo nia madaagoo gi nia goolo madammaa, gu haganiga taalinga di maa gi nia goolo.
\v 27 Mee guu hai nia buulei e lua gi nia goolo e dagidagi di maa, gaa hau gi baahi lala taalinga o nia baahi e lua e daahi nia laagau aamo.
\v 28 Mee guu hai nia laagau aamo gi nia laagau ‘acacia’, gaa hii nia maa gi nia goolo.
\s1 Nia lolo hagatulu mo nia ‘incense’
\p 
\v 29 Mee guu hai labelaa di lolo hagatulu hagamadagu mo nia ‘incense’ e unugi be di lolo kala.\x * \xo 37.29 \xt Exodus 30.22-38\x*
\c 38
\s1 Di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha
\r (Exodus 27.1-8)
\p 
\v 1 Mee guu hai di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha gi nia laagau ‘acacia’. Di maa e looloo nia piidi e 7½, piidi e 7½ palaha, ge nia piidi e 4½ tuuduu i nua.
\v 2 Mee guu hai nia madaagoo e haa i hongo nia madaaduge e haa gu hagabuni gi di gowaa e dahi gi di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha. Mee guu hii di maa hagatau gi di baalanga mmee.
\v 3 Mee guu hai nia goloo huogodoo ala e hai hegau ai i di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha: nia mee baabaa dunu mee, nia daawolo, nia boolo, nia poogi, mo nia mee dugu ahi. Nia goloo huogodoo aanei la ne hai gi nia baalanga mmee.
\v 4 Mee guu hai dana hada baalanga mmee, gu haganiga i taalinga di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha, gaa tugi i tungaalodo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha.
\v 5 Mee guu hai ana buulei e haa e dagidagi di maa, gaa hau gi nia madaaduge e haa.
\v 6 Mee guu hai nia laagau aamo mee gi nia laagau ‘acacia’, gaa hii nia maa gi nia baalanga mmee,
\v 7 ga daalo nia maa gi lodo nia buulei ala i nia baahi di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha. Di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha ne hai gi nia laubaba, gei e bongoo laa lodo.
\s1 Di baisin baalanga mmee
\r (Exodus 30.18)
\p 
\v 8 Mee guu hai di baisin baalanga mmee mo dono lohongo baalanga mmee gi nia kalaadi mmada ada o nia ahina ala e ngalua i di ngudu di bontai di Hale laa Dimaadua.\x * \xo 38.8 \xt Exodus 30.18\x*
\s1 Di abaaba e duuli di Hale laa Dimaadua
\r (Exodus 27.9-19)
\p 
\v 9 Mee guu hai di duuli di Hale laa dela e noho ai Dimaadua gi di gahu lenge humalia. I di baahi gi ngaaga di Hale laa le e looloo nia ‘yard’ e 50,
\v 10 e daahi go nia duludulu baalanga mmee e 20 ala e haganoho gi lodo nadau lohongo duludulu baalanga mmee e 20, dalia nia maadau mono amu daahi ne hai gi nia silber.
\v 11 Tuuli i baahi gi ngeia le e hai hua be tuuli i baahi gi ngaaga.
\v 12 I di baahi gi dai, nia gahu duuli le e 25 ‘yard’ looloo, ono waduu e 10 ge 10 lohongo waduu, madalia nia maadau mono amu daahi ne hai gi nia silber.
\v 13 I di baahi gi dua i di gowaa dela iai di bontai, di tuuli le e palaha labelaa nia ‘yard’ e 25.
\v 14-15 I nia baahi e lua o di bontai, nia ‘yard’ gahu duuli e 7½ i golo, e daahi go nia waduu e dolu mo nadau lohongo waduu e dolu.
\v 16 Nia gahu lenge duuli huogodoo la ne hai gi nia gahu lenge humalia.
\v 17 Nia lohongo nia waduu la ne hai gi nia baalanga mmee, gei nia maadau, amu, mo di gahu di ulu gi nua nia waduu ne hai gi nia silber. Nia duludulu huogodoo ala e haganiga di abaaba le e duudagi gi nia amu silber.
\v 18 Di gahu duuli gi di bontai di abaaba duuli, ne hai gi di gahu lenge ne dui gi nia gahu gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, ge guu humu gi nia duain. Ma e looloo nia ‘yard’ e 10, nia ‘yard’ 2½ tuuduu i nua, e hai be nia gahu o di abaaba.
\v 19 Ma e daahi go nia waduu e haa i hongo nadau lohongo baalanga mmee e haa. Nia maadau nia maa, nia gahu laa nua, mo nia amu nia maa le e gahu gi nia silber.
\v 20 Nia daula di Hale laa mo nia daula o di abaaba huogodoo la ne hai gi nia baalanga mmee.
\p 
\v 21 Aanei nia baalanga ne hai hegau ai i di hau di Hale laa Dimaadua, di gowaa dela nogo benebene nia baahi hadu e lua Madangaholu Haganoho. Nia baalanga ne tiumongo go Moses, ne hai go digau Levi nogo ngalua i lala Ithamar, tama daane Aaron, tangada hai mee dabu.
\p 
\v 22 Bezalel, tama daane Uri, dono damana madua go Hur mai di madawaawa Judah, guu hai nia mee huogodoo a Dimaadua ne helekai ai bolo gi heia.
\v 23 Dono dangada hagamaamaa la go Oholiab tama daane Ahisamach, mai di madawaawa Dan, tangada dugidugi mee, dili mee mo llanga nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee gi habuihabula.
\p 
\v 24 Nia goolo huogodoo ala ne wanga gi Dimaadua belee hai dono Hale laa e daamaha nia pauna e 2,195, e pauna gi di hai dela e mogobuna di hai hegau.
\v 25 Nia silber ala ne hagabudu mai di dau o nia daangada tenua e daamaha nia pauna e 7550, e pauna gi di hai dela e mogobuna di hai hegau.\x * \xo 38.25 \xt Exodus 30.11-16\x*
\v 26 Di hulu deenei le e hai be di hulu ne hui go digau huogodoo ala ne ianga di tau, tangada e dahi e hui di hulu dela belee hui, e pauna gi di hai dela e mogobuna di hai hegau. Nia daane e 603,550 nadau ngadau e madalua be mada mmaadua nadau ngadau i lodo di dau.\x * \xo 38.26 \xt Matthew 17.24\x*
\v 27 Nia pauna silber 7,500 ne hai hegau ne hau nia lohongo waduu e 100 ang gi di Hale laa dabu mo ang gi nia gahu duuli, 75 pauna ne hai hegau gi di lohongo hagamau e dahi.
\v 28 Bezalel gu hai hegau gi nia pauna silber 50 ala ne dubu, guu hai ana amu, nia maadau ang gi nia waduu, mo di gahu laa hongo nia ulu o nia duludulu.
\v 29 Nia baalanga mmee ala ne wanga gi Dimaadua la nia pauna e 5,310,
\v 30 gu hai hegau iei mee gi nia lohongo waduu o di bontai di Hale laa Dimaadua, di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha baalanga mmee mo dono hada baalanga mmee, nia goloo huogodoo ang gi di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha,
\v 31 nia lohongo waduu o di abaaba mai daha mo ang gi di bontai di abaaba mo nia laagau daula e daahi di Hale laa mo tuuli di abaaba mai daha.
\c 39
\s1 Di hai o nia gahu digau hai mee dabu
\r (Exodus 28.1-14)
\p 
\v 1 Digaula guu hai hagamadamada nia gahu gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, e ulu ai digau hai mee dabu ma gaa hai nadau hegau i lodo nia gowaa dabu. Digaula ne hai nia gahu Aaron gii hai be nnelekai Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses.
\p 
\v 2 Digaula ne hai di gahu ‘ephod’ gi nia gahu humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, gei nia duain gili siibi halatee ne hai gi nia goolo.
\v 3 Digaula gu dugidugi di baalanga goolo gi palaha gi lahilahi ga duuduu gii hai be nia loahi deleedu e hagaulu gi lodo di gahu lenge duuli mo gi lodo nia duain gili siibi halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee.
\v 4 Digaula guu hai nia daulagi di ‘ephod’ e lua, guu dui gi nia baahi e lua, e daulagi ai di ‘ephod’.
\v 5 Di tuu guu llanga hagalligi gi humalia dela ne hai gi nia goloo la hua, gu duudagi gi di ‘ephod’, guu hai di bida mee e dahi, gii hai be nnelekai Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses.
\v 6 Digaula gu hagatogomaalia nia damaa hadu hagalabagau ‘onyx’ ga haganoho gi nadau lohongo goolo, gaa hihi gi nonua nia ingoo nia dama Jacob dilongoholu maa lua.
\v 7 Digaula gaa dugu nia maa gi hongo nia hagamau di gahu ‘ephod’, e pono nia madawaawaa madangaholu maa lua o Israel, gii hai be nnelekai Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses.
\s1 Di mee gahu hadahada
\r (Exodus 28.15-30)
\p 
\v 8 Digaula ne hai di mee gahu hadahada gi nia goloo la hua ala ne hai di ‘ephod’, ge guu humu gi nia duain be di maa.
\v 9 Tuuli deenei le e hai ono hagatau be di mee e dahi, ge hadui hagalua; dono palaha mo dono looloo e 9 ‘inch’.
\v 10 Digaula gu hagatau nia goolongo hadu hagalabagau e haa gi hongo di maa. Di goolongo matagidagi, digaula gu hagatau nia ‘ruby’, ‘topaz’ mo di ‘garnet’.
\v 11 I di lua goolongo, di ‘emerald’, di ‘sapphire’, di ‘diamond’.
\v 12 I tolu goolongo, di ‘turquoise’, di ‘agate’ mo di ‘amethyst’.
\v 13 Di haa goolongo, di ‘beryl’, di ‘onyx’, mo di ‘jasper’. Nia hadu aanei ne haganoho gi nia lohongo goolo.
\v 14 Nia hadu dagidahi e 12 aanei la guu hihi ginai nia ingoo nia dama daane Jacob, e pono nia madawaawa 12 o Israel.
\v 15 Di mee gahu hadahada guu hai dono daulagi goolo madammaa dela gu bini be di mee ne daga.
\v 16 Digaula guu hai nia ada goolo e lua mo nia buulei goolo e lua, guu wanga nia buulei e lua gi nia madaaduge baahi nua e lua o di mee gahu hadahada.
\v 17 Digaula gu nneennagi di uga mo di buulei goolo gi di gowaa e dahi,
\v 18 ga duudagi nia mada e lua o di uga gi nia hagatau e lua, i di hai deenei gu duudagi nia maa i mua gi nia daulagi o di ‘ephod’.
\v 19 Digaula guu hai nia buulei goolo e lua, ga hagapigi nia maa gi nia madaaduge baahi gi lala o di mee gahu hadahada, i taalinga baahi gi lodo e tale gi di ‘ephod’.
\v 20 Digaula guu hai labelaa nia buulei goolo e lua, guu wanga nia maa gi di baahi i lala i mua nia daulagi bakau e lua o di ‘ephod’, hoohoo gi duudagi, ge baahi nua di tuu guu llanga hagalligi gi humalia.
\v 21 Digaula guu nnoo nia buulei o di mee gahu hadahada gi nia buulei o di ‘ephod’ gi di loahi halatee bolo di mee gahu hadahada gi daudau mau i hongo di tuu ge hagalee mehede, gii hai be nnelekai Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses.
\s1 Nia gahu o digau hai mee dabu ala i golo
\r (Exodus 28.31-43)
\p 
\v 22 Di gahu looloo dela e ulu gi baahi gi lodo di ‘ephod’ la ne hai hagatau gi di gahu halatee.
\v 23 Di bongoo di libogo la ne dui gi nia gahu llanga maadolu e duuli di maa gi hagalee mahaa.
\v 24-26 Taalinga di gahu gi lala hagatau la guu hai nia ada ‘pomegranate’ ne hai gi nia gahu gili siibi humalia gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, e wanga hagadau gi nia beele goolo madammaa i nadau mehanga, gii hai be nnelekai Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses.
\v 27 Digaula guu hai nia gahu Aaron mo ana dama daane,
\v 28 mo nadau angkadi nnoo libogo, goobai, bida gahu wae tiligi,
\v 29 mo di tuu nnoo gahu ne hai gi nia gahu gili siibi gi nnadunga halatee, halatee luuli mo mmee, ge guu humu gi nia duain, gii hai be nnelekai Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses.
\v 30 Digaula guu hai di mee humu mee madamada gi nia goolo madammaa, e hai di hagamodongoohia di hagadabu dabuaahia, gei digaula gu maaga gi hongo di maa “Hagadabu gi Dimaadua”.
\v 31 Digaula guu nnoo di maa gi mua di gahu libogo gi di loahi halatee gii hai be nnelekai Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses.
\s1 Di hagalawa di moomee
\r (Exodus 35.10-19)
\p 
\v 32 Nia moomee huogodoo ala nogo hai gi di Hale laa, di gowaa e noho ai Dimaadua, la guu lawa. Digau Israel guu hai nia mee huogodoo ala ne hagi anga go Dimaadua gi Moses.
\v 33 Digaula gu gaamai gi Moses di Hale laa, mo nia goloo ngalua, maadau, mo ono abaaba, nia giodo hale, nia duludulu, mo nia lohongo duludulu;
\v 34 di gahu ne hai nia gili dama siibi daane gu hagammee, di gahu ne hai gi nia gili nia manu, di gahu duuli,
\v 35 Tebedebe o di Hagababa dela e haa nia baahi hadu, nia waduu aamo di maa, mo dono uhi;
\v 36 teebele mo ono goloo huogodoo, mo di palaawaa tigidaumaha ang gi God;
\v 37 di lohongo malama goolo madammaa, ono malama mo ono goloo huogodoo, mono lolo ang gi nia malama;
\v 38 di gowaa hai tigidaumaha goolo; nia lolo hagatulu, nia ‘incense’, di gahu duuli di bontai di Hale laa;
\v 39 di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha baalanga mmee, mo dono haaligi ne hai gi nia baalanga mmee, nia waduu amu, mo ono goloo huogodoo, di baisin tonotono mo dono lohongo;
\v 40 nia gahu duuli ang gi di abaaba e duuli di Hale laa, mo nia duludulu mo nadau lohongo, di gahu duuli gi di bontai di abaaba mo ono loahi, nia laagau dogi e daahi di Hale laa, mo nia goloo huogodoo ala e hai hegau i lodo di Hale laa;
\v 41 mo nia gahu hagalabagau o digau hai mee dabu ala e ulu ai i lodo di Gowaa Dabu go nia gahu dabu a Aaron tangada hai mee dabu mo ana dama daane.
\p 
\v 42 Digau Israel guu lawa di hai nia hegau huogodoo gii hai be nnelekai Dimaadua ne hai gi Moses.
\v 43 Moses gu hagadina nia mee huogodoo gu gidee bolo digaula guu hai nia mee huogodoo be di hiihai a Dimaadua ne helekai ai. Moses gu hagamaluagina digaula.
\c 40
\s1 Di hagaduu aga mo di hagadabu di Hale laa Dimaadua
\p 
\v 1 Dimaadua ga helekai gi Moses,
\v 2 “I di laangi matagidagi o di malama matagidagi, hagaduu aga ina di Hale laa Dimaadua.
\v 3 Duguina Tebedebe di Hagababa dela e haa ginai nia baahi hadu o di Madangaholu Haganoho, daudaulia di gahu duuli i mua di maa.
\v 4 Kaina teebele gi lodo, dugua nia goloo huogodoo gi hongo di maa. Kaina labelaa di lohongo malama gi lodo, wanga ina nia malama gi hongo di maa.
\v 5 Dugua di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha goolo e dudu nia ‘incense’ i mua Tebedebe di Hagababa, daudaulia di gahu duuli i di ngudu di bontai di Hale laa.
\v 6 Dugua gi mua di Hale laa di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha e dudu nia tigidaumaha.
\v 7 Dugua di baisin tonotono i mehanga di Hale laa mo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha, haga haulia gi nia wai.
\v 8 Haganoho ina di gahu duuli di abaaba di maa, daudaulia di gahu duuli i di ngudu di bontai di maa.
\p 
\v 9 “Hagadabu ina di Hale laa mono goloo huogodoo gi di lolo hagamadagu hagatulu, gei di maa gaa dabu.
\v 10 Nomuli, hagadabu ina di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha mono goloo huogodoo gi di lolo hagamadagu hagatulu, gei di maa ga dabuaahia.
\v 11 Hagadabu ina labelaa di baisin tonotono mo dono lohongo i di ala hua e dahi.
\p 
\v 12 “Laha mai a Aaron mo ana dama daane gi di bontai di Hale laa, gaugaulia digaula gi di hai e hagamadammaa digaula.
\v 13 Hagagahu ina Aaron gi ono goloo hai mee dabu, hagatulu ina a mee. Di hai deenei e hai a mee gii dabu gii mee a mee di hai dagu dangada hai hegau.
\v 14 Laha mai ana dama daane, hagagahu ina digaula.
\v 15 Hagatulu ina digaula, be di hai ne hagatulu di nadau damana, gii mee digaula di hai agu daangada hai mee dabu. Di hagatulu deenei gaa hai digaula gii hai nia daangada hai mee dabu i nia madagoaa huogodoo ala e lloomoi.”
\p 
\v 16 Moses guu hai nia mee huogodoo a Dimaadua bolo gi heia.
\v 17 Tahi laangi o tahi malama o di lua ngadau o di nadau hagatanga mai i Egypt, gei di Hale laa Dimaadua ga haga duu aga.
\v 18 Moses gaa dugu nia lohongo waduu o di hale laa, ga haga noho di maa, nomuli ga haga tuu nia duludulu.
\v 19 Gaa lawa, gaa holo di gahu gili manu laa hongo di Hale laa, gaa gahu labelaa laa tua, gii hai be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai.
\v 20 Gaa lawa, gaa haa nia baahi hadu e lua ala ne hihi ginai di Madangaholu Haganoho gi lodo Tebedebe o di Hagababa. Gaa lawa, gaa wanga nia laagau ala e dagidagi di maa gi lodo nia buulei, gaa lawa gaa uhi.
\v 21 Gaa lawa, gaa kae Tebedebe gi lodo di Hale laa, gaa lawa gaa dau tuuli di maa be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai.
\v 22 Gaa lawa, ga haga noho dana deebele gi lodo di Hale laa, i di bahi i ngeia, i daha mo tuuli,
\v 23 gaa dugu di palaawaa dela gu tigidaumaha gi Dimaadua gi nonua, be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai,
\v 24 ga haga noho di lohongo malama i lodo di Hale laa i bahi i ngaaga, e huudonu gi teebele,
\v 25 gaa dudu nia malama i mua o Dimaadua, be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai,
\v 26 ga haga noho di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha lolo kala ne hai gi nia goolo, i lodo di Hale laa, i mua di tuuli,
\v 27 gaa dudu nia ‘incense’ i hongo di maa, be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai.
\v 28 Gaa lawa, gaa dau gi nua tuuli i di ngudu o di bontai di Hale laa,
\v 29 gaa dugu di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha la gi mua tuuli deelaa, gaa hai dana tigidaumaha dudu mo dana tigidaumaha huwa laagau i hongo di maa, gii hai be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai,
\v 30 ga haga noho dana baisin tonotono i mehanga di Hale laa mo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha, ga haga hau ginai nia wai.
\v 31 Moses mo Aaron mo nia dama daane a Aaron e tonotono nadau lima mo nadau wae i di gowaa deelaa,
\v 32 i nadau madagoaa huogodoo ma ga ulu i di Hale laa be gi di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha, gii hai be nia helekai a Dimaadua ne hai.
\v 33 Moses guu hai dana abaaba e duuli di Hale laa mo di gowaa dudu tigidaumaha, ge daudau tuuli i di ngudu o di bontai di abaaba. Moses gu haga lawa ana moomee nogo hai huogodoo.
\s1 Di gololangi i hongo di Hale laa Dimaadua
\r (Numbers 9.15-23)
\p 
\v 34 Di gololangi mo di madamada o Dimaadua gu hii hua di Hale laa, guu gahu hagatau.\x * \xo 40.34 \xt 1-Kings 8.10,11; Isaiah 6.4; Ezekiel 43.4,5; Revelation 15.8\x*
\v 35 Di gololangi mo di madamada o Dimaadua guu hai a Moses gi deemee di ulu gi lodo di Hale laa.
\v 36 Nia madagoaa huogodoo di gololangi ma gaa maa gi daha mo hongo di Hale laa, gei digau Israel guu mee di hagatanga i di gowaa deelaa.
\v 37 Maa di gololangi la ga hagalee maa gi daha, ge digaula hagalee hagatanga, e tali loo di laangi dela e maa ai di gololangi, ga hula laa.
\v 38 I lodo hua nadau taele huogodoo, digaula guu mmada gi di gololangi o Dimaadua le e dehedehee i hongo di Hale laa i di aa, ma gaa boo la di ulaula. 
